title: broiled lobster tail
directions: Place lobster tails in large saucepan.
Add remaining ingredients.
Bring to boiling point.
Cover and cook 20 minutes. Remove tails from water.
Split in half with sharp knife.
Serve with melted butter.

title: lo-cal yogurt pie
directions: Mix or blend yogurt and whipped cream until smooth.
Pour into pie shell.
Refrigerate until solid, about 3 hours.
Garnish with fresh strawberries or fruit of your choice.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Butter dish.
Put beans, then corn.
Mix soup, cheese, sour cream and onion.
Put on top 1 roll crackers with 1 stick margarine (crumble).
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: coffee bars
directions: Combine raisins, coffee and cinnamon; let stand.
Cream shortening and sugar; add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Mix and sift flour, baking powder, baking soda and salt; add to mixture.
Gradually add to this the coffee mixture. Spread the batter in greased shallow 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Try with a toothpick.
While warm, spread with glaze.

title: chili louisiana-style
directions: Combine first four ingredients and brown in a large frying pan.
Drain all excess fat.

title: crisp crusted baked chicken
directions: Wash chicken pieces and pat dry.
Beat eggs and milk in bowl. In another bowl mix potatoes, garlic powder and grated cheese. Roll chicken first in egg mix, then in potato mixture.
Melt butter in shallow baking pan.
Roll coated chicken pieces in butter and place them skin side up in pan.
Bake at 400° for 45 to 50 minutes, or until juices from thighs run clear when pierced with fork. Serve with celery for garnish.

title: beef and cabbage rolls
directions: Combine meats, salt, pepper, onion and rice and shape into rolls.
Remove the core from cabbage; place cabbage in 1 quart water in saucepan and steam until leaves begin to wilt.
Separate cabbage leaves and wrap meat rolls in a cabbage leaf.
Secure with toothpicks and place in a casserole dish.
Combine tomato sauce, salt, pepper and Worcestershire sauce and pour over cabbage rolls. Cover casserole.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 30 minutes or until the rice is done.
Makes 10 servings.

title: chicken pasta
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Garnish with diced fresh tomatoes (optional).

title: hot apple cider
directions: Fill the lined basket of a large automatic percolator with the brown sugar, cloves, allspice and cinnamon stick.
Prepare as you would coffee according to manufacturer's directions but substitute with cider for water.
(Do not use a drip style coffemaker.) Makes 16 to 20 servings.

title: sausage stars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine sausage with cheese, salad dressing, olives and red peppers.
Lightly grease muffin tins, and press won ton wrapper in each cup.
Brush with oil.
Bake for 5 minutes, until golden brown.
Remove from tins; place on baking sheets.
Fill with sausage mixture.
Bake for 5 minutes, until bubbly.
Makes 4 to 5 dozen.

title: aunt doris' tostado salad
directions: * These ingredients may be mixed in the blender.

title: cracker barrel hash brown casserole(nelda's recipe)
directions: Herman is a sourdough starter that can be used to make a number of baked goods.
"He" is simple to make and maintain.
It is traditional to nurture Herman.
Use part of the starter and share a cup with a friend.
You also need to
pass on the feeding instructions with the shared cup of starter

title: cool lemon angel food cake
directions: Prepare or purchase 1 large angel food cake. Cover and chill or freeze. In a heavy, medium saucepan, stir together the 1 1/2 cups sugar, the cornstarch and flour; gradually stir in water. Bring to boiling, stirring constantly. Reduce heat; cook and stir over medium heat for 2 minutes. Remove from heat. Gradually stir about 1 cup of the hot mixture into beaten egg yolks; pour yolk mixture back into remaining hot mixture in saucepan. Bring to a gentle boil; cook for 2 minutes more, stirring constantly. Remove from heat; stir in cut up butter and grated lemon peel. Slowly stir in 1/2 cup lemon juice. Pour into glass container; cover and chill several hours or overnight.

title: chicken and rice
directions: Pour all 4 cans of soup over rice and mix. Butter and season chicken breasts. Put rice in casserole dish. Add chicken on top. Cover and cook at 325° for 3 1/2 hours. Uncover the last 30 minutes and lift chicken up to brown.

title: yogurt pie
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients.
Pour into pie shells.
Let set in fridge overnight.

title: brownie pudding
directions: Mix all together; pour into a greased casserole dish.

title: cupcake brownies
directions: In a double boiler melt chocolate and butter.
Mix together flour and sugar.
Add eggs one at a time, stirring as little as possible.
Add vanilla, then chocolate mixture.
Add pecans and stir.
Pour mixture into paper baking cups in muffin pan.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes at 325°.
Makes 24.

title: candied sweet potatoes
directions: Boil sweet potatoes until soft; drain and mash.
Stir in butter and brown sugar to taste.
Put 1/2 of mixture in casserole dish.
Put a layer of marshmallows on, then put the rest of the potatoes on top.
Put a layer of marshmallows on top; dot with butter.
Sprinkle with brown sugar.
Add walnuts on top.
Cover and bake at 375° for 45 minutes.
Lower heat 25° for glass pan.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix the soup and sour cream together.
Mix onion, celery, stuffing and melted butter.
Layer, starting with chicken, then sour cream and soup and finally the stuffing mixture.
After completion of layering, pour 1 1/2 cups of broth over mixture. Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: nanny's sugar cream pie
directions: This pie is best if made directly in the pie shell.
First add sugar, flour, and salt in pie shell and mix well.
Next add the half and half, whipping cream, and vanilla.
Mix with index finger until sugar is dissolved.
Dot with butter.
Bake at 425° for 20 minutes then turn oven back to 350° and bake for approximately another 20-25 minutes.

title: pumpkin roll
directions: Line wax paper on cookie sheet.
Pour mixture on wax paper. Bake 15 minutes at 325°.
After baking, put on dish towel sprinkled with confectioners sugar.
Pull off wax paper and roll in jelly roll.
Let cool.

title: scalloped tomatoes
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Mix tomatoes, salt and pepper; pour into a greased 1 1/2-quart baking dish.
Pour melted butter over the bread crumbs; sprinkle bread crumbs on top of tomatoes.
Bake for 30 minutes at 325°.

title: beef patties parmesan
directions: Combine ground beef, biscuit mix, tomato juice, green pepper, egg, garlic and seasonings; mix lightly until ingredients are blended.
Shape into 4 patties and place in a greased shallow baking pan.
Bake in hot oven (400°) for 20 minutes.
Remove from oven; sprinkle each patty with about 2 teaspoons Parmesan cheese and garnish with olive slices.
Serve on a bed of buttered noodles.
Makes 4 servings.

title: peanut brittle - microwave
directions: In 1 1/2-quart casserole, stir together sugar and syrup.
Cook on High for 4 minutes.
Stir in peanuts.
Cook on High for 3 to 5 minutes until light brown.
Add butter and vanilla to syrup, blending well.
Cook on High 1 to 2 minutes.
Peanuts will be lightly browned and syrup very hot.
Add baking soda and gently stir until light and foamy.
Pour mixture onto lightly greased cookie sheet. Let cool.
Break up.
Store in airtight container.

title: apple walnut cake
directions: Mix apples and sugar; let stand.
Mix flour, nuts, oil, eggs, soda, cinnamon and vanilla.
Add apples; bake 45 minutes to 1 hour at 350°.
Mix butter, powdered sugar, lemon juice and enough water to spread to make icing.
This cake is moist.

title: zabaglione
directions: In top of double boiler over boiling water, put egg yolks, sugar, wine and egg whites.
Beat and add cream, vanilla, confectioners sugar and cinnamon.
Beat until well blended, thick and fluffy.

title: walnut-vegetable medley
directions: In 10-inch skillet over medium heat, add 1/2-inch water. Bring to a boil.
Add carrots and cook 5 minutes until tender-crisp. Drain.
In the same skillet, combine milk and basil until smooth. Add carrots and broccoli.
Heat to boiling. Reduce to low. Cover and simmer 10 minutes
or until veggies are tender, stirring often.
Top with walnuts.
Yields 8 to 10 servings.

title: squash casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Put in greased casserole and bake at 375° for an hour or
until done.

title: crock-pot macaroni pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together and put into greased crock-pot. Cover top with grated cheese.
Cook 3 hours and 15 minutes on low. Great for Sunday dinner; cooks while you're at church.

title: liverwurst log
directions: Mix ingredients.
Form log into about 1 1/2 inches in diameter. Wrap in wax paper; chill for 2 to 3 hours.
Garnish with pimiento and chopped hard-cooked egg yolk.
Serve with snack crackers or party rye bread.

title: mexican wedding cakes
directions: Cream butter.
Add sugar gradually until smooth.
Add flour, salt, vanilla and pecans.
Blend until stiff.
Pinch off small pieces of dough and roll into balls and place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Pat down balls.
Bake at 400° about 12 minutes or until very lightly browned.
Roll cookies in powdered sugar while warm. Yields about 4 dozen.

title: green beans with coconut(same ki bhaji)
directions: Measure half the coconut and water into blender; cover.
Blend on medium speed, scraping sides of container, if necessary, for 3 minutes; reserve.
Repeat procedure with remaining coconut and water.
Saute onion, mustard seed and garlic in oil in Dutch oven over medium heat for 5 minutes.
Mix remaining ingredients and reserved coconut mixture; cover.
Heat to boiling; reduce heat. Simmer, stirring occasionally, 15 minutes.

title: breakfast pizza
directions: Cook sausage; drain.
Separate rolls and place in 12-inch pizza pan with points to center.
Press together to form a crust. Spoon in sausage, hash browns, then cheese.
Beat eggs, milk, 1/2 teaspoon of salt and 1/8 teaspoon of pepper.
Pour over all.
Put the Parmesan cheese on top.
Bake at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: cheese cake
directions: In a 9-inch pie dish, combine crumbs, butter and 1/2 cup sugar.
Press to form crust.
Beat cream cheese, 3/4 cup sugar, vanilla and eggs.
Pour over crust.
Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes or until top cracks open.
Test with toothpick.
Top with thickened strawberry sauce or cherry pie filling.
Chill.

title: heavenly hash
directions: Brown ground beef. Add bacon, onion, celery and cheese. Cover; simmer for 30 minutes. Add macaroni, tomato soup and mushroom soup; mix well. Place in casserole. Bake for 1 hour at 350°. Serves 6 to 8.

title: jewish coffee cake
directions: Mix sugar, nuts and cinnamon.
Pour 1/2 batter in a 9 x 13-inch greased and floured pan.
Sprinkle 1/2 sugar mixture over batter.
Pour rest of batter; top with sugar mixture.
Cut through cake with a spatula to work in sugar mixture.
Bake 40 to 45 minutes at 350°.
Don't over bake.

title: pork chop casserole
directions: Brown pork chops on one side in hot oil.
Place 1/2 potatoes in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Top with cheese slices and then remaining potatoes.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Cook onion in drippings in skillet until tender but do not brown.
Add soup and milk. Heat, then pour over chops.
Cover with foil.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Remove cover and bake 30 minutes more.

title: lemon pie
directions: Cook sugar, cornstarch and hot water until thick and clear; add egg yolks.
Remove from stove and add butter, lemon juice and grated lemon rind.
Pour into prepared crust shell; heap with meringue.

title: creamy spam and broccoli casserole
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Spray 2-quart casserole with vegetable cooking spray.
Cook macaroni, broccoli, Spam and red pepper.
In small saucepan, stir together milk, cornstarch and pepper until cornstarch is dissolved.
Bring to a low boil, stirring constantly, until thickened.
Reduce heat to low.
Add cheese; stir until melted.

title: layered green salad
directions: Layer the ingredients as numbered in a large salad bowl and refrigerate.

title: cornbread salad
directions: Crumple bread and bacon together in large salad bowl.
Chop all vegetables and add to bread and bacon.
Add mayonnaise to bread, bacon and vegetables and mix well.

title: chicken cacciatore
directions: Dredge chicken in flour.
Combine tomatoes, tomato paste, onions, garlic, oregano, thyme, parsley, pepper, wine and water. Stir until well blended.
Add chicken pieces, turning to coat well with sauce.
Cover.
Microwave 35 to 40 minutes on High, or until chicken is fork-tender, stirring after 15 minutes.
Stir in mushroom slices and salt.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Serve over spaghetti.

title: quick caramel rolls
directions: Thaw
bread
about
45	minutes.
Grease Bundt pan with butter.
Sprinkle
nuts on bottom and sides of pan.
Cut bread into 12 equal pieces and put in pan.

title: peanut butter popcorn bars
directions: Place popcorn in a large bowl; set aside in a sauce pan over medium heat, bring sugar and corn syrup to a boil, stirring constantly.
Boil for 1 minute.
Remove from the heat.
Stir in peanut butter and vanilla:
mix well.
Pour over popcorn and mix until well coated.
Press into a buttered 13 x 9 x 2 pan.
Cool slightly before cutting.

title: best chicken marinade
directions: Place boneless, skinless chicken breasts in a shallow container. Pour the marinade over the chicken and refrigerate for 2 to 4 hours. Barbecue the meat over medium heat for 5 to 7 minutes until done.

title: chocolate chip pudding cookies
directions: Mix flour with baking soda.
Combine butter, sugars, pudding mix and vanilla in large bowl.
Beat until smooth and creamy. Beat in eggs.
Gradually add flour mixture, then stir in chips and nuts.
Batter will be stiff.
Drop by rounded measuring teaspoon onto sheets, about 2 inches apart.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Makes about 10 dozen.

title: steamed chicken with yellow rice and black beans
directions: Boil chicken in Dutch oven with celery, onion, salt and pepper over medium heat for 45 minutes to 1 hour.
Chicken should almost fall off bones.

title: classic cole slaw
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients; stir in remaining ingredients. Cover; chill.

title: coconut custard pie
directions: Beat sugar and eggs.
Add slowly milk, butter and flavoring. Add coconut last.
Pour into uncooked pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: lumpia shanghai
directions: Mix thoroughly all ingredients, except lumpia wrappers and oil for wrapping.
Take a heaping teaspoonful and roll in lumpia wrapper.
Make a long roll about 3/4-inch diameter.
Cut to 2-inch pieces, using very sharp knife.
Deep fat fry.
Serve with soy sauce and lemon or sweet and sour sauce.

title: baked chicken breasts
directions: Salt and pepper chicken breasts.
Mix remaining ingredients; place in a 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Bake in a 350° oven for 45 minutes.
Serve over rice or in pastry shells.
Serves 4.
Elegant and easy.

title: iced mint chocolate
directions: Cut chocolate into small pieces and place in blender.
Add sugar and hot water; blend about a minute, or stir over low heat until dissolved.
Add other ingredients.
Place hand on cover of blender and blend another minute.
Serve in tall glasses and garnish with whipped cream or ice cream.
This makes 3 servings.

title: holy smoke
directions: Mix and press into 12 x 15 inch pan.
Bake 20 minutes at 350°.
Let cool.

title: cream puff cake
directions: Bring to a boil 1 cup water and 1 stick margarine.
Gradually stir in 1 cup flour (use whisk to avoid lumps).
Take from stove. Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Pour into a greased 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Bake at 375° for 30 to 35 minutes.
When cool, beat cream cheese until smooth.
Add 2 1/2 cups milk and the pudding; spread on cake.
Top with Cool Whip.

title: stuffed green peppers
directions: Saute onions in oil 2 to 3 minutes.
Add ground beef and cook until brown.
Drain excess fat.
Add tomatoes, water, rice, chili powder, salt, pepper, brown sugar and Worcestershire sauce.
Cover and simmer 30 to 40 minutes until liquid is absorbed.

title: peter paul mounds cake
directions: Bake according to directions on box and cool.
Split layers, making four.

title: lemon sherbet
directions: Mix sugar, lemon juice, Pet milk and half and half.
Pour into freezer.
Finish filling freezer with milk (about 1/2 gallon).

title: pepper steak in oyster sauce
directions: Marinate meat for 15 minutes in mixture of cornstarch, sugar, salt, sherry and soy sauce.
Heat wok or large skillet.
Pour in 1 tablespoon oil and heat.
Stir-fry onion and green pepper until crisp-tender.
Remove to bowl.
Add 2 tablespoons oil to wok and stir-fry beef until done.
Add oyster sauce and vegetables and mix well.
Add tomatoes and heat until warm.
Serve over rice.

title: butterhorn rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in the lukewarm water.
Pour boiling water over shortening, sugar and salt; beat with mixer until soft.
Add 1 cup cold water; mix well.
Add 5 cups flour, dry milk and eggs; mix well.
Add yeast.
Add gradually 5 to 5 1/2 cups flour.
When too stiff for mixer, knead by hand until smooth and elastic.
Grease the top well and cover with waxed paper; place in refrigerator to rise, or on counter.
Make into desired shape rolls anytime in the next 3 to 4 days and let rise until double in size.
Bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: crab imperial
directions: Combine the first 9 ingredients; mound on shells.
Combine bread crumbs and melted butter; sprinkle over crab meat.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes, or until lightly browned.

title: peanut butter bars
directions: Melt oleo in microwave.
Add graham crackers, peanut butter and powdered sugar.
Put mixture in pan.
Melt chocolate for approximately 30 to 40 seconds on 100% power.
Pour over top of mixture.
Cool and slice with plastic spatula.

title: chicken crumble
directions: Cut chicken breasts into bite size pieces.
Melt margarine in skillet and saute chicken until no longer pink on outside.
Scoop out chicken into casserole dish.
Mix chicken with soup and sour cream.
Crumble crackers into margarine remaining in skillet; mix and sprinkle on chicken mixture.
Bake, uncovered, at 375° for 1/2 hour.
Serve over rice or noodles.

title: cream cheese pound cake
directions: Combine margarine, butter, cream cheese and sugar.
Beat well. Add salt and vanilla.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Add flour and mix well.
Pour into greased and floured 10-inch tube pan.
Place pan in cold oven and set at 275°.
Bake 1 1/2 hours or until cake tests done.
Cool in pan.

title: oven barbecued chicken
directions: Place chicken, skin side down in a single layer, in a buttered, shallow baking pan, top with onion slices.
Mix remaining ingredients in a small saucepan.
Heat to boiling and pour over chicken.
Bake in hot oven (400°) 30 minutes.
Turn chicken skin side up, baste with sauce in pan.
Continue baking, baste once or twice, 30 minutes longer or until tender or richly glazed.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Combine all ingredients except cheese and potato chips.
Pack it lightly in baking dish and sprinkle with cheese and potato chips.
Bake at 450° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Don't burn potato chips.
Can be made night before.
Serves 12.

title: roast beef supreme
directions: Sprinkle beef lightly with pepper and flour; spread cooking oil in bottom of roaster.
Place meat in roaster and sprinkle soup mix over roast.
Add water and cover.
Bake at 350° until tender, 25 to 30 minutes per pound.

title: fat-free dressing
directions: Mix together and store in refrigerator.
Makes 1 pint.

title: rice and green chilies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Bake in 12 x 8 x 2-inch casserole. Melt butter in large skillet.
Saute onion, remove from heat and stir in rice, sour cream and Ricotta.
Salt and pepper to taste. Toss lightly.
Drain and halve
chili peppers.
In casserole layer rice mixture, chilies and cheese.
Repeat this to form 2 layers. Bake 25 minutes uncovered, until bubbly.

title: rocky road squares
directions: Mix chocolate morsels, condensed milk and butter.
Put in microwave until melted.
Remove and add marshmallows and peanuts (do not let marshmallows melt).
Fold together and spread out in 9 x 13-inch square, lined with wax paper.
Chill for 2 hours.
Peel off paper.
Cut into squares.

title: macaroni salad carbonara
directions: Bring mushrooms with broth to a boil in a 10-inch skillet. Add peas; cover and cook 3 minutes.
Uncover and add ham.
Heat and stir until broth is absorbed and peas are tender-crisp.
Toss cooked macaroni, green pepper and tomatoes with salad dressing. Stir in mushrooms, ham and pea mixture.
Chill and serve.

title: make-it-easy chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Shake flour in Reynolds oven cooking bag.
Place in 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Add water, basil, thyme and seasoned salt to bag.
Squeeze bag to blend ingredients. Cut onion and potatoes into 8 wedges each.
Slice carrots and cut red pepper into cubes.
Add vegetables to bag.
Turn bag to coat vegetables.
Arrange in an even layer.
Sprinkle chicken with seasonings; place in bag.
Close bag with nylon tie.
Make 6 half-inch slits in top.
Bake 50 to 55 minutes or until tender.

title: beet pickles
directions: Tie spices in a bag and add to beet liquid, vinegar and sugar.

title: punch
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Add ginger ale right before serving. Chill.

title: eggplant casserole
directions: Eggplant can be cooked in chunks or diced. After cooking, drain well to remove excess water. Saut onion, bell pepper and jalapeno pepper in 1 tablespoon oil until tender, not brown. Mix all ingredients together well. Place in casserole and top with 1/2 cup grated cheese and 1 slice of bacon, cut into pieces. Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: 7-up salad
directions: Mix well and refrigerate until firm.

title: easy fruit salad
directions: Drain fruit cocktail.
Mix pudding mix and pineapple.
Add Tang. Stir in other ingredients.
Chill and serve.

title: honey spread
directions: Soften butter to room temperature.
Mix with honey.
Serve or refrigerate for later use.

title: dirt cake
directions: Crush
Oreo
cookies.
Mix
pudding according to directions. Mix
pudding
with	next
4 ingredients, starting with crushed cookies. Alternate with pudding mix in a large bowl or clear flowerpot.	Top with crushed cookies.
Place artificial flowers in cake to resemble a potted plant.

title: jeannette's crab dip
directions: Mix all ingredients. Pour in dish. Put cocktail sauce over or sprinkle with dill weed.

title: pound cake
directions: Cream the cheese and butter together.
Add sugar and mix.
Add 1 egg at a time, beating well after each.
Add cake flour, mixing well.
Add vanilla and lemon flavoring.
Pour into greased and floured tube pan.
Bake at 300° for 1 1/2 hours.
Start in cold oven.

title: chunky brownie cookies
directions: Heat oven to 350 degrees.
Line cookie pan with parchment paper.
Mix ingredients in order listed above.
Roll into balls or drop by table spoon onto parchment paper lined cookie sheet.
Bake 8-10 minutes.
Don't let them burn!

title: simple stew
directions: Mix together pepper, salt, celery salt, Accent, garlic salt, sugar and tapioca.
Place meat in greased casserole.
Sprinkle with mixed seasonings.
Add rest of ingredients.
Cover with tight fitting cover and bake at 250° for 4 hours.

title: taffy apple salad
directions: Drain pineapple.
Mix with marshmallows.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Mix together juice, sugar, flour, egg and vinegar.
Heat until it boils.
Cool until thickened.
Store in refrigerator overnight.

title: kolache
directions: Dice squash into 1/2-inch pieces.
Melt butter and olive oil and saute squash in it until partly browned.
Remove squash (and juice if too much) from pan.
Add onion and green peppers.
Saute until limp.
Add tomatoes.
Season well with salt, pepper and cayenne.
Add corn.
Cook, uncovered, for 30 minutes.
Return squash to pan.
Serves 8.

title: easy jello salad
directions: In medium-size mixing bowl, empty cottage cheese.
Add dry jello; mix until absorbed into cottage cheese.
Mix in crushed pineapple that has been drained.
Chill and serve!

title: beets in orange sauce
directions: Melt butter.
Mix sugar and cornstarch.
Blend into butter. Stir in juice and cook until thickened.
Add salt, pepper and beets.
Sprinkle with orange rind.
This is an excellent dish for your Thanksgiving meal.

title: coconut oatmeal cookies
directions: Cream first 5 ingredients.
Add dry ingredients, then oatmeal and coconut.
Roll into balls and press flat on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° about 10 minutes.

title: shaped sugar cookies
directions: Mix dry ingredients and generously sprinkle on countertop. Roll cookie dough in flour and sugar until flat.
Sprinkle extra flour and sugar on top of cookie dough and smooth out.
Cut with cookie cutters. Bake at 350° for 8 minutes.
May decorate with frosting and sprinkles.

title: baked corn
directions: Mix all together.
Bake for 1 hour in 350° oven.
This may be made and refrigerated until ready to bake.

title: m&m cookies
directions: Cream the shortening, sugar, vanilla and eggs.
Add remaining ingredients (except M&M's) and mix well.
Stir in M&M's.
Drop by rounded teaspoonful onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: puppy chow
directions: Melt chips, peanut butter and butter in microwave.
Pour over Rice Chex and mix thoroughly.
Pour mixture in brown paper bag (grocery bag).
Dump into powdered sugar and shake until coated.

title: corned beef brisket steamed
directions: To braise brisket, line a pan with a rack, with foil.
Pour ginger ale in bottom of pan.

Place brisket on rack and cover tightly with foil.	Place in 300° oven for approximately 5 hours. Remove foil cover and generously coat brisket with orange marmalade.	Increase oven temperature to 375° and bake for about 45 minutes until carmalized.
Slice thin and serve.

title: walnut pie
directions: Melt butter and blend in brown sugar.
Beat in eggs, one at a time.
Add syrup, vanilla and walnuts.
Pour into pie crust.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes.

title: chocolate oatmeal cookies
directions: Boil sugar, milk, cocoa and butter for 3 minutes or until hard ball forms in cold water.
Remove from heat.
Add peanut butter, oats and vanilla.
Drop teaspoon of cookie onto wax paper.

title: tex-mex dip
directions: Layer ingredients.
First layer:
refried beans and taco mix. Second layer:
avocados, lemon juice, chili powder, salt and 1/4 cup mayonnaise.
Third layer:
sour cream and 1/4 cup mayonnaise. Layer remaining ingredients and serve with tortilla chips.

title: chicken delight
directions: Combine vegetables, including liquid, chicken, soup, cheese and celery seed.
Place in a baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Remove from oven and top with biscuits.
Return to oven and bake at 400° for 10 to 15 minutes or until biscuits are lightly browned.

title: banana split cake
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients and pat into pie plate.
Bake 15 minutes at 400°.
When cool, crumble into 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: corn casserole
directions: Combine ingredients. Fold in egg whites last. Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: fruit cobbler
directions: Cook fruit of your choice, sugared to taste, until done.
Melt butter in baking dish.
Mix flour, sugar, baking powder and milk together.
Pour over melted butter in pan and blend.
Pour hot fruit over batter.
Bake at 375° for 40 minutes.

title: polish potatoes
directions: Cook potatoes and mash.
Add 1 can of drained sauerkraut. Meanwhile, cook cut up bacon and chopped onion together until almost well cooked.
Drain, yet keep small amount of liquid.
To this, add 1 pint of King Sour.
Simmer and stir until blended. Add to potatoes and sauerkraut.
It is ready to serve.

title: diabetic date nut cake
directions: Cream butter.
Add egg, sweetener and vanilla.
Sift dry ingredients and add to other mixture.
Beat until well blended. Turn into buttered loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: carrot cake
directions: Cream sugar and oil.
Add eggs.
Cream until soft.
Sift flour and measure and sift dry ingredients.
Add to other ingredients and mix well.
Fold in grated carrots and nuts.
Cook 35 minutes at 275° in 3 round pans.

title: breakfast pizza
directions: Mix together the first 5 ingredients.
Spray a 13 x 9-inch pan with Pam.
Press crescent rolls into pan.
Top crescent rolls with sausage, hash browns, cheese and eggs (in that order). Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: graham cracker crusts
directions: Melt margarine or butter.
Stir in sugar.
Add crushed graham crackers.
Toss to mix well.
Spread mixture evenly into a 9-inch pie plate.
Press onto bottom and sides to form a firm, even crust.
Chill about 1 hour or till firm.
(Or bake in a 375° oven for 4 to 5 min. or until edge is lightly browned.
Cool on a wire rack before filling.)

title: jam cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake at 250° to 275° for 45 minutes.
(Line pan with wax paper for easy removal.)

title: plantation pound cake
directions: Sift flour; measure and sift again.
Cream butter until light and fluffy.
Gradually add sugar, stirring all the while until fluffy and well blended.
Add one egg at a time, beating well after each addition.
After adding the last egg, beat about 5 minutes longer.
Add flour gradually; mix well to blend.
Add desired flavoring.
Pour into a well-greased 10-inch tube pan. Bake in a 300° oven for 1 1/4 hours, or until done.
Let cool slightly in pan.
Invert on a cake cooler.

title: scalloped corn
directions: Mix all ingredients together and place in a casserole dish. Bake at 375° for approximately 1 1/2 hours.

title: marinated carrot salad
directions: Cook carrots in a small amount of salted water until barely tender.
Drain.
Add onion and pepper strips to carrots.
Mix together remaining ingredients and pour over carrots.
Cover and marinate in refrigerator several hours or overnight.
This salad will keep for several days.
Makes 5 cups.

title: best ever seafoam
directions: Boil sugar, syrup and water to soft-ball stage.
Then pour slowly over the egg whites, which have been beaten with the salt until stiff, stirring all the time.
Beat well.
Add nuts, if wanted.
Beat until nearly cold.
Work fast and drop from spoon on waxed paper.

title: chocolate pound cake
directions: Cream real well the margarine, shortening and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Measure, then sift flour, salt, baking powder and cocoa.
Sift all 2 times, then add milk, vanilla and nuts.
Bake in tube pan at 325° for 90 minutes.

title: chocolate creams
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Sift together flour, baking soda and salt.
Heat brown sugar, butter and 2 tablespoons water to melt butter.
Add the chocolate morsels; stir to melt.
Beat in eggs. Stir in flour mixture.
Drop by heaping teaspoons into greased cookie sheet or line with greased foil.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Yields 8 dozen.
Sandwich together in pairs with 1 teaspoon of cream filling.

title: chocolate zucchini cake
directions: Cream the margarine, oil and sugar.
Add the eggs, vanilla and sour milk.
Beat well with mixer.
Mix together all the dry ingredients and add to the creamed mixture.
Stir in zucchini. Pour batter into 2 greased and floured loaf pans.
Top with chocolate chips and nuts.
Bake for 45 minutes at 325° (until toothpick comes out clean).

title: cincinnati chili
directions: Crumble raw, do not brown, ground beef into water.
Add rest of ingredients.
Bring to a boil, then simmer for 3 hours.
Remove garlic clove and bay leaves.
Add whole red peppers, if desired, for spicier taste.
Serve over rice or may be served in bowl with chips, or grated Cheddar cheese and chopped onions.

title: carne con chile
directions: Brown meat; add tomato, onion and jalapenos.
Cook 20 minutes, adding garlic, comino and salt.
Add 1/2 tablespoon flour and brown; add 1/2 cup water or more to thicken forming a gravy. Simmer for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: tomato bacon cups
directions: You also need 30 mini-muffin cups.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Mix until creamed together.
Serve with fresh vegetables.

title: three layer salad
directions: Chill and pour in 7 x 11-inch buttered pan.

title: barbecued shrimp
directions: Mix all ingredients, except shrimp. Add shrimp in their shells to the mixture. Marinate the shrimp overnight, turning occasionally.

title: western chili casserole
directions: Brown hamburger, 3/4 onion and celery; cook until tender. Drain fat.
Add chili and pepper and heat through.
Place layer of crushed chips in ungreased 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Alternate layers of chips, chili and cheese.
Reserve 1/2 cup chips, 1/4 cup onion and 1/4 cup cheese to garnish top.
Cover and bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: bob andy pie
directions: Mix all the ingredients together real good.
This makes a good 8 or 9-inch pie.
Bake until firm, around 1 hour, in a 350° oven.

title: country grits and sausage casserole
directions: Brown sausage in a large skillet, stirring until it crumbles. Drain well and set aside.
Bring water to a boil in a large saucepan; stir in grits.
Return to a boil; cover, reduce heat and simmer 5 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Remove from heat; add cheese and next 3 ingredients, stirring until cheese melts.
Stir in sausage and eggs.
Spoon mixture into a lightly greased 13 x 9-inch baking dish and sprinkle with paprika.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until golden brown and thoroughly heated.
Let stand for 5 minutes before serving.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: mississippi mud
directions: Crust:
Mix flour, oleo and chopped nuts. Spread in a 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake for 20 minutes at 350°.
Cool.

title: bean and roasted red pepper dip(low-fat)
directions: Heat oil in a medium nonstick skillet over medium heat.
Add onion; saute 4 minutes or until tender.
Add basil and beans; cook over low heat 5 minutes, stirring frequently.
Partially mash beans.
Stir in bell pepper.
Serve with pita chips.
Yield:
2 1/2 cups (serving size 1/4 cup).
Cal:

title: easy noodle 'n dogs dinner
directions: In medium skillet, bring water to boiling; stir in remaining ingredients.
Continue boiling over medium heat, stirring occasionally, 7 minutes or until noodles are tender.
Makes about 4 servings.

title: sinful potatoes
directions: Mix in mixing bowl.
Spread in a baking or serving dish (or use a glass 8 x 12 dish) cornflakes (or use the small box).
Crush with a rolling pin before opening the package or use a Ziploc bag, 3/4 cup melted butter.
Mix butter and corn flakes and spread on mixture.
Bake in 350° oven for 90 minutes.

title: mexican wedding cakes
directions: Mix thoroughly the butter, sugar and vanilla.
Work in nuts and flour.
Shape dough into 1-inch balls.
Bake at 300° for 25 minutes or until hard but not brown.
Remove from sheet and roll in powdered sugar.
Makes 2 dozen cookies.

title: green rice casserole
directions: Put broccoli in bowl, pour boiling water to cover and thaw. Cook rice, saute onion and celery in margarine until soft.
Mix rice, soup, cheese, celery and onion.
Drain water from broccoli and blend with mixture.
Pour into greased casserole and bake 35 minutes at 350°.

title: hash brown quiche
directions: Press hash browns between paper towels to remove excess moisture.
Press into bottom and up the sides of 9-inch pie plate. Drizzle with butter.
Bake 450° for 25 minutes.

title: christmas punch
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Add sugar and juices.
Add enough water to make a gallon.
Slice an orange into thin pieces. Add to punch.
Peel off rind from slices and drop into punch bowl.

title: all in one skillet dinner
directions: Brown ground beef and onion about 10 minutes.
Add noodles, water, carrots, Worcestershire sauce, salt and pepper.
Simmer 30 minutes or until carrots are tender.

title: homemade ice cream
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients well, then add cream.
Pour into ice cream freezer and add milk to fill line.
Use plenty of rock salt in the freezer.

title: chicken loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients and put in 9 X 13 inch pan. Bake at 350° about 1 to 1 1/2 hours until set. Cut in squares and serve with mushroom sauce.

title: pecan pie squares
directions: Mix flour, 1/4 cup plus 2 tablespoons sugar, margarine and salt together.
Press firmly into a greased 10 x 5-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until light golden brown.
Set aside to cool.

title: date and nut cake
directions: Mix dates, baking soda and boiling water together; let cool. Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and line a loaf pan.
Combine the eggs, butter, sugar, salt, nuts, raisins and vanilla.
Add date mixture.
Add flour and mix well.
Turn into pan and bake for about 1 hour or until golden brown and firm to touch.
Turn out and allow to cool before storing.

title: prize winning apple coffee cake
directions: Blend cake mix, pudding mix, oil eggs and sour cream.
Beat at highest speed for 10 minutes.
Grease and flour an angel food pan or bundt pan.
Pour 1/2 of batter in pan.
Combine sugar, cinnamon, apples, and nuts.
Pour 1/2 of above mixture on top of batter.
Swirl it in.
Then add remaining batter.
Top with rest of apple mixture.
Swirl through batter again.
Bake at 350 degrees for 1 hour.
Remove from pan.
Drizzle frosting on.

title: pecan pie
directions: Bake at 375° for 20 minutes; then bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: quick tea doughnuts
directions: Beat eggs.
Add sugar and milk.
Mix dry ingredients together and add to liquid.
Beat thoroughly and add melted fat.
Add more flour to make a batter stiff enough to hold a spoon in at standing position.
Drop by spoonfuls into deep fat at 375°.
Remove when brown and roll in sugar.

title: french oven stew
directions: Combine all ingredients, except potatoes, in 2 1/2-quart casserole.
Cover and cook at 325° for 2 1/2 hours.
Stir occasionally.
Add potatoes and cook 1 more hour.
Serve with French bread.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mix and pour into baking dish.
Bake 15 minutes at 450°.

title: blueberry delite
directions: Mix flour, margarine and nuts and press to bottom of 9-inch pie pan or oblong pan.
Bake 20 minutes at 350°.
Cool completely.
Mix remaining ingredients and spread over pastry layer.
Spread 1 can blueberry pie filling over cream cheese layer.
Top with remaining Cool Whip.
Sprinkle with 1/2 cup or more as desired of pecans, toasted (optional).
Chill for at least 2 hours.
Serves 6.

title: green pepper steak
directions: Sprinkle garlic powder, onion powder and tenderizer on meat. Melt butter in skillet. Saute onions and peppers for 2 minutes. Set aside. Leave butter in pan. Add beef and saute until lightly brown.
Put in slow cooker.
Add tomatoes and bouillon cube. Blend together the cornstarch, water, soy sauce, sugar and salt. Stir into meat mixture.
Add water chestnuts and celery.
Cook in slow cooker 3 hours.
Add onion and pepper.
Heat 1 hour. Serve over rice.

title: corn souffle
directions: Mix all ingredients, except Swiss cheese, and pour into a 9 x 13-inch casserole dish.
Bake for 35 minutes in a 350° oven. Remove from oven and add shredded Swiss cheese, then return to oven for 10 minutes.

title: chicken and noodles
directions: Buy it, and cook it.
It takes 17 minutes.
After 17 minutes you take them out and eat them.
You could eat them with ketchup, if you want.

title: parmesan fillets
directions: Preheat broiler.
In cup, combine oil and lemon juice.
On nonstick baking sheet, arrange fillets in a single layer and, using a pastry brush, brush both sides of each fillet with 1/4 of oil mixture.
Sprinkle half of the cheese on each fillet.
Broil until golden brown and fish flakes easily with fork, approximately 3 to 4 minutes.
Serves 2.
The scrod contains 162 calories, 7 gm fat and 175 mg sodium.
The flounder contains 172 calories, 8 gm fat and 206 mg sodium.

title: oyster crackers
directions: Dump all ingredients in brown paper bag and shake well. Spread out on another paper bag to dry.

title: paige's sour cream biscuits
directions: Cut in butter and flour.
Add sour cream.
Drop in greased muffin tins and bake 10 to 12 minutes at 400°.
Makes 12.

title: golden salad
directions: Dissolve lemon gelatin in boiling water.
In another bowl, mix cream cheese and dry whipped topping mix.
Mix in crushed pineapple.
Slowly mix in gelatin mixture.
Slowly add 7-Up.
Pour in serving dish.
Cover top with pecans.
Refrigerate until set.

title: chicken marengo
directions: Place all ingredients in microwave-proof casserole.
Cook on High for 25 to 30 minutes.
Serve over wild rice.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Optional:
Add raisins, nuts, chocolate chips, peanut butter.

title: garden pizza
directions: Press rolls in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 375° for 8 minutes. Cool crust.

title: ruth's strawberry dessert
directions: Put together thawed strawberries, lemon juice, sugar and egg whites in mixing bowl and beat with electric mixer for 20 minutes, no longer than that.
While this is being done, crush one package of Keebler sandy pecan cookies.
Reserve some to sprinkle on top of dessert.
Put remaining in 9 x 13-inch pan. When mixture has been mixed for 20 minutes, fold in thoroughly one large container of Cool Whip.
Spread over crushed cookies in pan and sprinkle reserved crushed cookies on top.
Place in freezer.
This can be made a week ahead and is just fine.

title: dad's cobb salad
directions: Arrange lettuce on plate, then place all ingredients in sections on the bed of lettuce.
Top with dressing and Italian bread to dip.

title: ham and broccoli chowder
directions: Mix flour and milk in cooker.
Add other ingredients, except cream.
Cook on low for 7 hours or automatic 4 hours.
Before serving, stir in cream and heat through.
Makes 6 servings.

title: candied jalapenos
directions: Drain jar of jalapenos completely. Lightly pat dry with paper towel. Put jalapenos back in jar and add cracked pepper. Pack as much sugar as possible into jar. Turn upside down and refrigerate overnight. Pack more sugar; shake and put back in fridge.

title: seafood quiche
directions: Separate triangles of rolls and place 5 in a 9 inch pie pan pressing seams together to form a crust.
Combine remaining ingredients and pour
into crust.
Roll out remaining triangles. Cut in 1/2 inch strips and make lattice effect on top of quiche. Bake at 325 degrees 50-60 minutes.

title: stromboli
directions: Use pizza dough or unthaw one loaf of frozen bread dough. Grease cookie sheet and spread dough to cover sheet.
Layer ingredients listed along one side of pan.
Spread a small amount of sauce on top.
Fold empty dough over layered dough.
Brush top with oil, pinch edge and bake at 425° for 30 minutes.
Cut into 6 pieces and eat.

title: swedish apple cake
directions: Place the bread crumbs in a frying pan with butter and brown on moderate heat until the bread crumbs are crisp.
Peel and core the apples; cut them into wedges.
Butter an ovenproof dish.
Put in alternate layers of bread crumbs, apples or puree and sugar; the top layer should be bread crumbs.
Bake in a 400° F or 200° C oven for approximately 20 minutes.
Serve directly from the dish with whipping cream.

title: night before casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients together, and pour into a greased 9 x 13 x 2-inch baking dish.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: In a Corning casserole dish, dilute soup with water and mix. Blend in onion, celery, lima beans and juice, carrots, peas and juice, raisins, parsley, orange rind, paprika, garlic salt and oil.
Cover and simmer on stove top (large burner) for about 15 minutes or until all veggies are cooked.
This recipe serves 4.

title: spaghetti with ricotta
directions: Cook spaghetti as directed on package.
Drain; turn into warm serving dish or bowl.
Stir in melted butter, then add Ricotta and toss gently to blend.
Sprinkle with grated cheese, salt and pepper.
Garnish with a little chopped parsley.
Serves 6.

title: sweet-sour zucchini salad
directions: Cook bacon until crisp; remove from fat.
In a saucepan, combine 1 tablespoon bacon fat with flour.
Cook slightly.
Add vinegar, water and seasonings.
Cook and stir until thickened. Add cooked bacon pieces.
Cool.
Just before serving, toss dressing with shredded zucchini.
Arrange tomato and mushroom slices on salad greens.
Top with a mound of zucchini mixture.

title: speedy scalloped corn
directions: Mix corn, green pepper, onion, milk, salt, pepper and half of cracker crumbs in a buttered 1-quart casserole.
Dot with oleo. Top with rest of crumbs.
Bake at 350°.

title: caramel corn
directions: Put brown sugar in heavy saucepan and just enough water to dissolve.
Stir and cook over medium heat until it forms soft ball in cold water.
(Don't stir much.)
Remove from heat and add evaporated milk and margarine.
Put back on heat and cook to soft ball stage again.
Remove from heat and pour over a large bowl of popped corn mixed with peanuts, if desired.

title: crab swiss bites
directions: Combine all ingredients; place rolls flat on jelly roll pan (ungreased).
Spoon the mixture over rolls and bake 10 to 12 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: phoebe's cake
directions: Bake cake in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cool.
Soften cream cheese in 1/2 cup milk.
Blend well.
Add rest of milk alternately with pudding in cheese mixture.
Beat 5 minutes at high speed.
Pour over cool cake.
Sprinkle pineapple over pudding.
Frost with Cool Whip.
Sprinkle with nuts or coconut.

title: hot dog sauce
directions: Brown ground beef, add onion, brown sugar, mustard, vinegar, salt and tomato sauce.
Cook.

title: almond tea
directions: Steep 4 tea bags.
Add water to make 4 cups tea.
Add other ingredients and stir.
Pour over ice.

title: boy's skillet macaroni and beef
directions: Cook the ground beef, onion, bell pepper, salt, tomato sauce, water and Worcestershire sauce.
Add elbow macaroni and simmer until macaroni is tender.
Serves 6.

title: broccoli bread
directions: Mix together, adding corn meal last. Grease 9 x 13 pan. Bake at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes to light golden brown. This is very tender and does not rise and get crisp like regular cornbread. Cut and serve.

title: banana drop cookies
directions: Sift together flour, sugar, baking powder, soda and salt.
Cut in shortening; add eggs, bananas and vanilla.
Beat thoroughly. Drop spoonfuls on cookie sheet.
Sprinkle with sugar and cinnamon. Bake 12 minutes in a 375° oven.

title: sour cream coffee cake
directions: Cream butter and 2 cups sugar until fluffy.
Beat in eggs. Fold in sour cream and vanilla.

title: beef enchiladas
directions: Brown ground beef in skillet.
When nearly browned, drain and add drained green chilies, garlic, onion hot pepper and fresh green pepper.
Finish browning and drain well.

title: sour cream pound cake(winning recipe from southern living)
directions: Beat butter at medium speed for 2 minutes or until soft and creamy.
Gradually add sugar, beating at medium speed 5 to 7 minutes.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating just until yellow disappears.
Combine flour and baking soda; add to creamed mixture alternately with sour cream, beginning and ending with flour mixture.
Mix at lowest speed, just until blended after each addition.
Pour into greased and floured 10-inch tube pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 20 minutes or until wooden pick comes out clean when inserted in center.
Cool in pan 10 to 15 minutes.

title: stacy's taco dip
directions: In a small bowl, mix cream cheese and sour cream until well blended.
Spread mixture evenly onto two platters.
Pour picante sauce over each platter.
Spread evenly.
Scatter tomato, olives and lettuce evenly over mixture.
Top with shredded Cheddar and serve with tortilla chips.

title: pound cake
directions: Mix well.
Pour in tube pan and bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli until tender, about 10 minutes.
Salt to taste; drain and chop.
Add other ingredients except crackers.
Mix. Place in baking dish.
Put cracker crumbs on top and dot with butter. Bake on 350° for about 35 minutes.

title: beth's molasses cookies
directions: Cream butter or margarine, brown sugar, egg and molasses until light.
Add dry ingredients and mix well; chill 1 hour.
Roll into balls and dip into sugar.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet for 8 to 10 minutes at 350°.

title: charlie chaplin - rocky road
directions: Mix the chocolate, walnuts, coconut and marshmallows together. Mix well.
Spoon mixture onto cookie sheet lined with wax paper. Refrigerate approximately 10 minutes.
(Makes about 2 pounds.)

title: liver pate
directions: Saute chicken livers and onions in margarine; cool.
Place in blender small amount at a time with hard-boiled eggs.
Add mayonnaise if too thick.
Serve with crackers.

title: chicken a la fonda
directions: Butter 2-quart baking dish.
Boil chicken and remove from bone.
Mix soup and sour cream and pour over chicken in baking dish.
Crumble Ritz crackers on top.
Melt butter and drizzle over crackers.
Sprinkle with poppy seed if desired.
You may also put grated cheese on before crackers if desired.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until bubbly.

title: tutti-frutti jam
directions: Put all into a pan and slow boil until it thickens like honey. Makes about two 1 pound jars.
Keep refrigerated.

title: 3 layer brownies
directions: Mix and bake in greased 9 x 13-inch pan at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: sweet and sour pork chops
directions: Add water to pineapple syrup to make 1 cup.
Mix in saucepan with cornstarch, vinegar, brown sugar and soy sauce.
Heat until thickened and clear.
Add green pepper and pineapple.
Pour over browned pork chops and simmer until done.

title: brownies
directions: Sift dry ingredients together.
Add melted butter and cocoa. Blend with dry ingredients.
Bake 25 minutes at 350° in 9 x 13-inch greased pan.

title: barbecue beans
directions: Brown hamburger, onion and pepper.
Mix with remaining ingredients and simmer for at least 30 minutes.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into lightly greased casserole dish.
Bake at 375° for 30 to 40 minutes or until brown and set.

title: toad in a hole
directions: Melt margarine in frying pan.
Cut about a 3-inch round hole in center of bread.
Place bread in pan, break egg into hole and fry on both sides.

title: swedish pickled shrimp
directions: Layer shrimp and onion slices in a glass bowl.
Combine remaining ingredients and pour over shrimp.
Chill, covered, at least 24 hours.
Drain shrimp and arrange shrimp, onion, capers and lemon slices on lettuce leaves to serve as a first course or with picks as a party platter.

title: italiano down under meat pie
directions: In saucepan, add ground beef, onion, salt, pepper, flour, stock and tomato sauce.
Stir over fire until it comes to a boil, then simmer for 15 minutes.
Allow to cool.

title: blueberry cream pies(makes 2 pies.)
directions: Whip the Dream Whip according to package directions. Cream sugar and cream cheese until smooth. Add to Dream Whip.
Using 2 cooked pie shells, slice 6 bananas over the bottom, then fill with mixture. Spoon 1 can blueberry pie filling over the 2 pies. Keep refrigerated.

title: pecan pie
directions: Beat eggs slightly.
Mix in syrup, sugar, margarine, vanilla, salt then nuts.
Pour into unbaked shell.
Bake at 400 degrees for 15 minutes. Set oven temp back to 350 and continue to bake 30 to 35 minutes.
Remove from oven and place on cooling rack.

title: red chicken stew
directions: Place cut up fryer in a large pot and cover with water and salt.
Bring to a boil until tender.
Peel and dice potatoes.
Put into a separate saucepan and boil until done.
While the chicken and potatoes cook, cut up bacon and fry until crisp.
Remove bacon from pan and saute diced onions in the bacon drippings.
Add catsup, hot sauce, Worcestershire sauce, boiled potatoes and liquids in which they are cooked into the saucepan containing the chicken.
Let this simmer about 30 minutes, adding seasoning as desired.
Serve over rice.
Serves 6.

title: mary's special
directions: Crush wafers with rolling pin or blender.
Butter casserole dish or baking pan.
Line dish with 1/2 of the wafer crumbs.
Beat margarine and sugar until fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time. Beat each egg 3 minutes as you add them.
Spread the mixture on crumbs. Top with well drained pineapple.
Put sliced bananas over this. Spread Cool Whip on top.
Spread remainder of the wafer crumbs over this.
Cover with Saran Wrap and chill at least 4 hours.

title: beef burgundy
directions: Cut steak in small pieces.
Shake with flour (use all).
Melt butter and brown steak.
Remove and add onions, parsley, garlic, salt and pepper.
Stir in mushrooms, tomato sauce, Burgundy and water.
Heat to boiling.
Reduce heat and simmer, covered, 1 hour or until tender.
Serve over rice or noodles.
Serves 4.

title: coconut orange balls
directions: Crust vanilla wafers.
In large mixing bowl, cream sugar, orange juice concentrate and margarine.
Mix in cookie crumbs. Shape into balls.
Roll in coconut.

title: potato cakes
directions: In small mixing bowl, combine dry ingredients.
Stir in water and onion.
Spoon into a hot, oiled pan.
Fry over medium heat until golden brown on both sides.

title: borscht(cabbage and red beet soup)
directions: Saute medium onion (chopped) and garlic (minced) in oil until soft.
Add tomatoes (chopped), salt, pepper, vinegar, beef bouillon and water.
Heat to boiling; reduce and simmer 30 minutes.
Add cabbage (shredded) and sausage (sliced).
Simmer 15 minutes, then add beets.
Serve with tablespoon sour cream.

title: creamy veal
directions: Heat heavy skillet.
When very hot, add 2 tablespoons butter. When it smokes, add cutlets and brown thoroughly on both sides. Remove from fire, trim off all gristle and fat, cut into 1/2-inch cubes.
Add remaining to pan and when hot, add cubed veal.
Again, brown on all sides.
When meat is browned, add cream and salt. Lower heat and simmer 30 to 40 minutes until thickened.
Do not boil.
Serve over toast, toasted on one side only, toasted side down.
Serves 2.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Cream together margarine, peanut butter and sugar replacement.
Add egg, water and vanilla, beating until fluffy. Combine flour, baking soda and baking powder in sifter and sift dry ingredients into creamed mixture.
Stir to blend completely. Chill thoroughly, at least 2 hours or overnight.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto lightly greased cookie sheets, 2 to 3-inches (5 to 7 cm) apart.
Press flat with a floured bottom of a small glass.
Bake at 375°F (190°C) for 12 to 15 minutes.
Yield: 42 cookies.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Cover and bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: homemade picante
directions: For HOT sauce leave seeds in the jalapenos.
For milder sauce, remove the seeds before beginning the recipe.

title: apple torte
directions: Cream sugar and butter.
Add egg; beat well.
Add flour, soda, nuts, apples, extract and spices.
Put in well greased pie plate. Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: mexican wedding cake
directions: Mix all ingredients well.

title: breakfast tarts
directions: Pull biscuits in half; put in greased muffin tin.
Combine remaining ingredients and spoon into tins.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.
If frozen, freeze and pull from freezer.
Microwave on High one minute in paper towel.

title: mock enchiladas
directions: Brown hamburger and onion.
Drain.
Add chili beans with drained hamburger and onion.
In flat baking dish alternate layers of hamburger-bean mixture, Cheddar cheese and Fritos.
Bake 15 minutes in 350° oven or until cheese is melted.

title: never fail pie crust
directions: Blend shortening and water until shortening dissolves.
Mix together salt and flour, then blend with water and shortening mixture.
Roll onto floured surface.
Makes approximately 6 crusts or 3 doubles.

title: marble cake
directions: Flour and grease a 9-inch tube pan.
In bowl, mix sugar, butter and eggs until fluffy.
Add flour, milk, baking powder, vanilla and salt.
Measure cocoa in bowl.
Add 1 cup of the batter and 1 tablespoon water.
Mix until smooth.
Pour half of cake batter in tube pan.
Add chocolate mixture, then top with rest of cake batter.
With knife, swirl into mix to marbelize the cake.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 55 minutes.
Cool.
Sprinkle top with confectioners sugar.

title: slow-cooked baked potatoes
directions: Prick potatoes with fork and wrap in foil. Place potatoes in crockpot, do not add water. Cover and cook 8-10 hours. Stays hot until you need them.

title: guilt free alfredo sauce
directions: Combine all ingredients in container of an electric blender; process until smooth, stopping once to scrape sides.
Pour into small saucepan.
Cook sauce over low heat, stirring constantly, until thoroughly heated.
Yields 2 3/4 cups (for one 12 ounce package fettuccine).
One serving (3 1/2 ounces) contains 86 calories and .8 grams fat.

title: heavenly rice casserole
directions: Mix together and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Combine cornmeal, flour, dry milk, sugar, baking powder and salt in medium bowl. Stir in cheese and chiles. Beat water, oil and eggs together.
Stir into dry ingredients just until blended. Pour into buttered 8-inch square baking pan.
Bake in a 375° oven for 30 to 35 minutes or until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.

title: ice cream delight
directions: Combine cracker crumbs and melted butter, stirring well; press into a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 5 to 8 minutes.
Allow to cool.
Combine ice cream, pudding mix and milk; beat at low speed of electric mixer 2 minutes.
Pour ice cream mixture over crust and chill until set.
(Cover with Saran Wrap.) Spread whipped topping over ice cream and sprinkle with crushed candy.
(I freeze the Heath bars before trying to crush them. Crush in Ziploc bag.
Sometimes Heath bits are available in bags and can be used.)
Keep covered in refrigerator.

title: chicken thighs provencale
directions: Brown chicken in oil; remove.
Add onion, mushrooms, garlic, tomato paste and herbs; cook 1 minute.
Return chicken and add wine and broth.
Bring to a boil.
Braise, covered, in a 400° oven for 20 minutes, or until tender.
Salt and pepper.
Sprinkle with parsley.
Serve with noodles or rice.
Serves 2.

title: chocolate cookie cheesecake or teen-agers dream cake
directions: In food processor, whirl 1/2 package of cookies until they form fine crumbs or crush in plastic bag with rolling pin.
Mix in butter.
Press crumbs evenly in a 9-inch pie pan; bottom and sides.
Chill until firm.

title: mud cake(from dorothy rostosky, haverhill, ma)
directions: Bake 1 chocolate cake.
Break up half of cake in bowl.
Pour 1 ounce of Kahlua over cake.
Make the chocolate pudding.
Beat 5 minutes and pour 1/2 of pudding over cake.
Put half of Cool Whip on top of this, then half of Skor bars or Bits O' Brittle.
Repeat for second layer.
Refrigerate.

title: cheese bits
directions: Soften margarine and add grated cheese.
Blend flour, salt and pepper; add to cheese mixture.
Fold in Rice Krispies.
Roll into balls.
Bake 15 to 17 minutes at 350°.

title: robert redford cake
directions: Bake German chocolate cake according to package directions in a 9 x 13-inch (floured and greased) pan.
Leave in pan.
When cool, poke holes in top of cake with end of wooden spoon.
In bowl, mix caramel topping and Eagle Brand milk; pour over cake. Frost cake with Cool Whip.
Crush candy bars; sprinkle on top. Refrigerate until time to enjoy!

title: chunky potato salad
directions: Cook potatoes in a small amount of water. Do not overcook potatoes. They should be done, but not too soft. Let cool. Add onion, eggs, relish, salt, and pepper. Mix salad dressing and pickle juice together for a creamy mixture. Combine with potatoes. Refrigerate.

title: chocolate dip(for coating candies)
directions: Melt
paraffin
in
double
boiler;
add
chips.
When thoroughly melted and blended, put toothpick in piece of candy and dip into hot chocolate until coated.
Place on waxed paper to cool.

title: marinated grilled chicken
directions: Place chicken in a large, shallow dish.
Combine soy sauce and all other ingredients, mixing well.
Pour over chicken; let it marinate for 30 minutes.
Remove and place on a hot grill for 25 minutes, or until done, turning and basting with marinade about every 5 minutes.

title: quick mix cake
directions: Grease 7 x 14-inch baking pan and empty can of pineapple, including juice, into it.
Open cake mix and pour over pineapple in pan.
Drizzle melted butter over all, then add nuts.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Serve hot or cold with whipped cream.

title: spinach salad
directions: Grease 13 x 9-inch pan with a layer of mayonnaise (all sides). Layer spinach, lettuce, bacon, scallions and eggs in exact order. Top with frozen peas.

title: lemon bread
directions: Cream margarine and sugar; add eggs and beat well.
Blend in lemon rind.
Mix dry ingredients; add slowly to creamed mixture. Alternate with milk.
Blend until smooth.
Pour into greased loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 55 minutes.
Mix lemon juice and sugar. Pour over bread as soon as it is out of oven.
Use a knife to loosen sides of bread from pan first.
Leave in pan for 15 minutes.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Slice potatoes making layers in baking dish.
Between layers, sprinkle onions and 2 to 3 pats of butter.
Fill dish with layers. Pour in milk.
Cover with lid and bake for 45 minutes to 1 hour at 400°.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli until done.
While doing that, cook onion and butter.
When
all this is done, combine everything together in a buttered dish.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes (don't let it get dried out).

title: blueberry muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Butter 12 (3-inch) muffin tins generously.
In a small bowl, combine flour, salt, baking powder and baking soda, first setting aside a couple of tablespoons of flour to coat the blueberries.

title: noah's ark brownies
directions: Over double boiler, melt together butter and chocolate.
Remove from heat.
Stir in flour and vanilla.
With electric mixer, whip eggs and sugar until mixture resembles a yellow ribbon.
Blend in chocolate mixture on slow speed.
Stir in walnuts.
Spread batter in greased 9 x 13-inch pan and greased 8-inch square pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes for large pan, 30 minutes for small pan.
Do not overbake!
Yields 40 rich brownies.

title: tin roof dessert
directions: Mash 2 rows of package of Oreo cookies.
Melt margarine; pour onto crumbs and stir well with a fork.
Press crumbs into bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: egg and sausage breakfast dish
directions: Spray cooking dish (glass) with cooking spray.
Mix ingredients.
Place pieces of bread in the bottom of glass cooking dish.
Pour mixed ingredients in cooking dish (11 x 7 x 1 1/2-inch).
Cover and let set overnight.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix together and pour into casserole dish.
Bake at 350° until almost done.
Sprinkle with grated cheese and bake a few more minutes.
Do not overcook.
It should be soft in center (30 to 40 minutes).

title: hidden valley pasta primavera
directions: Steam carrots, broccoli and pea pods together until crisp-tender.
Cool.
Cook fettuccine in chicken broth, just until tender.
Drain and cool.

title: stew
directions: Brown hamburg, add other ingredients and simmer 1 hour or so. Flavor to taste.

title: southern red rice
directions: While bacon is draining, add chopped onion and rice to bacon grease.
Fry until brown.
Pour in tomatoes and all the remaining ingredients.
Stir well, place in baking dish, cover and cook in moderate oven for one hour, stirring with fork occasionally to fluff.
(May also be baked in a heavy iron skillet or cooked in an electric frying pan.)

title: wonderful potatoes
directions: Bring water, butter and salt to a boil.
Remove from heat; add milk and potatoes.
Let stand.
May need to add a little more milk; stir until fluffy.
Combine sour cream and cream cheese; add to potato mixture.
Stir in onions.
Put in 1 1/2-quart casserole; dot with butter.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Bake at 325° for 40 minutes.

title: west pork chops and rice
directions: Brown chops in oil.
Remove.
Stir in chili powder.
Add green pepper, rice, tomato sauce, water and salt; cook for 2 minutes. Pour into shallow 8-cup baking dish.
Put chops over rice.
Place onion slices on chops.
Cover dish.
Bake at 375° for 45 to 60 minutes.
Add a little water after 40 minutes to keep moist.

title: apple fritters
directions: Mix flour, salt, sugar and baking powder together.
Make a well in the center of the mixture and add oil, egg and milk; mix well.
Add vanilla and nutmeg.
Grate apple on large side of grater.
Stir into batter and refrigerate overnight. Fry in deep oil by the heaping spoonfuls.
Drain fritters on paper towels. Just before serving pour Lemon Sauce over fritters and sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: chicken elegant
directions: Combine dressing, soup and preserves and pour over chicken that has been placed in a large shallow baking dish or pan.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°; then 1 hour at 315°.
Baste with pan juices occasionally.
Serve with rice.

title: apple-stuffed turkey tenderloins
directions: In small saucepan, combine apple, orange juice, jellied cranberry sauce and marmalade; cook until apple is soft but holds its shape.
Rinse tenderloins and pat dry.
Slice them lengthwise not all the way through to form a pocket.
Spoon some of the apple mixture into pocket.
Secure cut edges with toothpick or skewer pin.
Dip tenderloins in beaten egg and dredge in crumbs.
Place them in a casserole so that they do not touch.
Bake 25 to 35 minutes at 350°.
Heat remaining fruit mixture and serve over tenderloins.
Yields 5 to 8 servings.

title: best chicken and asparagus casserole
directions: Sprinkle chicken with pepper and Accent.
Pour corn oil into frying pan.
Heat oven medium heat.
Add chicken.
Saute slowly about 6 minutes until white and opaque.
Drain on paper towel. Line bottom of 9 x 9-inch baking dish with asparagus.
Place sauteed chicken over the asparagus.
Mix together chicken soup, mayonnaise, lemon juice and curry powder; pour over chicken and asparagus.
Sprinkle cheese over top.
Cover and bake at 375° for 30 minutes.
May be assembled and refrigerated the day before. Then bake before serving.

title: autumn apple salad
directions: In saucepan, combine pineapple and sugar; bring to a boil and boil for 3 minutes.
Add jello.
Stir until dissolved.
Add cream cheese.
Stir until mixture is combined.
Cool.
Fold in apples, nuts, celery and whipped topping.
Pour in 9-inch square pan. Chill until firm.

title: cornish pasties
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Roll out pastry thinly and cut into 5 inch rounds.
Mix together round steak, potatoes, onion, thyme, Scotch, mustard, salt, pepper and parsley.	Place 3 Tbsp. mixture in center of each round; dot with butter.
Moisten edges of pastry and fold dough over filling to make pillow shapes; seal edged with fork.
Cut 2 small slits in top and brush with beaten egg.	Place on baking sheet and bake 40-50 minutes or until pasties are golden brown.
Serve warm.
Yield: 8 pasties.

title: delicious baked beans
directions: Place the beans in a casserole dish.
Add the remaining ingredients, except the bacon, and stir thoroughly.
Add bacon, covering top of the beans.
Bake covered for 40 minutes at 400°. (Stir occasionally.)
Uncover and bake 10 minutes more.
Serves 4.

title: sweet-sour shrimp
directions: Combine all ingredients in pressure cooker and close cover securely.
Place pressure regulator on vent pipe.
Cook 2 minutes. Cool pressure at once.
Thicken sauce, if desired, and serve on hot rice.
Makes 4 servings.

title: quick pumpkin bread
directions: Sift together flour, baking powder, baking soda, salt, cinnamon and cloves.
In a large bowl, beat until light and fluffy the sugar, shortening and eggs, then beat in pumpkin.
Add dry ingredients, 1/3 at a time, alternately with milk and vanilla.
If desired, fold into batter 1/2 cup of coarsely chopped nuts.
Pour batter into a greased pan and bake about 1 hour or until bread tests done (clean toothpick).
Yield: Makes 1 (9 x 5-inch) loaf.

title: lumpia
directions: Mix above ingredients.
Add seasoned salt to taste.
Wrap in egg roll wrappers.
Heat electric skillet with enough vegetable oil to cover half an egg roll.
Cook until wrapper is brown and crispy.

title: ice pack for boo boos
directions: Mix rubbing alcohol with water.
Freeze in a zip-type plastic bag.
Keep it in your freezer.
Even frozen it will be pliable enough to form to a knee or elbow or bump on the head.
After its used, just toss it back in the freezer and it will be ready for the next time.
When you use it, be sure to place a damp cloth between the skin and the ice pack in order to prevent frostbite.

title: best yet cake
directions: Preheat oven to
350°.	Mix cake ingredients by hand.
Bake for 35 minutes in a 9 inch x 13 inch pan sprayed with vegetable oil.

title: brownies
directions: Mix in order given.
Bake in greased 9-inch square pan at 325° about 25 minutes.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar if you like or ice with chocolate topping.

title: five cup salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Chill 24 hours for best results.

title: connecticut beef supper
directions: Heat oil in large skillet.
Cook and stir meat and onions in oil until meat is brown and onions are tender.
Add water; heat to boiling.
Reduce heat; cover and simmer 50 minutes.
Heat oven to 350°.
Pour meat mixture into ungreased baking dish (13 x 9 x 2-inch).
Arrange potato slices on meat.
Stir together soup, sour cream, milk, salt and pepper.
Pour over potatoes.
Sprinkle with cheese and cereal.
Bake, uncovered, 1 1/2 hours.

title: chocolate oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix butter, sugar, cocoa and milk; bring to a boil.
Boil 3 minutes.
Set aside and while hot, stir in oats and vanilla.
Drop quickly on waxed paper or greased cookie sheet.
Do not bake. Yields 30 cookies.

title: egg dish
directions: Combine white sauce and ketchup.
Add sliced eggs, mushrooms, peas and pimentos.
Heat thoroughly.
Broil tomato slices 5 minutes.
Place on toast.
Pour sauce over all.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Mix the dressing first and refrigerate.
The dressing isn't added until just before serving.
Place all ingredients except sunflower seeds in the bowl. Right before serving, add sunflower seeds and dressing. Serves 8.

title: lentil soup
directions: Wash lentils and soak overnight covered in cold water.
Drain lentils.
In Dutch oven saute diced bacon until golden.
Add sliced onions and diced carrots and saute until onions are golden.
Add lentils, water, sliced celery, salt, pepper, thyme and bay leaves. With medium grater, grate peeled potato into lentil mixture; add ham bone.
Simmer, covered, 3 hours.
Lentils should be nice and tender.
Remove bay leaves and ham bone.
Cut all the bits of meat from bone and return meat to soup.
If you are serving at once, add the lemon juice.
If you are planning to serve another time, just refrigerate the soup and add lemon juice before serving.

title: spinach rolls
directions: Wash spinach leaves and dry; lay aside.
Mix remaining ingredients.
Crumble bacon.
Lay 1 tablespoon of mixture in spinach leaves and roll it up.

title: chicken and rice casserole
directions: Butter dish.
Place rice in bottom; salt and pepper chicken. Place on rice.
Add soup and water.
Sprinkle onion soup mix on top.
Cover with dabs of butter.
Cover and bake slow for 1 hour.

title: marinated carrots
directions: Mix the tomato soup, oil, vinegar, Worcestershire sauce, mustard and sugar; heat well.
Let cool.
Pour over drained carrots, onions and pepper.
Cover; let stand in refrigerator. Serve cold as a relish.
Will keep well for at least 2 weeks.

title: nort's barbecue sauce
directions: Melt butter in medium saucepan.
Add rest of ingredients.
Let lemon rinds cook in sauce, then add spices.
Simmer on low heat for about 10 minutes.
Baste on the grill your choice of meat (beef, chicken, pork or fish).
Sliced potatoes wrapped in foil are great.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350.
Cook broccoli and drain.
Crack eggs into large bowl and whisk together.
Add soup, mayonnaise and cheese.
Stir well.
Add broccoli.
Stir well.
Place mixture into ungreased 8 x 8 x 2 casserole dish.
Coarsely crush the Ritz crackers.
Melt butter and pour over the crackers.
Stir gently. Cover the top of the broccoli mixture with the crackers and butter topping.
Bake for about 40 minutes or until set.

title: regular brownies
directions: Melt over hot water chocolate and Wesson oil (may use 4 tablespoons cocoa in place of chocolate).
Beat in sugar and eggs. Sift together and stir in flour, baking powder, salt and chopped nuts.
Spread in well-greased oblong pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
A slight imprint will be left when touched with finger.

title: strawberry angel roll
directions: Heat oven to temperature as directed on cake package.
Line 15 x 10 x 1-inch baking pan with foil.
Lightly sprinkle clean towel with cocoa.
Prepare cake mix according to package directions. Spread batter in foil-lined pan.
Bake in preheated oven for 25 to 30 minutes or until deep golden brown and top springs back when lightly touched in center.
Immediately
invert cake onto towel sprinkled with cocoa.
Remove baking pan; carefully remove foil. Starting at shorter end, roll up cake in towel; cool completely on wire rack.
Unroll cooled cake; remove towel.
Spread cake with yogurt; roll up again, rolling loosely to incorporate yogurt. Cover; freeze until firm, 3 hours or overnight.

title: judy's green bean casserole
directions: Mix green beans, soup, cheese, mayonnaise, egg, pepper to taste and 1/2 of the onions.
Put in a 2-quart casserole dish. Cook at 350° for 30 minutes.
Sprinkle the rest of onions on top and bake for 5 minutes.

title: the original better-than-sex cake
directions: In an oblong baking pan, bake cake according to package directions.
Bring pineapple and sugar to a boil.
Pour over the warm cake and cool.
Beat pudding and milk and spread over cake. When the pudding is firm, spread Cool Whip over cake and top with coconut.
Chill until serving.
Makes 10 to 12 servings.

title: easy potato cheese soup
directions: Combine contents of potato package including cheese sauce mix, broth, water, carrots and celery in a 3 1/2-quart saucepan.
Bring to a boil, stirring occasionally.
Reduce heat and simmer covered for 15 minutes or until potatoes are tender.
Remove from heat. Add milk.
Garnish with parsley.

title: veg-all casserole
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients and put into a small baking dish. Cover with cheese, then crushed Ritz crackers.
Dot with butter. Bake for 20 minutes at 350°.

title: beef pie
directions: Dip beef cubes in flour and brown in Crisco.
Salt and pepper and cook until tender in a little water.
Heat shortening in skillet; add celery, onion and green pepper; saute until soft. Stir in beef, soup and seasonings.
Place meat mixture between two pastry crusts, slashing top to make steam vents.
Bake in hot oven (400°) for 40 to 50 minutes.

title: "chili" homemade
directions: Brown together the ground beef, cooking oil, onion and garlic. Stir in remaining ingredients.
Mix well.
Cover and simmer 40 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Chili is best when cooked and let cool for several hours, then heat to desired temperature.
Do not cook again!
Do not cook again!
Yours for better chili eatin'.

title: deer or beef jerky
directions: Cut meat into very thin strips.
Put into sauce and cover. Refrigerate overnight.
Bake in 200° oven for several hours.
Test by breaking jerky.
Should be almost crisp.
Store in freezer.

title: lemon cake pie
directions: Combine sugar, flour, butter, salt and egg yolks.
Blend until smooth.
Beat in lemon juice and peel.
Add milk, beating slowly. Beat egg whites stiff but not dry.
Fold in mixture.
Bake pie shell at 350° for 5 minutes.
Pour in filling.
Bake 40 minutes or until filling is firm.
When cut there will be a delicate cake on top of the pie filling.

title: blueberry salad 2
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Add undrained pineapple and blueberry pie filling.
Mix thoroughly.
Chill until congealed.

title: tomato soup salad dressing
directions: Combine into blender and blend well.

title: blueberry pie
directions: Bake crusts and cool. Whip cream cheese and confectioners sugar. Stir in Dream Whip, flavorings and pineapple. Pour 1/2 of the mixture into each crust and top each with blueberry filling.

title: mixed pickles
directions: Slice pickles into 1/2-inch pieces.
Cover with mixture of 1/4 cup pure salt and water per 2 quarts of pickles used.
Boil the rest of ingredients in large pan.
Add pickles.
Bring to a boil again.
Can and store.

title: taco chip dip
directions: Layer cream cheese, salsa and Cheddar cheese.
May serve cold or heat in microwave.
Serve with chips.

title: fiesta taco salad
directions: Preheat oven to 425°. Line 2 baking sheets with foil. Divide 6 inverted 6-ounce custard cups among baking sheets. Place 3-inches apart. Spray tortillas with cooking spray. Drape one over each cup. Bake until lightly browned and crisp, about 8 minutes. Cook beef until browned; drain. Add beans; simmer, stirring frequently, for 5 minutes. Invert tortilla bowls. Layer lettuce, beef, green onions and tomatoes and sprinkle with chips and cheese.

title: chicken and rice casserole
directions: Cover bottom of casserole with rice and put enough water in to cover rice.
Lay some chicken parts on the rice.
Pour soup over it and sprinkle dry onion soup over it.
Bake at 325° to 350° for 1 to 2 hours.

title: peach melba layer cake supreme
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Grease and flour two 8-inch round cake pans.
Combine flour, baking powder and salt; set aside.
Beat butter at medium speed in large bowl of electric mixer until light and fluffy.
Blend in egg yolks and vanilla.
Alternately add dry ingredients and apple juice concentrate, beating well after each addition; spread evenly into prepared pans.
Bake 20 minutes or until golden brown and wooden pick inserted in centers comes out clean.
Cool 10 minutes in pans on wire racks.
Remove from pans; cool completely.

title: pumpernickel bread dip
directions: Mix together and serve with pumpernickel bread slices.

title: vidalia onion casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In medium pan, combine onions with water to cover.
Bring to a boil and boil for 1 minute.
Drain. Transfer to an 8-inch square baking dish.
In a bowl, combine egg, cream, salt and pepper.
Pour over onions.
Sprinkle with cheese, then paprika.
Bake 25 minutes.
Makes 6 servings.

title: jam cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar lightly, then add eggs and beat all together.
Combine buttermilk and soda and add alternately with flour and spices.
Add preserves last.
This makes a large cake. Two-thirds of the recipe makes two 8-inch layers.

title: hand prints
directions: You will also need a pie tin, glitter, pencil, markers, ribbon or yarn, paint and white glue.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Melt butter.
Stir in flour, onion, salt and pepper.
Cook until bubbly.
Remove from heat.
Stir in broth and milk.
Boil and stir 1 minute.
Stir in chicken and vegetables.
Put in crust. Bake at 425° for 35 minutes.

title: maple cream pie
directions: In a medium saucepan, combine the condensed milk and maple syrup.
Cook over low heat, stirring constantly until mixture bubbles up, then cook, uncovered, for 4 minutes, watching carefully to prevent scorching.
Pour into the pie shell.
Let cool completely, about three hours.
Top with whipped cream.

title: light cocoa frosting
directions: Mix together and beat on high speed of mixer about four minutes or until soft peaks, then frost cake.
