title: holly cookies
directions: Melt margarine and marshmallows together.
Add food coloring. Pour mixture over corn flakes, coating them.
Drop onto wax paper by teaspoonful and shape into a wreath and add cinnamon candies.

title: spinach rolls
directions: Cook spinach and squeeze out liquid.
Chop spinach finely and set aside.
In a bowl combine ricotta cheese, flour, egg, parmesan cheese, and nutmeg.
Add chopped spinach and blend evenly.
Divide the mixture into 12 small portions.
Using palms of both hands, quickly roll spinach mixture to form ovals, 1 1/2 to 2 inches long.
Repeat the process until all 12 ovals are shaped.
If mixture starts to stick to your hands, dust them lightly with flour.
In a sauce pan over medium heat, heat olive oil.
Add garlic and cook for 1 minute.
Add tomatoes, oregano, basil, and salt. Simmer sauce gently for 5 minutes. Bring water to a boil in a large sauce pan, add a pinch of salt.
Add spinach rolls, 4 at a time.
When water returns to a boil remove spinach rolls with a slotted spoon, and transfer to a warm serving platter.
Repeat process until all rolls are cooked.
To serve top with sauce.

title: green enchiladas
directions: Heat soup, milk, pimentos, green chilies, grated Longhorn cheese and Velveeta.
Brown ground beef and onion.
Add to soup mixture.
In an 11 x 7-inch casserole, layer tortillas with soup mixture.
Start and end with tortillas.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: barbecue
directions: Pour barbecue in pan and add onions, brown sugar and garlic salt.
Mix well.
Simmer on stove 10 minutes, then add 2 teaspoons lemon juice.
Use on your favorite meats when you barbecue.

title: shrimp puff
directions: Heat oven to 325°.
Cut crusts from bread; cut slices into cubes.
Beat eggs, milk and seasonings together.
Stir in bread cubes, cheese and shrimp.
Pour into oblong (11 x 7 x 2-inch) baking dish.
Bake for 1 hour, or until center is set.
Serve immediately.
Serves 8.

title: cornbread stuffed bell peppers
directions: Cut bell peppers into 4 sections and scoop out the seeds and inside rind.
Mix your cornbread and tomatoes together well.
And mayonnaise to desired consistency.
Spoon cornbread mix into scooped out pepper "shells".
Refrigerate (covered) about 1 hour before serving.

title: j.c.'s vegetable soup
directions: Cook soup meat in about 2 quarts of water until tender.
Add ground beef and diced vegetables adding more water as needed. Cook until almost done.
Add all other ingredients and let simmer until macaroni is cooked.
Be sure and use a large soup kettle. Makes enough for company.

title: mexican fruit cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Place all ingredients in a large bowl and mix with a wooden spoon. Pour into a greased 13 x 9-inch pan. Bake for 40 minutes or until cake tests done. Makes 8 to 12 servings.

title: hot scalloped corn casserole
directions: Mix slightly. Bake, covered, at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: neiman-marcus poppy seed dressing
directions: Mix mustard, sugar, salt and vinegar.
Add onion juice and stir it in thoroughly.
Add oil slowly, beating constantly and continue to beat until thick.
Add poppy seed and lemon and beat for a few minutes.
Store in a cool place or the refrigerator, but not near the freezing cell.

title: lime sherbet punch(makes 2 gallons)
directions: Chill the Kool-Aid until mushy.
Pour over sherbet and blend partially.
Last, pour a bottle or two of 7-Up over the punch. Add 7-Up as needed.

title: fruitcake cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients, roll into small balls and bake on a greased cookie sheet for 25 minutes at 300°.
Mixture will be sticky.
You may have to keep hand damp while rolling into balls.

title: super nachos
directions: Brown meat and onion (season lightly).
Layer in a 10 x 15-inch dish the beans, meat, chilies, cheese and taco sauce. Bake 20 minutes at 400°.
Top with green onions, olives, avocado and sour cream.
Dip with tortilla chips.

title: sour cream softies
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add eggs, vanilla and sour cream. Mix well.
Sift flour, baking powder, salt and soda.
Add to cream mixture.
Add 1 1/2 cups walnuts, 1 (6 ounce) package of any flavor chips and 1 1/2 cups raisins or just leave them plain.
Drop by teaspoon onto greased cookie sheet.
Flatten with glass bottom. Sprinkle with cinnamon and sugar.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: old-fashioned pecan cream cake
directions: Cream well the butter and sugar; add eggs one at a time, beating after each addition.
Add milk, alternating with flour, beginning and ending with flour.
Stir in vanilla.
To make 6 thin layers, bake in iron griddle in moderately hot oven, about 375° (it only takes a few minutes to bake each layer.)
Cool layers on wax paper; whip 1 pint whipping cream, adding 3/4 cup sugar and 1 teaspoon vanilla; continue whipping until thick.
Add 1 cup pecans, grated fine.
Stack each cake layer upside down with cream between each layer.
Top layer should be top side up dusted with powdered sugar.
Keep refrigerated until used.

title: mexican layer dip
directions: In a glass bowl (preferably, but not necessary), layer all ingredients.
On bottom, place mashed avocados. Sprinkle with a pinch of salt. Add sour cream.
Mix tomato sauce and picante sauce together and place on sour cream. Add cheese, then green onions on top. Garnish with a few black olives, if desired.
Serve with Tostitos or corn chips.

title: barb's granola
directions: Mix together and spread into a greased 13 x 9-inch baking dish. Bake at 300° for 30 minutes.
Stir twice while baking.
Add raisins or figs after removing from oven.
Stir and put into plastic containers.

title: refrigerator cheese cake
directions: Have evaporated milk thoroughly chilled.
Dissolve lemon gelatin in boiling water; let cool.
Cream the cream cheese with vanilla and sugar.
Add cottage cheese; mix well.
Beat evaporated milk on high until very stiff.
Combine all.
Beat until creamy. Pour into crust.
Sprinkle reserved crumbs over top.
Chill 24 hours.

title: creole style macaroni salad
directions: Cook pasta until tender; rinse well.
Combine all ingredients. Mix well to coat pasta.
Chill before serving.
Enjoy.

title: tandy cake
directions: Beat eggs with mixer until thick and lemony;
gradually add sugar
while
beating.
Add
milk and vanilla.
Blend dry ingredients
together
and	carefully fold into egg mixture by hand.
Blend
well.
Pour into greased 13 x 15-inch jelly roll pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Spread peanut butter over hot cake.
Allow to cool.
Cover with melted chocolate or your favorite chocolate frosting.

title: 4 hour oven stew
directions: Place meat on the bottom of dish, then add vegetables.
Mix tapioca, water and sugar; pour over top.
Pour tomato juice over all.
Bake in oven at 250° for 4 hours.

title: refrigerator pickles
directions: Wash and cut cucumbers into slices and put into pint jars. Mix other ingredients together and pour over cucumbers.
Cover and refrigerate 4 days.

title: mincemeat pie
directions: Place ground venison and water in large pot. Boil until water is gone.
Separate meat with fork and add remaining ingredients, using enough orange juice to cover 3/4 of the ingredients.	Cook very slowly over low heat until fruit is tender (about 10 minutes).
Stir frequently to prevent sugar from scorching.
Make your favorite pie crust and add mince meat filling.
Cut slits in top crust and sprinkle with sugar.	Place in preheated oven 425° and bake 15 minutes.
Reduce heat to 350° and bake 40 minutes. Serve with ice cream, whipped cream or a wedge of Cheddar cheese. Makes enough for two 9-inch pies.

title: sloppy joes
directions: Brown meat and onion; add remainder of ingredients.

title: rolls
directions: Cut biscuits in fourths.
Roll in sugar and cinnamon.
Put in greased Bundt or angel food cake pan.
Melt oleo, ice cream and sugars and pour over rolls.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes. Let stand 1 minute, then turn out on a plate.

title: cream cheese pound cake
directions: Sprinkle 1/2 cup pecans in pan.
Cream butter and cheese. Gradually add sugar.
Add eggs one at a time, beating well after each one.
Add flour and salt.
Stir in vanilla and pecans. Grease and flour tube pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: buttered potato chip cookies
directions: Cream butter well.
Mix with sugar and beat until creamy.
Add flour to mixture a little at a time.
Add vanilla and potato chips to mixture.
Put teaspoon size drops onto an ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 325° for 25 minutes.

title: old-fashioned peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix shortening, peanut butter, sugars and eggs thoroughly. Sift together flour and other dry ingredients.
Add to shortening. Roll dough into 1-1/4 inch balls.
Place 2 inches apart on a greased cookie sheet.
Flatten with a fork dipped in flour.
Bake 10 minutes at 375 degrees.
Makes about 180 small cookies.

title: potato rolls recipe
directions: Dissolve yeast in 1/2 cup warm potato water.
Add to the potato water mixture.
Mix warm potato water, sugar and salt together. Mix egg whites and shortening together.
Add yeast mixture.
Mix together mashed potatoes and flour.
Add to yeast and egg white mixture.
Mix well and knead until smooth.
Place in refrigerator immediately.
Punch down occasionally.
May be kept for 5 days.

title: cabbage casserole
directions: Shred cabbage wide and layer bottom of baking pan with part of the cabbage.
Next slice potatoes and layer over cabbage and then slice the onions on top of this layer.
Layer again until all vegetables are used.
Sprinkle salt and pepper on top of the vegetables.
Place bacon strips on top.
Cook in oven for about 45 minutes.
Also can use Reynolds Wrap instead of baking pan and cook on grill for about 1 hour.

title: down home cheese biscuits
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
In large bowl mix together flour, baking powder and half of cheese.
Add shortening and butter, cut into flour mixture with pastry blender or 2 knives until it resembles coarse meal.
Make a well in center, pour in milk and mix with fork until dough forms a ball.
On lightly floured board knead dough 15 times until smooth.
Roll 1/2-inch thick, cut with cookie cutter or glass.
Bake on cookie sheet for 10 minutes, remove and sprinkle with remaining cheese.
Bake 2 to 3 minutes longer or until cheese melts.

title: tijuana taco dip
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a medium bowl combine refried beans, 3 tablespoons tomato sauce and 1/2 teaspoon Tabasco sauce; mix well.
Spread evenly in 1 1/2-quart baking dish.
Top with chopped tomato and Monterey Jack cheese.
In a large skillet brown beef and chili powder.
Remove from heat; drain fat.
Stir in remaining tomato sauce, sliced olives and remaining 3/4 teaspoon Tabasco sauce.
Spread evenly over Monterey Jack cheese.
Sprinkle with Cheddar cheese.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes or until cheeses melt. Remove from oven.
Garnish with green onions, tomatoes, olives and cilantro.
Serve warm with tortilla chips.

title: peanut butter balls
directions: Mix peanut butter, sugar, cracker crumbs, vanilla and margarine.
Form mixture into small balls.
Melt paraffin wax and chocolate chips over hot water.
Dip each ball into chocolate with toothpicks.
Put on wax paper.
Let harden.

title: springer clinic punch
directions: Chill ingredients ahead of time.
Mix all together in a large punch bowl. Can also add one pint of any flavor sherbet.

title: watermelon pickles
directions: Cover rind with cold water and cook until tender; drain off part of the water.
Add salt, sugar and vinegar.
Cook until clear and syrupy like heavy cream.
Let stand until cold or a day or so, then put into jars.
Add salt to your taste.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: In mixer bowl, cream together the butter or margarine and brown sugar.
Blend in eggs, rum and vanilla; beat at medium speed of electric mixer for 2 minutes.
(Mixture will be thin.) Thoroughly stir together the whole wheat flour, dry milk powder, baking soda and salt.
Add to creamed mixture, blending well. Stir in semi-sweet chocolate pieces, sunflower seeds and chopped peanuts.
Drop from teaspoon, 2 inches apart, onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° until done, 8 to 10 minutes.
Makes about 3 dozen cookies.

title: best-ever meat loaf
directions: Mix thoroughly 1/2 can soup, 1/2 can water, beef, bread crumbs, onion, egg and salt. Shape firmly into shallow baking pan. Bake at 375° for 1 hour and 15 minutes. Blend remaining soup, water and drippings.
Heat.
Serve with meat loaf.
Makes 6 servings.

title: gail's spinach casserole
directions: Cook spinach lightly.
Drain and squeeze all water out. Combine all other ingredients except bread crumbs.
Pour into a buttered casserole. Sprinkle with bread crumbs. Bake at 350° for 1 hour. Freezes well if cooked within 10 minutes of doneness.
Use leftovers for omelettes.

title: simple japanese stir-fry
directions: *Or any other vegetables.

title: quick and easy lasagna
directions: Prepare lasagna noodles according to package directions.
As noodles are cooking, in large skillet fry ground chuck, breaking up the pieces with fork constantly.
Let meat brown.
When meat is done, remove meat with slotted spoon into a bowl.
Saute the onion and garlic in pan drippings.
(If there is too much grease left from the meat, drain some of it but not all of it.)
When onion and garlic are transparent, add meat back to the skillet; mix thoroughly with onion and garlic.
(Meat may be salted.)
Add spaghetti sauce to meat mixture and let cook for 10 minutes, stirring occasionally.

title: chili mac
directions: Cook macaroni until done.
Drain and set aside.
Add ground beef and onions.
Cook until brown.
Add macaroni, water, chili powder, salt and kidney beans.
Cover; simmer for 15 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Top with shredded cheese.
Place over low heat until cheese melts.

title: apple pie
directions: Cook the apples, put them in the refrigerator.
Take it to somebody's house and eat it.
Poke 2 holes in it.

title: spiced beets
directions: Put beets in large
bowl.
Add	all of the ingredients. Let set in refrigerator overnight.

title: chicken vegetable pie
directions: Pour mixture in bottom crust and top with other crust.
Bake at 350° approximately 30 to 40 minutes.

title: summer sangria
directions: Mix all together in a pitcher and add ice to taste.
Pour into wine glasses when serving.

title: mexican salad
directions: In a large salad bowl, place a layer of lettuce, layer of kidney beans, onions, bell pepper, tomato and cheese.
Continue layering until used up.
A few minutes before serving pour crushed corn chips.
Add dressing.
Mix.

title: watergate salad
directions: Stir dry pudding mix into Cool Whip. Add remaining ingredients and chill.

title: party mix
directions: Mix together and spread on cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes or until crispy.

title: never fail pie crust
directions: Cut shortening into flour.
Mix egg with water, vinegar and salt.
Add to flour mixture and blend well.
Rest dough 5 minutes. Roll out and trim to fit pie plate.
Makes two 9-inch crusts.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Layer each in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cover with foil.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 20 minutes.

title: cream cheese pie(sugar-free)
directions: Cook pudding according to directions on package.
Use 3/4 of the package of cream cheese and stir until smooth.
Mix with pudding.
Pour into crust and refrigerate until set.
Add fresh strawberries before serving (optional).

title: ground beef casserole
directions: Grease pan with butter.
Peel and slice potatoes and place in bottom of pan.
Add beef, salt, peas, corn, carrots and onions. Top with another layer of potatoes.
Spread soup over this and cook at 400° for 1 hour or until brown.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Spread 1/2 cup shredded cheese on top before baking. Cook broccoli as directed in microwave. Then mix all ingredients together. Pour in buttered 9 1/2 x 13 x 2-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: earthquake cake
directions: Spray a 9 x 13-inch pan with Pam.
Sprinkle the chopped pecans in the pan.
Sprinkle coconut over nuts.
Make cake mix as directed on box; pour over nuts and coconut.
Melt the oleo and mix with the cream cheese and powdered sugar; blend well together.
Drop by spoonfuls on top of cake.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes, or until done.

title: coconut cake
directions: Mix cake according to directions on box.
Bake in three pans. While baking, mix condensed milk and cream of coconut together. When cake is done, remove from pans and punch holes all over layers.
While cake is still hot, spoon the milk mixture on all the layers.
Let cool completely.

title: one-dish skillet dinner
directions: Brown sausage and pour off grease; add remaining ingredients. Cover and simmer 20 minutes.
Add sour cream and simmer for 5 minutes.
Serve immediately.

title: mint cordial
directions: Pick the leaves from the stalks of the mint; crush the leaves thoroughly.
Add the lemon juice and stand aside for 1 hour.
Boil the water and sugar to a syrup.
Pour over the lemon and mint. Cool and strain.
When cold, add the orange and pineapple juice and serve in glasses with a sprig of fresh mint in each.

title: chocolate sheet cake
directions: Mix flour, salt and sugar.
Place oleo, cocoa and water in saucepan and bring to boil.
Pour sugar and flour mixture into pan.
Add eggs, vanilla, buttermilk, soda and cinnamon.
Beat until smooth.
Pour into greased 11 1/2 x 16-inch pan.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.

title: frozen mud pie
directions: Preheat oven to 375 degrees.
Crush wafers.
Add melted butter.
Mix well with a fork and press into a 9 inch pie plate. Bake 10 minutes.
Cool completely.
Spread ice cream carefully onto crust.
Freeze 1 1/2 hours or until solid.
In a saucepan, cook cocoa, 2/3 cup sugar, 1/3 cup cream and butter until mixture is smooth and boils.
Stir in 1 teaspoon vanilla.
Cool, but do not let mixture get too hard to pour.
Pour sauce over frozen ice cream base.
Freeze at least 1 1/2 hours.
Before serving, whip remaining 1 cup cream with remaining 2 tablespoons sugar until soft peaks form.
Add remaining 1 teaspoon vanilla and spread over pie.
Garnish with chocolate shavings.
Makes 10 servings.

title: oven fried chicken
directions: Melt oleo.
Add dry ingredients.
Dip chicken in mix.
Place on shallow baking dish.
Pour any mixture leftover on chicken. Bake at 450° for about 50 minutes; do not cover.

title: honey graham goodies
directions: Break graham crackers into squares on line.
Cover bottom of cookie sheet with crackers.
Mix together the butter and brown sugar and heat until real hot.
Spoon over the graham crackers until gone.
Quickly sprinkle pecans over all and bake 10 minutes at 350°.

title: mashed potato salad
directions: Mashed potato preparation:
Peel about 6 medium potatoes into a 3 quart pan.
Cut potatoes as small chunks.
Add 2 cups water and 1/2 teaspoon salt.
Bring to boil.
Cover, simmer
20 minutes. Drain.
Add 8 tablespoons margarine.
Cover, melt margarine. Coarsely mash with masher.
Add about 1/2 cup evaporated milk. Beat with electric mixer on high.
Add evaporated milk in small amounts and beat until smooth.
Put 4 cups potatoes into large mixing bowl.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix with wooden spoon. Chill.

title: fruit brunch bars
directions: Beat eggs and sugar until fluffy.
Add flour, soda and salt alternately with fruit cocktail.
Mix well.
Spread into large greased cookie sheet with 1-inch sides. Top with coconut and nuts. Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: ann nelson's bratwurst cheese soup
directions: Steam broccoli and cauliflower and set aside.
In large saucepan, melt butter.
Add carrots and celery.
Cook until tender.
Stir in flour and pepper.
Add milk and bratwurst.
Cook over medium heat for 8 minutes or until mixture is thickened and bubbly.
Cook and stir 1 more minute.
Add cheese and vegetables. Stir constantly until cheese is melted.

title: strawberry pecan cake
directions: Combine dry cake mix, milk, eggs, and oil.
Beat until smooth and add remaining ingredients.
Bake in greased and lightly floured 9x13 pan at 350 degrees for 45 minutes or until done.
Let cool on rack and frost.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Combine hash browns, chicken soup, sour cream, cheese, margarine, onion, salt and pepper. Place in baking dish and bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: duck in burgundy
directions: Salt cavity of ducks.
Stuff with apple, celery and onion. Place in pressure cooker with 1 1/2 cups water.
Cook at 10 pounds pressure for 25 minutes.
Remove from pan and discard stuffing and broth.
Place ducks in roaster, breast down.
Add butter and cook on top of stove until browned.
Add wine, cover and bake at 325° for 1 hour or until done.

title: yellow squash casserole
directions: Stew squash and onion until tender enough to mash well.
Add salt, pepper and butter in a 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Put alternate layers of squash, cracker crumbs and undiluted mushroom soup. Bake at 400° until top begins to brown.
Sprinkle Parmesan cheese over top.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: beef pasties
directions: Cook meat; drain.
Add onion soup mix.
Clean and cut up vegetables into small pieces.
Mix with meat mixture.

title: independence day punch
directions: Mix ingredients in 1 gallon container and finish filling with water.
Chill or serve over ice.

title: dandylicious chocolate chip squares
directions: In a saucepan, melt shortening over medium heat.
Stir in brown sugar.
Cool slightly.
Combine flour, baking powder and salt; add gradually with eggs to shortening mixture.
Stir in the vanilla, chips and nuts.
Batter will be very stiff.
Spread into a greased and floured oblong pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Cut into squares while warm.

title: candy bar pie
directions: Melt candy bars, marshmallows and milk in double boiler over hot water over low heat.
Fold gently until smooth.
Pour into a shallow pan and put in freezer for 10 minutes to cool.
Fold in Cool Whip and pour into shell.
Before serving spread additional Cool Whip over the top.
Sprinkle with almonds.
Keep refrigerated.

title: apple turnovers
directions: Roll out biscuits to about 4-inches.
Put spoon of pie filling in center.
Seal edges.
Sprinkle with sugar, cinnamon or nutmeg. Bake at 350°.

title: berry-cherry pie
directions: Prepare pie crust.
Roll out half and line bottom of 9-inch pie plate.
Preheat oven to 350°.
In large mixing bowl, combine berries and cherries, all but 1 teaspoon sugar, the flour, lemon juice, lemon peel and melted butter.
Turn into pie plate.

title: oriental beef
directions: Cut beef into thin strips.
Combine all the rest of the ingredients except the broccoli and pour over beef.
Marinate for 4 to 6 hours.
(If you don't have time, mix the beef and marinade and continue on.)

title: orange delight
directions: Mix
jello according to directions on box.
Refrigerate for 1 hour.
After
jello has chilled, fold in with Cool Whip. Add drained
oranges
and
pineapple.
Mix
well.
Chill until firm, about 1 1/2 hours.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Cover cranberries with sugar and set overnight.
In the morning, add remaining ingredients, except bananas. Chill for a few hours.
Just before serving, add bananas (sliced).

title: italian meat loaf
directions: Mix this all together.

title: corn pudding
directions: Put 2 cans of corn in cake pan. In separate bowl, beat the eggs. Add melted butter, milk, sugar and flour. Pour mixture over corn and mix well. Bake in 350° oven for 1 hour.

title: sausage bread
directions: Thaw bread dough.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Saute sausage. Drain sausage and save grease.
Mix egg and cheese.
Mix sausage with cheese.
Roll out dough; divide mixture in half.
Place in dough.
Roll dough.
Poke holes in top with fork.
Brush with grease.
Bake for 30 minutes.
Enjoy.

title: 4 layer delight
directions: First Layer:
Mix together butter, flour and pecans.

title: apple brownies
directions: Mix dry ingredients together.
Add wet ingredietns.
Place in lightly greased 8 x 8-inch or 9 x 9-inch baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Mix together oil, sugar, eggs and vanilla.
Add flour, salt, soda and cinnamon; stir well.
Add apples and walnuts; stir. Spread in a 9 x 13-inch ungreased pan; bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: lava dip
directions: Hollow out Hawaiian bread and cut or tear middle into small pieces.
Mix onion, cheese and mayonnaise together and put in hollowed out bread.

title: microwave caramel corn
directions: Combine brown sugar, oleo, salt, syrup and oil in glass bowl or on stove in a pan.
Bring to a boil.
Cook for 2 more minutes. Remove and stir in soda.
Pour over popcorn in microwave-safe bowl.
Cook 1 1/2 minutes.
Shake.
Cook 1 1/2 minutes.
May need an additional 1 1/2 minutes.
Allow to cool.

title: rosemary's gingerbread
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add egg and dry ingredients alternately with milk and molasses.
Pour in greased pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: three-cheese chicken bake
directions: Cook lasagna noodles in boiling, salted water according to package directions.
Drain well.
Cook onion and green pepper in butter or margarine until tender.
Stir in condensed soup, mushrooms, pimiento, skim milk and basil.

title: coconut surprises
directions: Work cheese with spoon until light and fluffy.
Mix Sweet 'N Low, grated rinds and walnuts.
Form into 12 balls about 1-inch diameter (8 grams).
Roll in toasted coconut.
Refrigerate.
Makes 12.
One square equals 35 calories.

title: grandma's gingerbread cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Butter cookie sheets.
Heat molasses to boiling point, then add sugar, butter and milk.
Mix flour with baking soda, salt, nutmeg, cinnamon, ginger and cloves.
Add to first mixture and blend well.
Add a few tablespoons of water (enough so dough holds together and handles easily).
Chill mixture for easier handling.
Roll or pat out dough about 1/4-inch thick.
Cut into gingerbread people.
Bake 5 to 7 minutes.

title: chicken pie
directions: Boil chicken, bone and place in a large rectangular pan.
Mix soup and broth together.
Spoon over chicken.
Add drained Veg-All.
Mix flour, margarine and milk together.
Spoon over vegetables and bake at 375° for 1 hour or until brown.

title: marinated mushrooms
directions: Wash and cap mushrooms.
Cover in salt and boil 1 minute. Drain.
Prepare marinade from rest of ingredients.
Pour over caps and chill minimum of 24 hours.
Drain and serve cold.
Yields about 36.

title: sausage skillet dinner
directions: Saute sausage, onion, green pepper and celery in butter in a large skillet until vegetables are tender.
Stir in remaining ingredients, except cheese.
Cook over low heat, stirring frequently, until heated.
Sprinkle with cheese; cook until cheese melts.
Serves 6.

title: cream cheese icing
directions: Cream cheese and butter should be room temperature or soften, do not melt, in microwave. Blend cream cheese, butter and vanilla. Add sugar and mix. May be tinted with food coloring, if desired.

title: frozen fruit mold
directions: Mix cream cheese and sugar together.
To cream cheese mixture, add strawberries, pineapple and bananas.
Fold fruit into cheese mixture well.
Add Cool Whip to mixture.
Pour into large mold and freeze overnight.
Makes 12 cups.

title: pineapple pound cake
directions: Blend together the vegetable oil and sugar.
Add eggs to sugar mixture, one at a time.
Sift together flour, salt and baking powder.
Fold flour mixture into sugar and eggs.
Fold in crushed pineapple.
Add vanilla.
Bake in preheated oven at 350° for 1 hour and 25 minutes.

title: ginger cookies
directions: In a saucepan, combine sugar, shortening, molasses and ginger. Boil 1 minute.
Remove from heat.
Add baking soda dissolved in boiling water.
Stir until foamy, then add well beaten egg.
Sift cinnamon, salt and flour together.
Add to molasses mixture.
Mix well. Divide dough.
Roll on floured board to 1/4-inch thick.
Cut into desired shapes.
Bake on greased sheet at 375° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: orange-praline sweet potatoes
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
In large bowl, mash potatoes.
Add orange juice, rind, salt, ginger, pepper, 2 tablespoons butter and the egg.
Beat with electric mixer or wooden spoon until smooth and fluffy.
Spoon potatoes into buttered, shallow 1 1/2-quart casserole or 10-inch quiche pan, smoothing top.

title: watergate salad
directions: Mix pineapple, mandarin oranges and cottage cheese.
Add pudding mix and stir well.
Add marshmallows and mix.
Stir in Cool Whip.

title: baked artichoke dip
directions: Mix thoroughly all ingredients.
Bake 20 minutes at 350°. Serve hot with crackers or toast rounds.

title: claudette's meat loaf
directions: Mix all but last 3 ingredients until well blended and place in pan (glass does best).
Mix last 3 ingredients together well and spread over top of loaf.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: great beans
directions: Wash and clean beans, then cover with water; simmer for 1 hour.
Add all the other ingredients and cook on low heat for 2 hours more.
If using ground beef, add at this time.
For serving: Serve over brown rice; top with chopped lettuce, cheese or sour cream and salsa.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: spaghetti salad
directions: Cook spaghetti (do not overcook). Rinse well. Add veggies and dressing. Chill for at least 4 hours. Serve with Parmesan cheese.

title: grilled chicken
directions: Melt margarine. Add tarragon, seasoned salt, pepper and honey. Dip each chicken breast in mixture. Grill chicken breasts 5 to 7 minutes per side.

title: easy chili
directions: In a large frypan, brown ground beef.
Add remaining ingredients and simmer, uncovered, for 1 hour.

title: broccoli cornbread
directions: Mix all together.
Add just enough milk to thin to proper consistency.
Spray large iron skillet with Pam and sprinkle with corn meal.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 60 minutes.
If you do not want it too thick, use 2 skillets.

title: pumpkin apple streusel muffins
directions: In a large bowl combine the first 7 ingredients.
In a medium bowl combine eggs, pumpkin and oil.
Add liquid ingredients to dry ingredients.
Stir until moistened.
Stir in apple.
Spoon batter into greased lined muffin cups, 3/4 full.
Sprinkle topping over batter.
Bake in a preheated 350° oven for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: fattigmand bakkelse(poor man's cookies, norwegian)
directions: Beat eggs; add sugar, salt, vanilla or almond extract, cardamom and cream.
Stir in flour, a cup at a time.
Dough should be stiff. Chill.
Transfer a small amount of dough to a lightly floured surface.
Roll dough to 1/8-inch thickness; cut in 2 x 3-inch diamond shapes.
Make a lengthwise slit about 3/4 inch in the center of each diamond; gently pull one end of the diamond through the slit as far as possible.
Do not tear the dough.
Drop a few cookies at a time into deep, hot oil (more than 1 1/2 inches).
Fry until golden brown, turning once, about 1 minute.
Drain on paper towels.
When ready to serve, sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: applesauce cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour pan (13 x 9 x 2-inch). Beat all ingredients in large mixer bowl on low speed, scraping sides constantly, 30 seconds.
Beat on high speed 3 minutes.
Pour into pan.
Bake 60 to 65 minutes or until wooden pick comes out clean.

title: squash casserole
directions: Combine squash, onion, cracker crumbs and 1 1/2 cups of cheese.
Mix together eggs and milk and add to the squash mixture. Top with remaining 1/2 cup of cheese.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes until golden brown.

title: banana pudding
directions: Mix milk and instant pudding on low speed for 2 minutes.
Mix in sour cream.
Fold in 1/4 of container of Cool Whip.
In container of choice, layer wafers, bananas and mixture at least twice.
Spread remaining Cool Whip on top.

title: citrus slush
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients; stir until drink mix and sugar dissolve.
Divide into 2 heavy-duty gallon size zip-top plastic bags and freeze.

Remove bags from freezer 1 hour before serving. Place contents of each into a large pitcher and break into chunks. Add 1 bottle ginger ale to each pitcher, stir until slushy. Yields 1 1/2 gallons, or 3 quarts per bag of mixture.

title: no bake cookies
directions: Cook to boil; boil 5 minutes and then add 1/2 cup peanut butter and 3 cups oatmeal.
Drop fast with teaspoon on wax paper.

title: amazing egg custard
directions: Melt oleo in a 9 inch pan in the oven. Mix sugar, flour, eggs, milk and vanilla. Pour into pan and bake in a 375 degree oven until done. Cool.

title: lemon delite
directions: Mix butter, pecans and flour together.
Pat in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for about 20 minutes.
Let cool.
Mix cream cheese, Cool Whip and powdered sugar together.
Put on top of nut mix.
Mix lemon pudding and milk.
Spread on other layer.
Last layer is of Cool Whip; spread over entire pan.
Refrigerate until set, about 1 hour.
Must be kept in refrigerator.

title: copper penny carrots
directions: Cook carrots until tender; set aside.
Heat soup, oil, sugar, vinegar, mustard, Worcestershire sauce, salt and pepper.

title: clam stew
directions: Saute onion and celery in butter (or margarine).
Add potatoes and continue to saute.
Add dash of pepper, sage, hot sauce and parsley.
Stir.
Add clam broth.
Bring to boil and simmer until potatoes are cooked.
Turn down heat and add clams.
Heat, but do not boil.
Add milk of choice.
Allow to heat through, but do not boil.
Serve with a dot of butter, sprinkle of parsley, fresh ground pepper and oyster crackers.

title: pretzel salad
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix margarine and 2 tablespoons sugar together, add pretzels.
Pat into 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Bake 8 minutes.
Cool.
Mix cream cheese with 1 cup sugar until creamy. Fold in Cool Whip, spread on cooled pretzel crust.
Dissolve the strawberry Jell-O in 2 cups boiling water; set aside to cool.
Cut frozen strawberries in small pieces; while still frozen, stir into Jell-O.
Set mixture in refrigerator for 10 minutes.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Cube bread.
Brown sausage slightly.
Drain, cool and crumble. Set aside.
Beat eggs and add milk.
Add remaining ingredients and sausage; pour into greased or buttered 9 x 9-inch baking dish. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Let set a few minutes before serving.
Can be mixed in advance and kept in refrigerator and baked in the morning.
Recipe can also be cut in half.

title: banana split cake
directions: Combine crackers and butter.
Press into a 9 x 13-inch container.
Blend together the cream cheese, sugar, egg and lemon juice.
Pour mixture over the crust.
Pour the pineapple on the cream cheese mixture.
Slice the bananas on the pineapple.
Cover with Cool Whip.
Place cherries and nuts on top.
Refrigerate.

title: breakfast sausage pie
directions: Cook sausage until done.
Crumble, then drain.
Prepare a 9-inch pie shell.
Mix cheese and sausage.
Sprinkle in shell.

title: cruzan native side dish served with roast meats
directions: Peel and boil potatoes in salted water.
Mash when cooked. Saute pepper, celery and onions in little oil over a low flame until tender but not burnt.
Add tomato sauce and cook a few minutes.
Add mixture to mashed potatoes.
Mix thoroughly.
Add raisins, prunes and butter.
Bake in greased shallow baking pan at 325° for about 30 minutes or until brown.

title: prune cake
directions: Grease and flour tube cake pan.
Mix sugar and Wesson oil. Beat eggs in cup.
Add and mix sugar and oil.

title: hot spinach dip
directions: Cook spinach and drain well. Mix all ingredients in microwave safe bowl. Microwave on high until heated through (5-7 minutes). Serve with tortilla chips.

title: jalapeno pepper dip
directions: Use food processor.
Chop peppers, onion and garlic and then cut cheese in pieces and add to other ingredients.
When cheese is chopped and blended with other ingredients, add sugar, pimento and mayonnaise.
Continue processing until mixed well.
Chill several hours or longer before serving with chips.
Use chopper blade for processor.

title: potato salad
directions: Mix all together and chill.

title: mama's applesauce cake
directions: Combine shortening and sugar, mix well.
Add eggs and applesauce.
Add sifted dry ingredients.
Add applesauce, raisins and nuts.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour in tube or Bundt pan.

title: brownies
directions: Beat eggs; add sugar.
Melt margarine.
Mix cocoa into margarine.
Pour this chocolate mixture into egg and sugar mixture.
Blend well.
Add flour, vanilla and nuts.
Bake 25 minutes at 350° in a 13 x 9-inch greased pan.

title: onion roasted potatoes
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
In large plastic bag/container, add all ingredients.
Close bag/container and shake until potatoes are evenly coated.
Empty potatoes into a shallow 13 x 9-inch baking or roasting pan.
Bake, stirring occasionally, 40 minutes or until potatoes are tender and golden brown.
Garnish, if desired, with chopped fresh parsley.
Serves 8.
A great change from baked or mashed potatoes!

title: eggs sunny-side-up(microwave)
directions: Place a 9-inch browning dish in oven.
Cook on High for 3 minutes to preheat dish.
Add butter and allow to melt, tipping dish to coat entire surface.
Break eggs into dish; pierce yolks. Sprinkle lightly with dash of salt and pepper. Cover with glass lid.
Cook on High for 1 to 1 1/2 minutes or until desired degree of doneness.
Let stand 1 minute before serving.

title: coca-cola salad
directions: Mix cherry juice, gelatin and sugar in saucepan.
Heat, but do not boil.
Remove from heat; cool until mixture begins to thicken. Add Coca-Cola, cherries, pineapple and pecans.
Chill until firm. Makes 12 servings.

title: fresh salsa
directions: Stir well and serve ice cold with corn chips.

title: banana crush
directions: Dissolve sugar in water.
Add juices.
Peel and mash bananas; put through food mill or blender.
Stir into juices.
Ladle into freezer containers and freeze.
Before using, thaw in refrigerator about 4 hours.
In punch bowl, mix with equal quantity of 7-Up. Makes 60 (6 ounce) servings.

title: mud bars
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In bowl, combine flour, baking soda and salt; set aside.
In bowl, beat brown sugar, butter and vanilla extract until creamy.
Add egg; beat well.
Gradually add flour mixture.
Stir in 1 1/3 cups chocolate chips and nuts.
Spread into foil lined 9-inch square baking pan.
Bake at 375° for 23 to 25 minutes.
Immediately sprinkle 2/3 cup chocolate chips over top.
When chocolate chips are shiny, spread evenly.
When cool, chill 5 to 10 minutes to set chocolate.
Cut into 2 x 1 1/2-inch bars.
Makes 36 bars.

title: peppermint patties
directions: Mix powdered sugar, margarine, peppermint and evaporated milk well.
Roll in 1-inch balls and place in wax paper lined pan. Refrigerate 20 minutes and flatten with bottom of glass to about 1/4-inch.
Chill another 30 minutes.
Melt chocolate chips and shortening together.
Dip patties and place back in refrigerator on the wax paper for as long as they take to harden.
Makes 4 1/2 to 5 dozen.

title: chili con queso dip
directions: Heat oil in a medium saucepan over medium-high heat.
Add scallions, jalapenos and bell pepper; saute, stirring frequently until the vegetables are softened, 5 to 7 minutes.
Stir in the tomatoes and simmer 5 minutes.
Stir in the cream and heat the mixture just to boiling, then remove from the heat.
Break the cream cheese into small pieces and add to the hot cream mixture. Stir until completely melted.
Toss the shredded cheeses with the flour and stir into the hot mixture, one handful at a time, until all is completely melted.
Return the mixture to low heat and stir until heated through.
Season with the cumin, salt and pepper. Transfer the mixture to a chafing dish or crock-pot on low and serve warm with blanched broccoli and/or Pillsbury cornbread sticks (from refrigerator dough).
Makes about 1 quart.

title: quick rolls
directions: Put yeast and sugar in water.
Mix shortening in flour.
Start with 5 cups flour (self-rising) and work the shortening in flour good.
Pour in the water.
Stir good, then add more flour to make a stiff dough.
Put it on a floured board or counter and work 3 to 5 minutes.
Make out rolls or loaf of bread.
Let it rise twice its size.
Brush top with oleo.
Will keep in refrigerator for a week.
Cover tight.
Bake rolls at 425° and loaf at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: cranberry bread
directions: Cut shortening into dry ingredients.
Combine juice, peel and egg.
Add to rest.
Fold in berries and nuts.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour in greased loaf pan.

title: homemade buns
directions: Into large mixing bowl, combine salt, sugar and oleo.
Add the scalded milk (cool until lukewarm).
Add flour and egg; stir well. Dissolve dry yeast into the 1 cup lukewarm water and add to mixture, stirring well.
Add flour (1 cup at a time, stirring well each time).
If dough is still sticky, add up to 1 additional cup of flour.
Set aside and let rise for 1 hour or until dough is doubled in size.
Make into rolls and place onto greased cookie sheet.

title: diet lemon cheese cake
directions: Beat well the cream cheese and low-fat milk; add other ingredients and chill.

title: chicken club brunch ring
directions: Preheat oven to 375°. Combine mayonnaise, mustard, parsley and onion. Set aside. Combine chicken, bacon, 3/4 cup cheese and 1/3 cup of the mayonnaise mixture; mix well. Unroll crescent dough; separate into 16 triangles. Arrange triangles in a circle on a 13 inch round baking pan with wide ends of triangles overlapping in the center and points toward the outside. (There should be about a

5 inch diameter opening in the center.) Scoop chicken mixture evenly onto widest end of each triangle. Bring outside points up over chicken and tuck under inside edge. Place tomato slices between gaps in dough. Bake 20 - 25 minutes or until deep golden brown. Remove from oven; immediately sprinkle with remaining cheese. Put remaining mayonnaise mixture into cored pepper; set in middle of ring, surrounded by lettuce.

title: brownies
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add last 4 ingredients and mix well. Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch pan and bake at 325° for 30 minutes. Frost when cool.

title: 7-up cake
directions: Combine all ingredients into large bowl and mix at high speed for 4 minutes.
Bake at 325° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Sift flour, salt and soda into large mix master.
Add margarine, brown sugar, white sugar, egg, and vanilla.
Beat on No. 4
speed about 2 minutes, scraping bowl while beating.
Stop mixer, add chocolate chips and nuts.
Beat on No. 2 speed until blended (about 1/2 minute), scraping bowl while beating.
Drop by half
teaspoon on prepared cookie sheet.
Bake 350° about 12 minutes or until golden brown.
Yield: about 3 dozen cookies.

title: blueberry thrill muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Grease 18 muffin pan cups.
Sift dry ingredients in bowl.
Combine egg, sugar, melted shortening and milk; whisk until smooth.
Stir dry ingredients into egg mixture with rubber spatula just until combined.
Fold in 1 1/2 cups blueberries; spoon batter into prepared muffin cups.
Bake for 15 to 20 minutes, until toothpick inserted in center of muffin comes out clean.
Immediately remove muffins from cups.
Serve warm. Makes 1 1/2 dozen.

title: paper cup frozen salad
directions: Combine sour cream, lemon juice, sugar, salt, pineapple, banana, pecans, cherries and red coloring (if used).

title: coconut joys
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients in bowl; mix well.
Shape into balls.
Place in paper bon bon cups.
Make indentation in center of each ball.
Fill with chocolate.
Chill until firm.
Store in refrigerator.
Makes 3 dozen.

title: lurline's barbecue sauce
directions: Mix together the mustard, black and red pepper, Worcestershire sauce and liquid smoke.
Add catsup and vinegar.
Let come to a boil over low heat and cook for 5 minutes.

title: goo-ee burgers
directions: Grind bologna and cheese.
Add other ingredients.
Mix well. Spoon onto buttered buns.
Wrap individually in foil.
Bake 25 minutes in 325° oven.
Can be made ahead.
Refrigerate or freeze.

title: potato and sauerkraut casserole
directions: Cook potatoes until tender, mash smooth.
Cook bacon, dice. Chop onions and mushrooms.
Saute in bacon grease.
Drain and rinse sauerkraut.
Mix potatoes, sauerkraut, bacon, onions and mushrooms.
Stir thoroughly.
Season to taste with salt and pepper.
Spread mixture in baking dish.
Top with sausage pieces pressed slightly into the potatoes.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: molasses cookies
directions: Heat shortening over low heat.
Cool.
Add sugar, molasses and egg.
Beat.
Add flour, baking soda, cloves, ginger, cinnamon and salt.
Mix well.
Chill.

title: lazy stroganoff
directions: Mix soups and water, then mix with meat.
Bake, covered, at 275° for 3 to 4 hours.
Stir in second can of soup if cooked noodles are added.
Stir in 1/2 cup sour cream just before serving.
Serve over rice or noodles.

title: individual chicken pies
directions: In saucepan melt butter.
Add onion and cook until tender. Stir in flour and salt, seasoning and pepper. Add broth and stir to mix well.
Cook and stir until thick and bubbly.
Add cubed chicken and vegetables and heat until bubbly.

title: chicken roll-ups
directions: Combine first three ingredients (do not use all of the cheese). Roll out each biscuit and fill with 2 tablespoons of chicken mixture. Roll up and place in a greased baking dish. Bake for 15 to 20 minutes in 400° oven. Remove from oven. Combine soup and milk; pour over biscuits and sprinkle with cheese. Return to oven for 10 more minutes, until golden brown.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Combine oil and slightly beaten eggs in a bowl and stir; add sugar and 2 cups of the flour.
Add cinnamon and baking powder to the remaining 1/2 cup flour, mixing well, and add to oil, egg, sugar and flour mixture.
Add diced apples and pecans.
Beat with electric mixer on medium speed for 5 minutes until well blended, then beat for 5 minutes at high speed.
Turn into a greased and floured Bundt pan and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: microwave hot cocoa
directions: Combine cocoa, sugar and salt in a 2-quart microwave-safe glass measure or casserole; blend in water.
Microwave on High for 2 to 2 1/2 minutes, stirring occasionally, until mixture boils. Stir.
Microwave on High (so mixture boils) for 1 minute.
Stir in milk.
Microwave on High for 3 to 4 minutes, stirring occasionally, until cocoa is hot.
Do not boil.
Stir in vanilla. Beat with rotary beater until foamy.
Serve immediately.
Yields 4 to 5 servings.
Top each mug of cocoa with a marshmallow or whipped topping.

title: american apple pie
directions: Heat oven to 425°.
Mix sugar, flour, nutmeg, cinnamon and salt.
Stir sliced apples into mixture.
Pour all ingredients into pastry shell.
Cover with top crust pastry.
Make slits in top. Cover edges with aluminum foil (remove foil during the last 10 minutes of baking).
Bake for 40 to 60 minutes, until crust is brown and juice begins to bubble through slits.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Stir-fry until done, not browned.
Drain off grease.
Pour into 9 x 12-inch baking dish.
Sprinkle grated Cheddar cheese on top.
Put sausage on top of that.
Cover with foil.
Refrigerate overnight.
Take foil off and bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: potato chip chicken
directions: Dip chicken in melted butter.
Shake in bag of "CRUSHED" potato chips.
Bake in 350° oven for 1/2 hour.

title: basic crepes
directions: Place flour in medium bowl.
Combine milk, margarine and egg. Add mixture to flour, stirring with a wire whisk until almost smooth.
Cover batter and chill for 1 hour.

title: fruit punch
directions: Boil sugar and water together for 5 minutes.
Combine juices with tea; add to boiled sugar and water.
Just before serving, add ginger ale.
Makes 55 servings.

title: breakfast pizza
directions: Grease square cake pan.
Lay crescent rolls in bottom of a pan.
Press to seal.
Sprinkle on cheese and ham evenly.
In mixing bowl, combine egg, milk and salt. Beat well. Pour slowly over ham layer.
Cover with foil or plastic wrap tightly.

title: fabulous fondue
directions: Mix with electric mixer until blended and smooth. Makes great dip for fruits such as: Strawberries, bananas, cantaloupe, peach slices, etc.

title: buttered carrots
directions: Pare carrots and cut into julienne strips.
Place in a large heavy saucepan with sugar, salt, pepper, butter and water. Cover. Bring to a boil.
Simmer 10 to 15 minutes or until carrots are tender and moisture is evaporated.
Remove cover to evaporate moisture, if necessary. Turn carrots into serving bowl and sprinkle with parsley.
Makes 6 servings.

title: mom's sugar cookies
directions: Thoroughly cream shortening, sugar and vanilla.
Add egg and beat until fluffy.
Stir in milk.
Sift other dry ingredients together and blend into creamed mixture.
Divide dough in half and chill 1 hour.
On lightly floured surface, roll dough to 1/8-inch thickness.
Bake on greased cookie sheet at 375° about 6 to 8 minutes.
Makes 2 dozen.

title: helen's hawaiian chicken
directions: Put 4 or 5 skinned chicken breasts into an electric frying pan (large skillet will work) and add 1 quart Tropicana or other natural orange juice over them.
Add pineapple chunks, sliced peaches, a few maraschino cherries and mandarin oranges.
Cook over low heat or if electric skillet, about 250°, for a couple of hours, until chicken is very tender.
Serve over rice.

title: orange tapioca salad
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients together over medium heat until thick. Chill.
Mix in Cool Whip and oranges and let set.

title: blueberry-krisp
directions: Butter quart size casserole dish.
Pour can of blueberry pie mix into dish.
In a separate mixing bowl, combine flour, sugar, oleo and salt.
Cut with pastry cutter or fork until mixture is crumbly (small pieces).
Add pecans to this mixture.
Sprinkle crumbly mixture on top of blueberry mix.
Bake in 350° oven for 35 minutes or until crispy brown on top.
Serve warm with whipped cream or other topping.
Serves 6.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Drain and mash sweet potatoes; add sugar, flour and margarine and then add all other ingredients and beat well.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes.
Reduce heat to 350° and bake for 30 more minutes.

title: seafood thermidor
directions: Cut fish into 1/2-inch cubes.
Poach in greased skillet with onion and lemon, covered with water, for 5 to 6 minutes.

title: chocolate clair cake
directions: Mix pudding according to directions.
Fold in Cool Whip. Layer pan with graham crackers, alternating with pudding.
Finish with graham crackers on top.
Spread on icing.
Cool.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook squash and onion together until almost done; drain. Combine with other ingredients.
Put into greased casserole.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes or until done.

title: chicken and rice
directions: Boil chicken.
Cut into small pieces.
Add rice, garlic, salt and margarine.
Simmer for 20 minutes or until rice is tender. Add cheese and salt and pepper to taste.

title: fruit medley(for diabetics)
directions: Combine pineapple, orange slices, apple and cherries in a medium bowl.
Fold in yogurt.
Cover and refrigerate until chilled.
Yields 7 servings (2/3 cup).

title: cheese cake
directions: Butter a 10-inch spring-form pan.
Sprinkle with graham cracker crumbs.
Mix together and beat until smooth after each addition the cream cheese, eggs, sugar, vanilla and almond extracts.
Pour into prepared pan.
Bake at 325° for 40 minutes. Mix sour cream and 2 tablespoons sugar.
After baking cheese cake for 40 minutes spoon sour cream on cake and bake 10 minutes additional.
Cool in oven for 1 hour with door open.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: emperor's chicken
directions: Combine all ingredients in casserole dish.
Put can of chow mein noodles on top.
Bake 1 hour at 325°.

title: pimento cheese spread
directions: Cook first 4 ingredients
in top of double boiler until thick (like soft custard).
Add the cream cheese.
Beat with a rotary beater, adding pimentos.

title: granny's pecan pie
directions: Mix
all ingredients together.	Pour
into
9-inch
pie shell. Place in 350° oven and bake
minutes
or until you can stick a toothpick in center and it comes out clean.

title: linguine salad
directions: Cook linguine and drain.
Combine in bowl linguine, cucumbers, tomatoes, about 1/2 bottle of seasoning and salad dressing.
Stir and refrigerate.

title: chocolate mint freeze
directions: For crust, combine crumbs and 4 tablespoons butter.
Reserve 1/2 cup, press remainder in a 9-inch square pan and freeze. Spread ice cream over crust and freeze again.
Melt 1/2 cup butter and chocolate over low heat.
Gradually stir in beaten egg yolks, 10x sugar, nuts and vanilla.
Set aside.
Beat egg whites to stiff peaks, fold into chocolate mixture and spread on top of ice cream. Sprinkle with reserved crumbs.
Cut in squares to serve.
Yield: 8 servings.

title: salmon patties
directions: Remove bones from salmon; add onions, egg and enough corn meal to be able to form patties. The more meal the better. If you get too much, the mixture will get crumbly and not form good patties. If this happens, just add a little milk. Fry in pan over medium heat until brown or put on cookie sheet. Spray with cooking spray on top and bottom. Bake until golden brown.

title: quick dill pickles
directions: Boil together water, vinegar and salt.
Remove from heat and let cool completely.
Place 1/2 stalk of dill in bottom of a bean pot (cookie jar size) along with garlic bud.
Add washed cucumbers.
Pour cooled water over cucumbers (being sure that all cucumbers are covered).
Add other half of dill stalk; cover. Keep covered for three days.
After that, refrigerate.

title: beef barley soup
directions: In a soup pot, combine all the ingredients except the barley; cover and bring to a boil over high heat. Reduce the heat to low, cover, and simmer for 20 minutes, stirring occasionally. Add the barley and simmer for 15 to 20 more minutes, or until the barley is tender.

title: soft caramels
directions: Melt butter.
Add sugar and salt.
Heat until sugar dissolves. Stir in corn syrup.
Gradually add Eagle Brand milk, stirring all the time.
Cook until this mixture reaches 245°.
Stir in vanilla. Pour into a 9 x 13-inch buttered pan; cool.
Cut into squares and wrap in waxed paper.

title: vanilla brownies
directions: Beat eggs, margarine and cream cheese with mixer.
Add remaining ingredients and mix with hands.
Spread in 9 x 13 greased pan.
Bake at 300 degrees for 50 minutes.

title: taco dip
directions: Use 10-inch quiche dish or any round dish 1 inch high.
Mix cream cheese and sour cream together and spread evenly in dish. Layer evenly:
taco hamburg, onion, green pepper, black olives and tomatoes.
Pour picante sauce over and cover top with cheese. Serve with nacho chips.

title: delicious bran muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Lightly grease muffin pan or line muffin pan with muffin papers.
Cover raisins with warm water for 5 to 10 minutes.
Blend wheat bran with boiling water; let stand for 5 minutes.
In order, blend egg, honey, milk and bran mixture thoroughly with wire whisk.
Blend remaining dry ingredients in a separate bowl.
Blend raisins, then dry ingredients into liquid ingredients until mixed.
Do not overmix!
Fill muffin cups almost full.
Fill any empty cups halfway with water.
Bake for 20 to 25 minutes.
Cool 5 to 10 minutes before removing from pan.
Makes 10 to 12 large muffins.

title: ruby lemonade punch
directions: Thaw concentrate.
Stir into cranberry juice cocktail.
Slowly add soda.
Stir gently with up and down motion.
Serve over ice. Garnish with lemon slices.

title: pasta and shrimp(yield: 4 servings)
directions: 1. Place 2 Tbsp. olive oil in large saut pan and heat on medium high. Place red pepper slices in pan and saut till browned.

title: barbecued beef
directions: Brown sliced onion in the fat (in large stewing pot).
Add meat and all ingredients.
Cook for 2 to 2 1/2 hours, stirring occasionally.
Remove meat from pot and shred it with a knife and fork.
Place back in sauce.
Serve over hamburger buns or over noodles.
Serves approximately 12 people.

title: fruit salad
directions: Mix all together and enjoy!

title: coolrise sweet rolls
directions: Combine 2 cups flour, yeast, sugar and salt in a large bowl. Stir well to blend.
Add softened butter or margarine.
Add hot tap water to ingredients in bowl all at once.
Beat with electric mixer at medium speed for 2 minutes.
Scrape bowl occasionally.
Add eggs and 1 cup more flour.
Beat with mixer at high speed for 1 minute or until thick and elastic.
Stir in remaining flour gradually with wooden spoon.
(Use just enough flour to make a soft dough which leaves sides of bowl.)
Turn out onto floured board.
Round up into a ball.
Knead 5 to 10 minutes or until dough is smooth and elastic.
Cover with plastic wrap, then a towel.
Let rest for 20 minutes on board.
Punch down.
Divide and shape as desired into 2 1/2 to 3 dozen rolls.
Place into greased baking pans or on greased baking sheets.
Brush surface of dough with oil.
Cover pans loosely with plastic wrap.
(May refrigerate 2 to 24 hours.)

title: potato chip cookies
directions: Cream butter, sugar and vanilla until light and fluffy.
Stir in chips and flour.
Drop dough by teaspoon onto greased cookie sheet. Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes until brown.

title: chicken wings
directions: Sprinkle 1 envelope onion mix over wings that have been placed in large rectangle casserole dish.
Mix Italian dressing and apricot preserves together and pour over wings.
Sprinkle 1 envelope onion mix over top.
Cover with foil and refrigerate for several hours for best taste results.
Bake, covered, for 45 minutes at 350°.

title: fat-free granny's apple cake
directions: Combine the flours, sugar, baking soda and cinnamon; stir to mix well. Add the maple syrup, egg whites and vanilla extract; stir to mix well. Fold in the remaining ingredients.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli according to package directions.
Mix soup, rice and Cheez Whiz; set aside.
Saute onion and pepper in small amount of water and 2 tablespoons margarine.
Add to mixture and mix well.
Fold broccoli in.
Pour into baking dish.
Bake at 425° for 20 to 25 minutes, until bubbly.

title: asparagus parmigiana
directions: After removing the asparagus from the steamer, lay the stalks on a heated oblong serving dish.
Sprinkle with cheese and butter; place in a preheated 400° oven for 5 to 7 minutes.
Remove and serve.

title: chicken hot dish
directions: Cut up chicken and mix all ingredients together.
Place in
9 x
13-inch	pan.
Cover with foil and refrigerate overnight.
Bake with
foil
on for 1 1/2 hours at 325°.
Uncover and put crushed potato chips on top to garnish.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes more.

title: cheese and sausage balls
directions: Work into balls and bake for 20 minutes at 400°.

title: jazzed mashed potatoes
directions: Fix the mashed potatoes as you normally prepare them.
After mashing potatoes, mix the remaining ingredients and mix in well. Enjoy.

title: cheesy apples
directions: Drain apples. Set juice aside. Combine sugar, flour and melted butter with apple juice. Place apples in shallow baking dish that has been sprayed with cooking spray. Pour flour and sugar mixture over apples. Cube cheese and place on top of apple mixture. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: mashed potato pie
directions: Place oil in saucepan over low heat.
Add sirloin.
Stir in celery, peppers and onions.
Cook until tender.
Add garlic powder, seasoned salt, onion powder and dry mustard
and cook until tender, but not brown.

title: lime jello salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in boiling water. Add miniature marshmallows. When mixture has cooled, add cottage cheese, nuts and crushed pineapple. When mixture has thickened, fold in Cool Whip. Keep refrigerated.

title: teriyaki steak
directions: Combine all ingredients except meat together and heat in saucepan to boiling.
Score both sides of meat, 1/4 inch deep. Slash fat on edges.
Place meat in shallow dish.
Pour soy sauce mix over meat.
Cover with plastic and refrigerate at least 2 hours, turning 4 times.
Grill or broil 2 to 3 inches from heat, 7 to 8 minutes on each side.
Meat should be brown and have a crust on the outside and rare inside.
To serve, cut diagonally across grain into 1/4 inch slices.
Serves 8.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: Brown hamburger and Tater Tots.
In large casserole (9 x 13-inch) dish empty soup and 1/2 can of water or milk.
Drain corn and add to soup.
Grate cheese.
Layer hamburger on top of soup mix.
Top with half of cheese and Tater Tots.
Add remaining cheese.
Bake in 350° oven for 30 minutes.

title: coconut cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add one egg at a time, beating after each one.
Add flour, sifted 5 or 6 times with baking powder, alternately with milk.
Add vanilla.
Bake in 3 (9-inch) layers at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Cool and frost.

title: spanish rice
directions: Cook beef, onion and green pepper together and drain.
Add rice and juice.
Stir together; add salt and pepper (add salsa now if desired).
Put in crock-pot for 4 hours or cook in skillet for 10 to 15 minutes.
Let stand for 10 to 15 minutes before serving if cooked in skillet.
Serve.

title: almond bark cookies (unbaked)
directions: Melt almond bark (follow directions on package). Stir in peanut butter. Add pecans, marshmallows and Rice Krispies. Mix well but carefully. Cover pans with waxed paper. Drop by spoonfuls onto paper. Refrigerate to set. Store in the refrigerator. Sprinkle with colored sugar. Makes 53 cookies.

title: twenty four hour salad
directions: Two days ahead, drain pineapple, reserving 1/2 cup syrup.
In a saucepan, mix syrup with eggs, sugar, flour and salt.
Cook over low heat, stirring constantly, until very thick and smooth.
Stir in lemon juice.
Refrigerate until cool.
Fold in whipped cream. Add fruit and nuts.
Refrigerate 24 hours.
Serves 6.

title: boiled custard
directions: Mix all ingredients except milk in a heavy saucepan.
Heat on low.
Add milk gradually, cook on low heat until custard coats a metal spoon.
Cook by placing pan into bowl of ice water and stirring.
Chill.

title: poor man's spaghetti
directions: Boil spaghetti.
Drain.
Fry hamburg with onion, salt and pepper.
Drain grease.
Add meat to drained spaghetti, add the tomatoes and heat until warmed up.
If soupier sauce is wanted, add tomato juice.

title: pecan fingers
directions: Cream butter, blend in sugar, salt, vanilla and water. Add flour and pecans. Mix well. Chill if dough is soft. Shape into fingers- like ovals using level tsp. of dough. Place on ungreased cookie sheet and bake at 350° about 15 minutes. Roll in powdered sugar. Makes about 10 dozen.

title: buttermilk pancakes
directions: Mix together buttermilk, oil and eggs.
Add dry ingredients and stir just until moistened.
Pour onto hot griddle and cook until done.

title: layered taco spread
directions: In a 3-cup bowl, stir together the refried beans, taco sauce and several dashes of bottled hot pepper sauce, if desired.
Spread the refried bean mixture evenly on bottom and sides of rectangular server.
Sprinkle half of the shredded cheese over the bean layer.

title: strawberry-rhubarb custard pie
directions: Line pie plate.
Combine eggs and milk in large bowl; stir well.
Add sugar and flour, stirring well.
Gently fold in rhubarb and strawberries.
Pur filling mix into pastry shell.
Dot with margarine.
Top pie with 2nd pie crust, trimming off excess pastry.
Fold edges under and crimp.
Cut slits in top to allow steam to escape.
Bake at 400° for 1 hour.
Cover edges of pastry with strips of foil to prevent excessive browning after 30 minutes.
Cool on wire rack.

title: shrimp victoria
directions: In hot butter in large skillet, cook, stirring occasionally, shrimp and onion until shrimp are almost tender, about 5 minutes. Add mushrooms; cook, stirring occasionally, 5 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Stir in flour, salt and pepper, mixing well, then stir in sour cream.
Reheat very gently, do not boil.
Delicious served over rice or hot buttered toast.
Doesn't last, no leftovers. Serves about 4.

title: tuscan tomato soup
directions: Heat oil and butter in a heavy saucepan.
Cook carrots, celery and onions about 20 minutes or until tender.
Add tomatoes and continue cooking over moderate heat 25 to 30 minutes.
Stir in parsley and basil.
Season with salt and pepper.
Cook a minute or so longer and serve hot.

title: 1-2-3-4 cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add egg yolks and beat.
Add dry ingredients.
Alternate with milk.
Fold in stiffly beaten egg whites.
Bake in loaf pan at 350° for 1 hour.

title: grandma's potato dish
directions: Mix and heat oleo, soup, sour cream, onions and Velveeta.
Put potatoes in a casserole dish.
Top with the heated mixture and then with the crushed corn flakes and other 2 tablespoons oleo. Bake at 350°
for 45 minutes.

title: finn rye bread
directions: Mix rye flour, caraway seeds and buttermilk in a large bowl and let stand overnight.

title: pork chops and fried potatoes
directions: *Quantities are determined by number of servings needed.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli until done, drain well.
Add all ingredients except cracker crumbs.
Place in baking dish.
Put crumbs on top of casserole.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: punch
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour over ice.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Wash and drain broccoli flowerets.
Crisp in a plastic bag overnight in refrigerator.
When ready to serve, combine broccoli, sunflower seeds, raisins and onion.
Mix mayonnaise, sugar and vinegar together.
Toss with vegetable mixture.
Serve and enjoy.

title: meat sauce mix for pizza, chili, soup, etc.
directions: Melt shortening in a large skillet over medium heat.
Add onions, celery, garlic and carrots.
Saute until onions are golden.
Add ground beef.
Stir and cook until meat is browned. Add salt, pepper, Worcestershire sauce, ketchup and hot ketchup. Cover and simmer 20 minutes.
Drain off.
Cool.
Put into five 1 pint containers, leaving 1/2 inch space at top.
Cut through mixture with a knife several times to remove air.
Seal and label. Freeze.
Use within 3 months.

title: sour cream pound cake
directions: Cream the butter and sugar together. Add eggs, one at a time. Beat well after each egg. Cream well. Add the flour, one cup at a time. Beat well after each cup. Fold in the sour cream.
Grease and flour a tube pan.
Pour half of the batter in pan. Sprinkle chopped walnuts and sugar mixture over batter.
Pour remaining batter in pan. Top with rest of nut mixture.
Bake in a 325° oven for 1 1/2 hours.

title: nacho dip
directions: Brown hamburger and sausage. Crumble and drain off grease. Melt cheese in crock-pot. Mix all together. Serve with nacho chips.

title: meat balls in sour cream sauce
directions: Place meat balls in baking dish.
Cover generously with barbecue sauce and place in refrigerator overnight.
Place in oven and bake at 350° until meatballs are done.

title: pineapple pie
directions: Mix sugar, salt and cornstarch in saucepan.
Add pineapple and juice mix and bring to a boil.
Cook about 1 minute.
Stirring constantly.
Add to unbaked pie crust and top with crust.
Bake at 425° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Then invite your friend in.

title: barbecued meatballs and baked beans
directions: Peel and slice eggplant 1/2-inch or less.
Dip in flour, egg and crumbs.
Spray a cookie sheet with Pam.
Place on cookie sheet and bake at 350° for 10 minutes on each side.
Layer in casserole with sauce, Mozzarella cheese and grated Parmesan cheese.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix together and pour into pie shell.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes, then at 350° for 30 minutes.
Makes 2 (9-inch) pies.

title: zesty dressing
directions: In deep bowl, stir together all ingredients until well mixed. Cover and chill until ready to serve.

title: mini blintzes
directions: Cream first 3 ingredients until smooth.
Trim crusts from bread and roll each slice thin.
Spread with cheese mixture and fold in thirds.
Dip in melted butter and freeze on cookie sheets. When partially frozen, cut in half and bake in 400° oven for 10 to 15 minutes.
Serve with dish of strawberry preserves for dipping.
Can be made ahead and kept frozen.

title: homemade "cracker jacks"
directions: Mix together the popcorn and peanuts in a very large bowl or roast pan.
Keep this in warm 250° oven.
Melt butter in a heavy 2-quart saucepan. Stir in brown sugar, syrup and salt.
Bring to a rolling boil, stirring constantly.

Boil, without stirring, for 5 minutes. Remove from heat. Stir in baking soda and vanilla. Quickly pour over warm popcorn and peanut mixture while tossing until popcorn and nuts are well coated. Spread out in a shallow baking pan or cookie sheet.
Bake at 250° for 45 minutes. Stir about every 15 minutes.
Make sure every piece of popcorn has been moved around on the bottom. Remove from the oven. Turn out on aluminum foil to let cool. Store in tightly covered container. Makes 2 quarts.

title: blueberry muffins
directions: Cream together until fluffy the butter, sugar and eggs.
Then add the milk, flour, baking powder and salt.
Stir in by hand the blueberries.
Fill well greased muffin tins approximately 2/3 full.
Sprinkle with sugar.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Dissolve jello in hot water.
Add other ingredients and mix well.
Pour one-half mixture in mold.
Refrigerate.
Keep remainder out of refrigerator.
When first half is congealed, top with sour cream and cover with remainder of jello mixture. Refrigerate.

title: ricotta cake for a large crowd(makes 50 to 75 cakes)
directions: Grease and flour largest roasting pan.
Pour prepared yellow cake mix into pan.
Spread to cover entire pan.
This will be a thin layer.
With electric mixer, mix remaining ingredients.
Pour as evenly as possible over cake mix; do not mix.
Bake for 50 to 70 minutes at 350° in a preheated oven (middle rack).
Allow to cool thoroughly.
Cut into small squares; place into cupcake pans. Sprinkle with confectioners sugar, or top with desired canned pie filling.

title: baked round steak
directions: Line casserole dish with aluminum foil.
Place steak in pan. Sprinkle tenderizer on steak and let set for 30 minutes. Put onion
soup
mix
over
meat;
sprinkle on Worcestershire sauce, salt and pepper.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until tender.

title: mandarin orange fruit salad
directions: Combine all fruits and chill.
This makes a large fruit salad.

title: bubble soap recipe
directions: Combine ingredients.
Pour small amount into a paper cup. Place a straw in the cup and blow.
You may also use a wand to make bubbles.
Store in covered jar or container.

title: pepper steak
directions: Saute steak in oil until done.
Add water and beef bouillon and simmer, covered, for 1 hour.
Keep adding water and small amounts of bouillon if needed.
Add vegetables and cook until tender.
Remove 1/2 cup of liquid and stir flour in.
Pour flour mixture into meat and vegetable mixture to thicken.
Add more flour to desired thickness.
Serve over rice.

title: punch bowl cake
directions: Bake cake as directed on box.
In a large punch bowl, crumble half of the cake.

Mix 1 box of vanilla pudding; pour over cake. Spoon 1/2 can of pineapple over pudding, 1 can of cherry pie filling over pineapple and 1/2 carton of Cool Whip over cherries. Repeat this process again, then top with pecans.

title: oven fried zucchini
directions: Preheat oven to 475°.
Spray nonstick cookie sheet liberally. Combine bread crumbs, cheese, salt and pepper on sheet of waxed paper.
Set aside.
Quarter zucchini lengthwise, then cut each spear in halves or thirds.
Put these in plastic bag; add oil and water.
Close bag and shake so spears are coated.

title: baked chicken italiano
directions: Preheat oven to 350. Heat oil in large frying pan. Dip chicken in salad dressing, then in bread crumbs. Brown in oil. Transfer to shallow baking dish. Spoon marinara sauce over chicken. Top with sliced mozzarella, then chopped tomato. Sprinkle with herbs and a generous shake of Parmesan cheese. Bake 45 minutes. If tomatoes begin to burn, cover loosely with foil.

title: asparagus custard casserole
directions: Puree the chopped, cooked asparagus in blender.
Add eggs, cream, salt, nutmeg and melted butter to blender and mix thoroughly.
Add minced asparagus and pour into a 1-quart casserole.
Place casserole in pan of hot water and bake at 350° for about 30 minutes until firm in center.
Serves 4.

title: broccoli cornbread
directions: Melt oleo in pan.
Bake for 1 hour at 400°.

title: aunt ola's asparagus casserole
directions: Grease casserole dish with butter.
Mix all ingredients except potato chips.
Pour in casserole.
Crumble potato chips and sprinkle on top.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: chocolate mallow malt pie
directions: In top of double boiler combine marshmallows, chocolate pieces, milk and salt.
Cook over hot water, stirring occasionally, until marshmallows and chocolate are melted.
Remove from heat; cool until slightly thickened.
In small mixer bowl combine whipping cream, malted milk powder and vanilla.
Beat until very thick. Fold in chocolate-marshmallow mixture.
Spoon into baked pastry shell.
Sprinkle chopped pecans around edge of pie.
Chill at least 3 hours before serving.

title: orange pineapple cake
directions: Mix all ingredients well and bake at 350°.
Makes 2 layers. Cool cakes and split both layers.

title: poor man's dinner
directions: Brown steak in a little olive oil.
Slice as if you were going to stir-fry.
Salt and pepper.
Add onion,
garlic, tomatoes and A.1.
Simmer a little, then add meat to the cooked noodles and mix up.
Stir and simmer it until it is done to your taste.
Very good.

title: asparagus casserole
directions: Drain asparagus and place in bottom of dish.
Crush a layer of potato chips over asparagus.
Cover potato chips with a layer of grated cheese and spread one half can of mushroom soup over cheese.

title: impossible bacon, lettuce and tomato pie
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Grease a 10 x 1 1/2-inch pie plate. Layer bacon and cheese in plate.
Beat remaining ingredients except lettuce and tomatoes until smooth, 15 seconds in blender or 1 minute with hand mixer.
Pour into pie plate.
Bake until top is golden brown and knife inserted in center of pie comes out clean, about 30 to 35 minutes.
Cool 5 minutes.

title: potato salad
directions: Drain, cool and cut up potatoes. Add all ingredients and mix real good. It is best if let set in refrigerator over night.

title: country style ribs and kraut
directions: Brown ribs on all sides in skillet. Mix all ingredients with kraut with hands. Put in Dutch oven or roaster with lid. Put ribs on top and push down into kraut mixture Bake 2 hours at 325° basting twice. Add more stock if liquid gets low; don't let boil away.

title: baked chicken parmesan
directions: In a paper bag, place dry ingredients (garlic powder, paprika, thyme, Parmesan cheese, parsley and bread crumbs).
Coat chicken by shaking a few pieces at a time in the bag.
Oil a shallow roasting pan.
Pour in water and put in chicken pieces bone side down. Sprinkle chicken with oil and melted margarine.
Bake at 350°, uncovered, for 30 minutes.
Pour wine over chicken.
Lower oven to 325°.
Cover pan with foil.
Bake 15 minutes more.
Remove foil; raise oven to 350°.
Bake another 10 minutes.

title: tortilla roll-ups
directions: Mix softened cream cheese with the chopped cilantro, chilies, garlic powder and hot sauce.
Spread mixture on top of tortillas and roll them up.
Put into refrigerator for 30 minutes.
Remove and cut into pinwheel slices.
Serve with salsa for a great Mexican dip!

title: creamy seasoned turkey
directions: Combine all ingredients in double boiler.
Cover and cook over low heat until hot, about 25 minutes or more.
Add more milk, if needed.
Serve over toast, rice, noodles or patty shells.

title: meat balls and noodles
directions: Mix all ingredients except the soup and shape into 12 balls. Roll in 1 1/2 tablespoons flour. Brown.
Mix and add the soup and 2/3 cup water. Cover and simmer about 15 minutes. Serve over 3 cups hot cooked noodles.

title: homemade bologna
directions: Mix all ingredients together with your hands.
Divide meat into 2 portions and roll into 2 long rolls about the length of a regular size cookie sheet.
Put each roll tightly in foil and refrigerate for 12 hours.
Bake unrolled in aluminum foil for 50 minutes at 350°. Be sure to drain grease when you remove from oven. Slice into any size thickness portions you want.

title: marie gravier's forty-niner's mulligan
directions: Cut bacon and beef into cubes.
Fry together with crumbled sausage.
Remove most of fat.
Add chopped onions; fry until onions are clear.
Add garlic (minced).
Put in large kettle with water to cover and simmer until beef is tender.
Add hydrated mushrooms, potatoes (cut in chunks), chili powder, salt, pepper and shrimp.
Then add macaroni and more garlic, if desired.
Cook until well done.
Add more water if needed.

title: eugene's cheese biscuits
directions: Mix all dry ingredients.
Work in shortening and cheese with a pastry fork; stir in milk.
Drop by teaspoon onto ungreased baking sheet.
Bake at 400° for 12 or 15 minutes.
Use extra sharp cheese (sharp wine Cheddar).

title: carrot cake
directions: Cream together sugar, eggs and oil.
Add carrots and pineapple.
Mix well.
Add flour and spices.
Pour into 3 greased and floured pans.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: light chocolate cream pie
directions: Beat milk and egg together.
Combine 2/3 cup sugar, the cornstarch, cocoa and a pinch of salt. Gradually stir in milk mixture.
Cook over medium-low heat, stirring frequently until mixture comes to a boil, 10 to 12 minutes.
Boil, stirring 1 minute. Remove from heat and stir in vanilla.
Pour into cooled pie crust.
Refrigerate.
Spoon whipped topping over pie. Refrigerate.

title: nana's special crab dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Serve as a dip with potato chips, crackers, etc.
Serves approximately 16 to 20 people.

title: corn casserole
directions: Cook rice according to package directions. Add Velveeta while rice
is
hot to melt. Add other ingredients.
Mix well. Bake at 300° for 20 to 25 minutes, stirring thoroughly, once. Remove from oven. Top with shredded cheese.

title: impossible pie
directions: Grease a 10-inch pie plate.
Brown beef and onion; drain. Spread in dish.
Beat milk, eggs, baking mix, salt and pepper 1 minute with beater.
Pour over contents in plate.
Bake 25 minutes.
Top with tomatoes and cheese.
Bake 8 minutes.
Add favorite toppings:
mushrooms, peppers, etc.

title: greek style tomato salad
directions: About 2 1/2 hours before serving or early in day, place sliced tomatoes, Feta cheese, onion and olives in a 13 x 9-inch glass baking dish.
In a small bowl with fork, mix olive oil, vinegar, parsley, sugar, basil, salt and pepper.
Pour dressing over tomato mixture.
With rubber spatula, gently lift tomato slices to coat with dressing.
Cover baking dish and refrigerate at least 2 hours to blend flavors.

title: cranberry chicken
directions: Bake chicken for 30 minutes at 350°.
Mix cranberry sauce, apple, raisins, nuts and curry.
Spread sauce mixture evenly over chicken.
Bake 30 minutes.
Serve over couscous, rice or noodles.

title: lemon cake
directions: Combine jello and dry cake mix.
Add apricot nectar.
Add oil slowly then eggs one at a time until all are mixed well.
Beat with mixer about 4 minutes.
Bake in tube pan at 350° for 1 hour. When cake is done, allow to stand 3 or 4 minutes and turn out on cooling rack.
Glaze while hot.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix everything but 1/2 cup pecans.
Form in ball.
Roll in remaining pecans.

title: strawberry pie
