directions: Mix sugar, water and cornstarch and let come to a rolling boil.
(Stir constantly until thick.)
Remove from heat and stir in jello and strawberries.
Pour in 2 baked pie shells or graham cracker crusts.
Refrigerate until firm.
Top with whipped topping.

title: shoepeg salad
directions: Combine all vegetables in a large bowl; set aside.
In a saucepan, combine sugar, vinegar, oil, salt and pepper; bring to a boil.
Cool slightly and pour over vegetables.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.

title: french onion soup
directions: Slice onions.
Melt butter in large saucepan on high heat. Add onions and pepper to butter.
Saute until mixture is golden brown, stirring often.
Remove from heat.
Gradually add broth, stirring constantly.
Stir in water and bay leaf.
Return to high heat and bring to boil, stirring constantly.
Reduce to low heat. Cook uncovered 30 to 40 minutes.
Discard bay leaf.
Salt and pepper if desired.
Put in individual soup bowls.
Toast slices of French bread.
Float on top of soup.
Sprinkle grated cheese liberally on toast.
Broil in broiler until cheese melts.
(Be sure to use ovenproof bowls.)
Serves 4 to 6.

title: quickie baked beans
directions: Combine all ingredients, except bacon, in 1-quart glass casserole.
Top with bacon pieces.
Cover with glass lid or plastic wrap.
Microwave on Reheat for 12 to 14 minutes or until mixture bubbles.
Let stand, covered, for 3 minutes before serving.
Yields 4 servings.

title: happy cake
directions: No sifting.
Just put all ingredients in bowl and beat the dickens out of it.
Not necessary to grease pan.
Makes a very moist dark black chocolate cake.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: chicken and broccoli
directions: In large skillet over medium heat in 3 tablespoons margarine, cook chicken 10 to 15 minutes, or until browned on both sides. Remove chicken; keep warm.
In same skillet in remaining margarine, cook broccoli and carrots until carrots are tender.
In a small bowl, combine soup and milk; add to broccoli and carrots. Heat to boiling.
Add salt and pepper.
Return chicken to skillet; reduce heat to low and simmer 10 minutes or until chicken is fork-tender.
Makes 4.

title: beef stew casserole
directions: Mix beef stew, green beans, soup and 1/2 can of onions in casserole dish.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 30 minutes.
Top with remaining onions; return to oven for 5 minutes.

title: quick punch
directions: Remove rind from lemons, then squeeze lemons and set juice aside.
Combine lemon rind, water and sugar in a saucepan; boil 5 minutes.
Discard lemon rind.
Stir in lemon juice and remaining ingredients.
Chill.

title: bunny's cream cheese dessert
directions: Soften cream cheese.
Mix in (defrosted) Cool Whip.
Make pie crust by crushing vanilla wafers into coarse powder; mix together with butter.
Place in bottom of baking dish.
Optional:
Sprinkle slivered almonds on top.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes or until brown.
Cool crust.
Place cream cheese mixture over crust and top with can of cherry pie filling.
Enjoy.
It's very rich.
Need only small squares.

title: mexican potato skins
directions: Bake potatoes.
Cut into halves and scoop out insides.
Brush with butter and broil.
Sprinkle with chili powder, salt and onion. Broil 3 to 4-inches from heat for 8 minutes until edges are crispy. Remove and top with the rest of ingredinets.
Broil until cheese melts.
Top with sour cream and guacamole sauces.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: farm cookies
directions: In small bowl, combine flour, baking powder, baking soda and salt; stir to mix well.
Set aside.
In large bowl, beat butter. Add sugar; beat until fluffy.
Beat in eggs and vanilla.
Add flour mixture.
Beat until well combined.

title: grandmother hall's applesauce cake(good at christmastime; very old!)
directions: Sift cinnamon, cloves, nutmeg and salt into flour.
Cream sugar and butter; add applesauce with flour and spices.
Stir until well blended, then add soda, nuts and raisins and mix well. Bake in fluted pan for 1 hour or until a clean straw can be smooth after inserting into depth of cake.
Bake at 350°.

title: crab dip
directions: Top cream cheese with cocktail sauce, then top that with crab meat.
Dip with Sociables crackers.

title: pecan meringue pie
directions: Combine egg whites and vanilla.
Beat with mixer at medium speed to form soft peaks.
Add sugar gradually, beating to stiff peaks.
Add to crumb mixture.
Turn into greased and floured 8-inch dish.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.
Top with whipped cream.

title: cabbage rolls
directions: Place the vinegar and oil in bottom of pan or casserole.
Mix beef, rice, onion, soup, salt and pepper.
Form into oblong rolls, about 12 to 14 rolls.
Place 12 to 14 cabbage leaves in boiling water to soften.
Drain.
Wrap each leaf around meat.
Roll and place in dish; do not stack.
Can be a little crowded.
Fill tomato soup can with water and mix soup and water.
Pour over rolls.
Bake 1 1/2 to 2 hours.
Turn rolls after 1 hour.
Bake the last 20 minutes, uncovered, at 350°.

title: old fashioned salmon stew
directions: In large pot, put all ingredients together, except Carnation milk.
Cook over low heat for 1 hour.
Simmer another hour; take off burner.
Add the Carnation milk (do not dilute milk with water).
Stir; let simmer for 15 minutes.

title: pineapple-coconut cake frosting
directions: Stir together sugar and flour.
Add pineapple (including juice) and milk.
Cook over very low heat or in a double boiler.
This must be stirred constantly as it will stick very fast.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Cook macaroni as directed.
Mix salad oil, vinegar, minced onion, mayonnaise, salt and pepper. Set aside.
Add ham, cheese, eggs and peas to macaroni.
Add in salad oil mixture and combine well.
Chill at least 2 hours before serving.

title: turtle cake
directions: Mix cake as directed on box.
Add 1/3 cup evaporated milk and 1/2 cup margarine to batter.
Pour 1/2 batter into prepared 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Melt caramels and 1/3 cup evaporated milk.
Pour this over first layer of cake after baked.
Sprinkle chocolate chips and pecans on next.
Pour rest of batter over this.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: In greased, 9 x 13-inch pan, place 8 slices bread (no crust). Top with Velveeta cheese, ham, bacon or sausage and 8 slices of bread (no crust).
Combine eggs, milk, dry mustard and salt; spread over bread mixture.
Refrigerate overnight (covered).
Top with butter and corn flakes.
Bake 1 hour at 350° (uncovered).

title: pink punch
directions: Chill liquids. Mix all of the ingredients in a large punch bowl. Add spoonfuls of sherbet.

title: party punch
directions: Add sherbet to Sprite by spoonfuls.
Serves 12.

title: asparagus rolls
directions: Mix together Blue cheese, cream cheese and egg.
Remove crust on bread and roll out with a rolling pin until flat.
Spread cheese mixture on bread and add one asparagus spear.
Roll up and place on cookie sheet.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes.
Serve warm.

title: meatballs in tomato soup
directions: Form into meatballs and cook until done, turning every so often.
Mix 1 can tomato soup with 1/2 can water.
Pour over meatballs.
Cover and simmer for 15 to 20 minutes.
Use tomato gravy over potatoes, if you wish.
Soup may be doubled, if you like lots of gravy.

title: butter crunch pie crust
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Mix ingredients by hand.
Spread in an oblong cake pan.
Bake for 15 minutes.
Take from oven and stir. Save 3/4 cup for topping and press into pie pan to form crust. Use your choice of cream fillings.

title: jamaican red bean soup
directions: In a large soup pot, combine all ingredients except flour with an additional 4 cups of water. Bring to the boil; reduce heat and simmer, covered, for 25 to 30 minutes. In a cup, combine cornstarch with a bit of water until smooth. Stir into soup. Bring back to the boil and simmer for another 8 to 10 minutes. Makes 6 to 7 servings.

title: pancakes
directions: Mix together the flour, salt, soda and baking powder.
Mix together eggs, buttermilk and oil.
Mix flour mixture and egg mixture together until well blended.
Ladle batter onto hot griddle, 2 to 3 tablespoons at a time.
Turn when golden brown. Serve with warmed syrup and margarine.

title: prime (standing) rib roast with yorkshire pudding
directions: *The first 3 ribs are the best.
I use the first five.

title: pineapple cookies
directions: Combine all ingredients, mixing well.
Spoon onto cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: potato casserole
directions: Place thawed potatoes in buttered baking dish.
Salt and pepper top of potatoes.
Mix soup, cheese, sour cream and onion. Spread over top of potatoes.
Top with crushed cereal and drizzle melted butter over top.

title: surprise cake
directions: Spray a 13 x 9-inch baking pan with cooking spray.
Sprinkle marshmallows on bottom of pan.
Prepare cake mix as directed on box.
Take out enough batter for 6 cupcakes (bake separately). Pour remaining batter over marshmallows.
Combine cherry pie filling and dry gelatin; spread over batter.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: orange-pineapple salad
directions: Drain juice from pineapple and oranges.
Use juice and water to make 2 cups liquid.
Bring to boil; pour over jello and sugar. Add chopped cream cheese and marshmallows.
Cheese and marshmallows will melt.
When cool, add oranges and pineapple. Put in refrigerator until it begins to jell, then add whipped cream and pour into mold.
Makes approximately 12 servings.

title: grandpa's casserole
directions: Combine ingredients except 1/4 cup of Cheddar cheese and bread crumbs.
Put into 2-quart casserole dish.
Top with remaining cheese and bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes or until bubbly.

title: yellow banana punch
directions: Heat water and sugar until sugar is completely dissolved.
Mix other ingredients with sugar water.
Divide equally into 3 containers and freeze.
Remove from freezer about 3 hours ahead and let base get mushy.
Pour ginger ale over mushy base.
Serves 50 to 60.

title: bloody mary's
directions: Makes 2 drinks (10-ounce glass with ice).

title: easy fruit salad
directions: Drain liquid from fruit cocktail and orange slices into bowl. Add sugar to taste and stir until dissolved.
Add all fruit, except orange slices, and mix well.
Fold orange slices in gently. Chill.

title: black bean and chicken chili
directions: Saute chicken, red peppers, onions and garlic in oil in a Dutch oven about 5 minutes or until chicken is almost cooked.
Add chili powder, cumin and coriander; cook 3 minutes.
Stir in beans, tomatoes with their liquid and beer.
Bring to boil.

title: dump salad
directions: Dump it all into Jell-O and mix well.
Eat.

title: broccoli bake
directions: Mix all ingredients in a bowl.
Turn mixture into an oblong baking dish.
Bake 30 to 40 minutes at 350° uncovered.
If mixture seems runny, continue to bake until browned and firm.

title: pink lady salad
directions: Stir strawberry Jell-O into cottage cheese.
Add Cool Whip, pineapple, coconut and pecans.
Chill before serving.

title: shipwreck
directions: Drain and crumble bacon.
Saute onion in beef drippings, about 5 minutes.
Mix catsup and sugar.
Stir catsup mix into beef mixture.
Stir in pork and beans and all but 2 tablespoons of bacon.
Put in baking dish.
Top with bacon.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: saco ultimate chocolate chunk cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In a small bowl combine flour, soda and salt.
Set aside.
In large bowl combine butter, shortening, sugars and vanilla.
Beat until creamy.
Beat in egg.
Gradually add flour mixture and mix well.
Drop by teaspoonful on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes.
Cool on cookie sheet 2 minutes, then on rack.
Makes 3 to 4 dozen.

title: quick spaghetti sauce
directions: Combine ingredients in saucepan; bring to a boil.
Reduce heat; simmer 5 minutes.
Serve over pasta; top with grated cheese. Recipe makes 2 1/2 cups.

title: christmas cookie icing
directions: Sift powdered sugar and cream of tartar in bowl.
Add egg white and vanilla.
Beat with mixer until glossy.
Add colors.

title: potato pancakes
directions: Combine all ingredients, except oil, in a bowl and mix well. Heat oil in skillet.
Pour 1/2 potato mixture into skillet and cook over medium heat until bottom is browned.
Turn and brown other side.
Repeat with remaining mixture.

title: lush
directions: Mix butter, pecans and flour. Place mix in bottom of pan (13 x 9). Bake at 350° for 15 minutes. Let cool. Mix sugar and cream cheese and spread over cooled crust. Mix pudding as directed; spread over cream cheese mixture. Spread Cool Whip over pudding and refrigerate.

title: easy chicken bake
directions: Mix all ingredients together and place in a baking dish.
Bake at 325° to 350° until chicken is done.
No need to add water. Serve over cooked rice or potatoes.

title: key lime pie
directions: Beat the egg yolks with an electric mixer. Add the milk. Combine and blend in the lime juice.
Blend well.
Pour into crust.
Bake at 350° for 5 minutes in preheated oven.
Cool. Serve with Cool Whip.

title: german chocolate muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 400°. Grease or line 12 jumbo muffin or 24 regular muffin cups. Prepare cake mix and combine nuts, coconut and sugar in small bowl. Spoon batter into cups, filling half full. Sprinkle topping evenly over batter. Bake 20 to 25 minutes for jumbo or 15 to 20 minutes for regular. Cool in pan on wire rack 5 minutes. Remove and cool on rack 10 more minutes. Serve warm or cool completely.

title: lemon jello salad
directions: Partly set the first 3 ingredients.
Add the next 3 ingredients; let set until firm.
Make the sauce (like a white sauce).

title: apricot coffee cake
directions: Cream shortening and sugar; add egg and vanilla.
Sift dry ingredients; add alternately to creamed mixture with yogurt.
Mix well; add apricots.
Pour into greased 9-inch tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.
Remove from pan; dust with powdered sugar.

title: stove top pumpkin pie
directions: In saucepan, combine sugar, cornstarch and salt.
Gradually stir in milk and pumpkin.
Cook and stir until thickened.
Remove from heat; take out small amount of hot mixture and stir into beaten egg yolks.
Return to hot mixture and cook 2 minutes longer.
Remove from heat and stir in margarine and flavoring. Cool to room temperature; pour into pie shell.
Top with meringue.

title: banana split snack cake
directions: In a mixing bowl, cream butter and sugar.
Beat in egg, banana and vanilla.
Combine flour, baking powder and salt.
Stir into creamed mixture.
Add walnuts.
Spread evenly into a greased 13 x 9 x 2 inch pan.
Bake at 350 degrees for 20 minutes. Sprinkle with marshmallows, chocolate chips, and cherries.
Bake 10 minutes.
Cool on a wire rack.
Cut into squares.
Makes 24 - 30 bars.

title: easy corn pudding
directions: Bake at 350° to 375°.

title: squash soup
directions: Saute garlic and onion in oil and butter until transparent. Add squash and chicken stock.
Simmer until squash is tender. Transfer in batches to blender, adding a little milk to each batch.
Blend until smooth.
Stir in salt, pepper and onion. Should be thick.
Garnish with parsley or sliced squash.

title: southern pecan pie
directions: Mix filling ingredients together.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake 40 minutes in 350°
oven or until filling is set.

title: microwave english muffin bread
directions: Combine 3 cups flour, yeast, sugar, salt and soda.
Heat liquids (120° to 130°).
Add to dry ingredients.
Beat well.
Stir in rest of flour to make a stiff batter.
Spoon into 2 loaf pans that are greased and sprinkled with cornmeal.
Let rise in warm place 45 minutes.
Microwave on High 13 minutes.
Allow to set in pans 5 minutes.
Toast when ready to use.

title: marengo chicken
directions: Dredge the chicken in the flour seasoned with salt and pepper. Saute the chicken in three tablespoons butter until tender. Remove from frypan and keep warm.
Using the same pan, make a sauce with the flour, butter and chicken stock.
Stir until thick and smooth.
Add mushrooms, tomatoes, olives and white wine. Simmer for about ten minutes.
Pour the sauce over the chicken and serve with hot noodles.
Serves four.

title: yam or sweet potato bread
directions: *Use 2 good size yams that have been cooked and peeled or 16 ounce can whole yams, drained.

title: marinated potato and mushroom salad
directions: In shallow baking dish, combine potatoes, mushrooms, celery and onions.
In 1 pint jar with tight fitting lid, combine remaining ingredients, except pepper; shake well and pour over potato mixture; mix well.
Cover; chill 3 to 4 hours to blend flavors.
Serve with pepper, if desired.
Refrigerate leftovers. Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: wolf burgers
directions: *If wolf meat is not available, use ground round beef.

title: corn-pone casserole
directions: In 4-quart saucepan, over high heat, cook beef and onions until meat is browned, stirring occasionally.
Stir in chili powder.
Cook 1 minute.
Stir in tomatoes with liquid, sugar, salt and pepper.
Over high heat, cook to boiling.
Reduce heat to low. Cover and simmer 30 minutes, stirring often.
Stir in beans. Spoon mixture into 12 x 8-inch baking dish.
Preheat oven to 400°. Prepare corn muffin mix batter according to package directions. With a spoon, spread corn muffin mix over top.
Bake for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: hershey's chocolate cake
directions: Mix well all ingredients and bake at 350° for about 15 to 20 minutes.

title: apple dumplings
directions: Make a baking powder biscuit dough, roll out one-fourth inch thick.

Have chopped apples or peaches that cook well, sprinkle on dough, roll up tight, put in baking pan that has in it half cup melted butter, two cups granulated sugar, two cups boiling water. Bake in a moderately hot oven two hours.
One and a half cups flour for dough, one good pint fruit will serve six people.

title: crab melt
directions: Combine butter, lemon juice, Worcestershire sauce and garlic salt and mix well.
Fold in grated cheese and flaked crabmeat.
Add sliced olives if desired.

title: mom's pot pie
directions: Roll dough very thin and cut in strips.
Pull the strips thin while adding to broth.

title: supper in a skillet
directions: Cook beef, onion and celery in oil until onion is soft.
Add other ingredients except cheese and parsley and simmer 20 to 25 minutes.
Just before serving, fold in American and Parmesan cheese and sprinkle with parsley.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: bagels
directions: Scald milk, butter 1 tbsp sugar and salt together and let cool enough so as to not kill the yeast. Add dry yeast and mix well.

title: apple coffeecake
directions: Combine the 5 tablespoons of sugar with the cinnamon.
Put the apples into the mix.
Sift the flour, remaining sugar (2 cups), baking powder and salt into a bowl.
Make a well in the center and pour in the oil, eggs, orange juice and vanilla.
Beat with a wooden spoon until well blended.
Pour in one-third of the batter; ring with one-half of the apples, then one-third of the batter, then apples and top with remaining batter.
Bake for one and one-quarter hours at 375°.
Cool in the pan.

title: mama's chicken pot pie
directions: Boil and cool chicken.
Remove from bones and skin.
Cube potatoes and slice carrots (cook until tender); drain.
Place chicken in a 9 x 13-inch dish.
Add chicken soup, broth, drained garden peas, potatoes and carrots.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.

title: aunt hattie's hermits
directions: Blend sugar, eggs, butter and milk.
Sift flour, soda, salt and spices.
Blend with egg mixture.
Bake at 350° about 8 to 10 minutes.

title: cheese straws
directions: Cream butter and cheese with hands until smooth, then work in dry ingredients until a firm dough is made.
Run through cookie press.
Bake at 375° until light brown.

title: old witch's magic nut cake
directions: Beat together the eggs, pumpkin, oil and water.
Add the remaining ingredients.
Pour batter in 2 buttered loaf pans. Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes or until a straw from a witch's broom comes out clean.

title: chicken broccoli casserole
directions: Spray a 13 x 9-inch pan with Pam and put chicken in bottom. Next, layer drained broccoli on chicken.
Salt and pepper.
In small saucepan, combine soup, Velveeta, chicken broth, sour cream and fresh mushrooms.
Heat until cheese is melted.
Pour over broccoli.
Crush cracker crumbs and add melted margarine. Sprinkle on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: strawberry angel food delight
directions: Mix together, bring to a boil and stir constantly the pineapple, sugar, lemon juice and jello.
Cool slightly; add strawberries.
Let slightly congeal and fold in whipped cream. Cover bottom of 13-inch Pyrex pan with broken pieces of angel food cake.
Pour mixture over cake.
Cut into squares and serve with whipped cream on top.

title: golden punch
directions: Mix all ingredients together adding ginger ale at last minute.

title: aunt cella's chicken breasts in white wine
directions: Season flour with salt and pepper.
Dredge chicken in flour. In a frying pan, saute chicken in melted butter until lightly brown on both sides.
Add wine so it almost covers chicken.
Cover and cook over low flame until tender, approximately 20 minutes. The wine and flour will have thickened into a light sauce.

title: texas sheet cake
directions: In a 2-quart pan, put oleo, water and cocoa.
Bring to a boil. Add flour, sugar and vanilla.
Put buttermilk, eggs and soda in separate bowl.
Beat well and add to cocoa mixture.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch pan and bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: salmon puffs
directions: Combine eggs, milk and soup.
Blend in remaining ingredients. Place in buttered casserole.
Bake for 45 to 50 minutes at 375°.

title: favorite banana pudding
directions: In a large bowl, combine sweetened condensed milk and water; add pudding mix and beat well.
Chill 5 minutes.
Fold in whipped topping.
Layer pudding mixture, vanilla wafers and bananas in a serving dish, beginning and ending with pudding mixture.
Cover; chill.
Garnish with cookies, bananas or whipped topping, if desired.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: fresh vegetable crisp
directions: Cut vegetables in pieces, using amount of each you desire.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Saute onion and celery in 3/4 stick of oleo; add soups, rice and broccoli.
Put in greased casserole dish and top with Cheez Whiz.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes or until rice is cooked.
This makes a large casserole.

title: baked fish
directions: Place each fillet on aluminum foil square about 12 x 12-inch. Squeeze few drops of lemon juice on fish. Add pepper and other desired seasonings. Butter pat (optional).
Fold foil so no juice leaks out.
Place each foil wrapped fillet on baking sheet. Bake for 1/2 hour at 350°.

title: barbecued meat balls
directions: Mix ground meat, 1/2 cup milk and 2 slices of bread.
Add to meat 1/2 teaspoon soy sauce, 1/4 teaspoon garlic salt; mix well. Shape into small balls.
Place in casserole dish.
Cover in barbecue sauce.
Cook for 45 minutes at 375°.

title: pina colada punch
directions: Mix together; then divide equally in 3 portions and freeze. When ready to serve, add 1 (2 liter) bottle of Sprite or 7-Up to each portion; stir.

title: apple muffins
directions: Sift dry ingredients.
Combine egg, milk and shortening.
Make well in dry ingredients.
Add liquid all at once; stir until mixed.
Add apples.
Fill greased muffin pans 2/3 full.
Bake at 400° for 25 minutes.
Makes 12.

title: 10 cup cookies
directions: Cream butter, peanut butter, sugar and eggs.
Add all ingredients with soda, baking powder and flour last.
Drop on cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: fudge
directions: Mix sugar, milk and margarine in heavy saucepan. Bring to a boil and cook 5 min., stirring constantly. remove from heat, stir in vanilla, chocolate chips, marshmallow cream and pecans. Spread in cake pan. Let set over night. Cut into squares.

title: silver and gold tea squares
directions: Combine shortening, salt, vanilla and lemon extract. Add sugar gradually and cream until light.
Add beaten egg yolks.
Sift flour and baking powder and add alternately with milk.
Spread batter in greased wax paper lined 9 x 12-inch pan.

title: cinnamon rolls
directions: In large bowl, put water and sprinkle with yeast.
Add 1 teaspoon sugar.
Stir until dissolved and let stand 5 minutes.
By electric mixer, beat in cake mix, egg, oil, salt and 1 cup flour. Stir in rest of flour by hand.
It will be sticky.
Cover and let rise until double.
Stir down and let rise again.
Stir down and divide in half.
Roll out on a lightly floured surface until about 12 x 18-inches.
Brush with 1/2 of the butter and sprinkle with sugar and cinnamon mixture.
Roll up and slice.
Place cut side down on a greased cookie sheet.
Repeat with second half.
Cover and let rise until double.
Bake in a 350° oven until light brown (20 minutes).

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients.
Brown hamburger and onion.
Place cheese over hamburger, onion and jalapenos.
Pour 1/2 meal mixture into deep skillet.
Then put hamburger mixture on top of meal mixture.
Layer cheese on top.
Pour the rest of meal mixture into skillet.
Bake at 375° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: broccoli dip
directions: Cook broccoli until tender and then press out all excess moisture.
In a large mixing bowl, combine sour cream, mayonnaise, lemon juice and salt.
Mix in green onions, parsley, chopped eggs and broccoli.
Chill several hours and garnish with fresh parsley. Serve with chips, crackers or sliced French bread (baguettes).

title: potato croquettes
directions: Mix and beat all ingredients together.
Shape into croquettes. Dip in slightly beaten egg yolks and then crumbs.
Fry until brown.
Drain and serve when hot.

title: buttermilk cake
directions: Cream the sugar and Crisco. Add eggs, one at a time.
Beat well. Add flour and alternate with buttermilk. Add lemon extract. Bake at 350° for 1
hour.
Test with straw at 50 minutes.

title: switchel(basic)
directions: Vary amount to your taste!

title: stu's cheese ball
directions: Soften cream cheese and mix with onion, salt, Blue cheese and milk.
Form into a ball and refrigerate for 1 to 2 hours.
Roll in chopped nuts.
Serve with crackers.

title: banana nut cake
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Beat thoroughly until smooth, about 5 minutes.
Turn into two greased and floured 9-inch cake pans or use a 9 x 12-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Saute onions and celery in margarine.
Cook spaghetti and drain.
Mix all ingredients together and spread over spaghetti in casserole.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: pineapple squares
directions: Place butter or margarine in bowl and melt in microwave, or soften at room temperature.
Cream together the butter and sugar with an electric mixer for 2 minutes on high speed.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each one.
Add dry ingredients (except powdered sugar) and mix.
Drain pineapple and add to the ingredients and stir with a spoon until blended.
Pour batter into 9 x 13-inch pan, greased with shortening, and bake 30 to 35 minutes at 350°.
Cool and cut into 24 bars.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: texas chili
directions: In skillet brown meat.
Drain.
Turn beef, simmer.
Add all remaining ingredients and stir to blend.
Cover and cook 7 to 9 hours.
Skim excess fat.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: pork chop-biscuit casserole
directions: * Can be omitted.

title: cauliflower chowder
directions: In a large saucepan, combine cauliflower and 1/2 cup of water. Cover and cook about 5 minutes or until tender; do not drain. Cut up large pieces.
Mash all of the cauliflower slightly.
Stir in the condensed potato soup or green pea soup.
Stir in milk and Swiss cheese.
Cook and stir until cheese is melted and soup is heated through.
Makes 6 servings.

title: strawberry cheese pie
directions: Beat cream cheese until smooth, gradually beat in sugar. Blend in sour cream, lemon juice and vanilla.
Fold in whipped topping, blending well.
Spoon 1/4 of the mixture into pie shell. Arrange whole strawberries on cheese mixture.
Carefully spoon remaining cheese mixture over berries.
Chill at least 4 hours.

title: curried pumpkin soup
directions: Melt butter in 3-quart saucepan over medium-high heat.
Add onion and saute until translucent, about 5 minutes.
Mix in flour and curry powder and cook until bubbly, about 2 minutes.
Remove from heat and gradually stir in broth.
Add pumpkin, brown sugar, salt, pepper and nutmeg.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until thickened.
Blend in milk and continue cooking until warmed through; do not boil.
Ladle into bowls.
Sprinkle with chives or parsley.
Garnish with yogurt.
Serve immediately.

title: curry dip
directions: Mix ingredients.
Serve with carrots, cauliflower, celery, sliced cucumber, zucchini or any raw vegetables that you like.

title: pressed chicken
directions: Heat broth; dissolve gelatin, then cool.
Add all other ingredients.
Mold in refrigerator.
Can be made a day or two ahead.

title: hot rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water and add sugar.
Beat egg, salt and honey together, add yeast and flour; mix.
Turn out onto floured board, knead well.
Place into well-greased bowl, let rise in a warm place until doubled in size.
Then roll dough out onto floured board; cut into rolls.
Place on greased cookie sheet. Let rise 1 hour.
Bake at 400° until golden brown.

title: homestyle mashed potatoes
directions: In a 4-quart pan, cover peeled, diced potatoes and chopped onions with water.
Cook until potatoes are done (approximately 20 minutes).
Drain water thoroughly.
Add butter or oleo, sour cream and shredded cheese.
Cover and, when softened, blend with potatoes.
Add milk, if necessary, to reduce stiffness.
Add green peas and salt and pepper to taste.
Place in buttered 8 x 8 x 1 1/2-inch baking dish.
Garnish with paprika and 6 to 8 dollops of butter or oleo.
Bake in a preheated 350° oven for 20 minutes.

title: herbs, pasta and poultry
directions: Cook pasta according to package directions.
Drain.
In a large skillet, melt margarine.
Add meat, carrots and seasonings. Cook until thoroughly heated.
Combine meat mixture with hot pasta. Blend well.
Serves 4.

title: cinnamon coffee cake
directions: Mix flour, sugar and cinnamon.
Cut in 1/4 cup butter until crumbly.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Use 8-inch square pan, greased.

title: meat loaf
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: layered taco dip
directions: In skillet, brown meat; drain fat.
Add chillies.
In small bowl, combine sour cream and taco seasoning.
In 8-inch spring-form pan or on large plate, spread beans.
Top with meat mixture, sour cream and avocado dip.
Cover.
Chill.
Garnish and serve with tortilla chips.

title: chicken barbecue sauce
directions: Mix well.
Also stores well in refrigerator.

title: old fashioned apple stack cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs and molasses.
Mix well. Add soda to buttermilk.
Mix dry ingredients together; add alternately with milk
to batter.
Bake 1/2-inch layers in 9-inch round pan at 350° for 12 minutes.
Spread filling between layers and on top of cake.

title: meatball stroganoff
directions: Combine beef, bread crumbs, onion, Worcestershire sauce, egg, salt and pepper.
Shape into small balls.
Brown in skillet in margarine.
Remove meatballs from skillet.
Add soup and sour cream to skillet and stir.
When it is hot, add meatballs to sauce.
Simmer for 15 minutes.
Serve over hot cooked noodles.

title: chicken dinner
directions: Heat oven to 350°F.
Shake flour in oven bag: place in 13x9x2 inch baking pan.
Add onion soup mix and water to oven bag, blend in flour.
Add carrots, potatoes, and green pepper to onion bag. Turn oven bag to coat ingredients with sauce.
Sprinkle chicken with seasonings. Arrange chicken and vegetables in an even layer in oven bag.
Close bag.
Cut six 1/2 inch slits in top of bag. Bake 55-60 minutes until chicken is tender.

title: cream cheese cake
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Chill until slightly thickened.
Mix cracker crumbs and margarine together, then pack in the bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: caramel candy bars
directions: Heat caramels and milk in 2-quart casserole on Medium in microwave until smooth. Stir often. Mix flour, oats, brown sugar, soda, salt and egg. Cut in butter with pastry blender until crumbly. Press half of mixture in 9 x 13-inch greased pan. Sprinkle with chocolate chips and nuts. Drizzle with caramel mixture. Sprinkle remaining crumbly mixture over top. Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes or until golden brown.

title: pecan tassies
directions: Mix cream cheese, oleo and flour to make crust.
Place in small cupcake pan.
Mix remaining ingredients and dip into each crust.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: delicious apple cake
directions: Sift the flour, sugar, cinnamon, allspice, soda, salt and cloves all together and then add the oil and eggs.
Mix well, then add the apples and nuts.
Bake in loaf pan 1 hour at 350°.
Mix with hands. No icing.

title: easy pound cake
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Bake in greased and floured 10-inch mold pan at 350° for 1 hour.

title: microwave vichyssoise
directions: In a deep 2 1/2 to 3-quart casserole, melt butter on full power 30 seconds.
Add leeks and onion.
Heat, uncovered, on full power 3 minutes.
Add diced potatoes and chicken broth to butter-leek mixture.
Heat, covered, on full power 15 to 18 minutes or until potatoes are very tender.
Press mixture through a sieve or electric blender until smooth.
Return mixture to casserole and gradually stir in cream.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Heat, covered, on roast 6 minutes or until soup is very hot.

title: butterscotch crunches
directions: Melt butterscotch morsels over hot water (not boiling). Remove from heat.
Stir in chow mein noodles and salted peanuts. Drop by teaspoon onto wax paper.

title: hot spiced tomato juice
directions: Simmer 10 minutes, covered.
Cool slightly. Add 2 tablespoons lemon juice.
Reheat.

title: goo
directions: Pour glue and starch into a container.	Let set about five minutes to allow the glue to absorb the starch.
Take out and knead.
This will take a while, and will be messy, but well worth it in the end.
If it is sticky, add starch, a little at a time. If the starch settles on top, add glue.
When it is the right consistency, add food coloring.
Store in an airtight container in the refrigerator.
Will last for months.

title: scottish oat scones
directions: Add
buttermilk
and
egg
to combined dry ingredients. Mix just
until
dry ingredients are moistened.
Stir in raisins. Shape
dough
to form ball.
Pat out on lightly floured surface to form 8-inch circle.
Cut into 8 to 12 wedges.
Bake on
greased cookie sheet in preheated hot oven (425°) 12 to 15 minutes	or until light golden brown.
Serve warm at breakfast or
brunch with butter, preserves or honey, as desired.
Makes 8 to 12 scones.

title: winter squash, raisin and pine nut lasagna
directions: Place flour in a small saucepan. Gradually whisk in milk and garlic. Warm over low heat, stirring constantly, until sauce simmers and is thickened, about 3 minutes. Remove from heat and stir in cheese, salt and pepper. Spread 1/4 cup cheese sauce over bottom of baking dish and cover with 3 lasagna noodles. Top with 1/3 of squash, 1/2 cup cheese sauce, 1/2 cup Mozzarella cheese and 1/4 cup raisins. Cover with 3 more noodles and spread 1/3 of remaining squash, 1/2 cup cheese sauce and 1/4 cup raisins. Cover with 3 more lasagna noodles and top with remaining squash and raisins. Cover with last 3 noodles, pressing down firmly. Top with remaining cheese sauce and sprinkle with pine nuts and remaining Mozzarella cheese. Bake about 30 minutes in a 350° oven until it bubbles around the edges and is brown on top.

title: rum pound cake
directions: Cream sugar, butter and Crisco. Add eggs; mix well. Add flour, 1 cup at a time, alternating with milk and rum. Add vanilla. Grease tube pan and line bottom with wax paper. Put 1 cup ground nuts in before adding batter. Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: rice tamale pie
directions: Trim off all fat from lean beef flank steak or brisket.
Cut lengthwise with grain into long thin strips, 1/4-inch thick. Combine 1/2 cup soy sauce with 1/4 teaspoon each garlic salt and lemon pepper.
Pour over strips and toss until well coated.
Place wire rack on a baking sheet.
Arrange strips on rack to touch, but not overlap.
Bake in a very slow oven (150° to 175°) overnight, 10 to 12 hours.
Store finished jerky at room temperature in an airtight container.
If all fat has been removed, beef jerky will keep indefinitely.

title: low-fat peanut butter cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a large bowl, combine all ingredients; mix well.
Shape into 3/4-inch balls, using 1 teaspoon dough per ball.
Place 2 inches apart on baking sheet. Flatten with fork in crisscross pattern.
Bake 12 to 15 minutes or until lightly browned.
Store in refrigerator.
Serves 24 (2 cookies per serving).
Each serving contains 86 calories, 2.64 g protein, 5 g fat, 0 mg chol. and 37 g sodium.

title: cheesy potatoes
directions: Thaw hash browns, then mix all ingredients, except potato chips, into a 13 x 9-inch pan. Top with potato chips. Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: chinese chicken casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients except corn flakes, almonds and butter.
Mix and pour into 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Combine corn flakes, slivered almonds and butter in pot and cook until butter melts and coats well.
Pour over as topping and cook at 350° until golden brown, approximately 30 to 40 minutes.

title: bolanglang(vegetables with fish)
directions: Scale and clean bangus; slice into 4 to 6 pieces.
Sprinkle with salt and fry in hot oil until brown on all sides.
Set aside.

title: almond sauce
directions: Melt the butter and stir in the lemon juice.
Add almonds and parsley and cook until the almonds are golden.
Do not allow the butter to brown.
Season to taste with salt and pepper.

title: pumpkin cupcakes
directions: Combine
dry ingredients.
Beat butter with sugar;
add eggs and
pumpkin.
Then add dry ingredients alternately with milk. Bake at 375° for 25 minutes.
Makes 2 dozen cupcakes or one cake.

title: weight watchers soup
directions: Cook first 5 ingredients until vegetables are nearly done. Add remaining ingredients and cook until done.
When soup is done, if you feel it is too thin, put 3 cups of it in blender and puree; return to soup.
This thickens it a bit.

title: spanish rice
directions: Heat oil.
Brown ground beef.
Add rest of ingredients.
Let boil for 3 minutes, then simmer, covered for 25 minutes.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli 5 minutes.
Drain well.
Combine other ingredients except cracker crumbs to make sauce.
Combine with broccoli.
Pour into greased casserole.
Sprinkle top (amount depends on individual taste) with cracker crumbs.
Bake in a 400° oven for about 20 minutes.
(This may be refrigerated or frozen before baking.)
Serves 8.

title: whoopie pies
directions: Cream sugar and shortening; add egg yolks, then add milk. Mix well.
Add remaining ingredients.
Drop on ungreased cookie sheet and bake for about 20 minutes in 350° oven.

title: orange dream cheesecake(low carb)
directions: Bring water to boil; remove from stove. Add jello and mix well. Set aside to cool for 10 minutes.

title: mini rye pizzas
directions: Mix listed ingredients together and spread on cocktail rye bread.
Place 1 tablespoon on each slice of bread.
Spread evenly. Spread slices on a flat sheet pan.
Freeze.
Bag for freezer.
To serve, remove as many as needed.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.
Serve warm.

title: date pudding
directions: Blend all the ingredients.
Pour into a buttered baking dish and bake 30 minutes in a slow oven.

title: fried cabbage
directions: In a large iron skillet, put oil and bay leaves. When oil is hot, add washed and chopped cabbage and salt and pepper to taste. When cabbage is almost done, add chopped onion. Turn off heat and let sit for a few minutes before serving.

title: beaver stew
directions: Cut beaver into serving size pieces.
Dredge in salt and peppered flour and brown in hot oil in a stew pot.
Add bay leaves, garlic powder, tomatoes and some water.
Cover and cook until meat is nearly done.
Add vegetables and cook further until carrots are tender.
Add cabbage and garlic; cook about 10 minutes longer.
The stew may be thickened by adding a flour and water paste.

title: gourmet rice
directions: Combine all ingredients in a large Dutch oven; mix well. Bring mixture to a boil; reduce heat to simmer.
Cover; simmer for 30 minutes, or until rice is tender.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: corn bread salad
directions: Bake corn bread mix as directed on package.
Cool and crumble. Add green pepper, tomatoes, onion, beans and ham.
Toss (do not stir) with mayonnaise.
Top with cheese.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix thoroughly shortening, peanut butter, sugar, brown sugar and egg.
Sift together and stir in flour, baking powder, soda and salt.
Chill dough.
Roll into balls size of large walnuts.
Place 3 inches apart on lightly greased baking sheet.
Flatten with fork dipped in flour.
Crisscross.
Bake until set, but not hard.
Bake at 375° (quick moderate oven).
Bake for 10 to 12 minutes.
Amount: about 3 dozen 2 1/2 inch cookies.

title: salmon steaks with mustard sauce
directions: Dip steaks in milk.
Remove and dredge on both sides in flour seasoned with salt and pepper.
Shake off excess.
Heat oil in heavy skillet until quite hot.
Add steaks and cook on one side until nicely browned, about 5 minutes.
Turn and continue cooking, basting often with the hot oil about 5 minutes.
Serve with mustard sauce.
Pour hot mustard sauce onto center of hot serving dish.
Arrange steaks over sauce and dot center of each with teaspoon of chopped dill or parsley.
Yields 4 servings.

title: microwave toffee candy
directions: Boil the sugar and margarine 8 minutes in microwave.
Pour onto sheet pan covered with foil. Sprinkle chips over cooked mixture.
Let melt before spreading. Sprinkle with nuts.
When cool, break into pieces.

title: mexican layered dip
directions: Arrange beans in a flat serving plate to form the first layer. Smooth guacamole dip on top to form second layer.
Combine sour cream, mayonnaise and taco seasoning to make third layer.
Use green chilies for fourth layer.
Mix green onions, tomatoes and black olives for the fifth layer.
Top with cheese.
Serve with chips.

title: holiday strata(breakfast or brunch)
directions: Arrange bread, overlapping rows in bottom of 3-quart oblong baking dish.
Sprinkle with ham, cheese, peppers and onions.
Beat eggs in large bowl.
Beat in milk, mustard, pepper and paprika. Pour egg mixture over ingredients in baking dish.
Cover; refrigerate at least 1 hour or overnight.
Heat oven to 350° and bake for 40 to 45 minutes, until a knife inserted comes out clean. Remove from oven; let stand 5 to 10 minutes.

title: microwave meatballs
directions: Combine egg, ketchup, Worcestershire sauce, bread crumbs, parsley and oregano.
Let stand about 10 minutes.
Mix with onion, ground chuck, salt and pepper.
Form into small balls about 3/4-inch in diameter.
Place in a shallow glass and cook on High for 3 1/2 to 4 minutes.
Turn meatballs over and cook 3 minutes. Remove and drain off grease.
Add a can of tomato sauce over meatballs and cook 2 minutes.
Let stand in microwave about 5 minutes.

title: quick barbecue beef bake
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Cook ground meat and 1/2 cup of the onion in skillet until beef is brown; drain.
Stir in barbecue sauce. Spoon into ungreased 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Stir baking mix, milk and eggs until blended; pour over beef mixture.
Sprinkle with remaining onion.
Bake for 25 to 30 minutes, or until crust is lightly browned.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Mix hash browns, soup, sour cream, onion and 1/2 cup of shredded cheese in a large bowl. Pour mixture into casserole dish. Sprinkle remaining cheese over the mixture. Cover with corn flakes. Pour melted butter over corn flakes. Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: refrigerator slaw
directions: Layer cabbage and onions in a bowl. Bring other ingredients to a boil and pour over cabbage. Cover and refrigerate 24 hours, at least.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cream shortening and sugar together, then add bananas, eggs and vanilla.
Mix well.
Blend flour, salt and vanilla.
Mix well.
Blend flour, salt and baking soda together, then add to the above mixture.
(Do not overmix.)
Fold in chopped nuts.
Prepare 3 (2 pound) aluminum foil loaf pans by spraying with Pam.
Pour batter into pans and bake at 350° for 1 hour or until done.
Test with round toothpick.

title: easy pizza dough
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Add remaining ingredients. Allow dough to rise at least 15 minutes.
Makes one large pizza.

title: strawberry fluff pie
directions: Slice enough strawberries to layer the bottom of the pie shells.
Prepare the vanilla pudding and pour on top of berries in shells.
Take 1 cup berries, sugar and egg whites and beat until fluffy (approximately 1/2 hour).
Pour over pudding in shells. Chill.

title: freddy robinson's monkey bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cut biscuits into quarters.
Combine sugar and cinnamon in a paper bag.
Drop biscuit quarters in bag and shake.
Layer in greased tube or Bundt pan.
Sprinkle nuts between each layer.
Melt margarine and brown sugar, then boil for 1 minute.
Pour mixture over biscuits.
Bake for 35 minutes at 350°.
Let stand 10 minutes before removing from pan.
To serve, take a pinch and eat.

title: apple cake
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients in large bowl, mix well.
Combine flour, soda, salt and cinnamon.
Batter will be thick at this point.
Add apples and pecans.
Beat until well blended, but not enough to puree apples.
Pour into greased and floured tube pan. Bake at 350° for approximately 1 hour or test with toothpick. Cool in pan.
Turn upside down on plate.
After completely cooled, add glaze.

title: italian cookies
directions: Mix together with spoon.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: oreo cake "tastes like ice cream"
directions: Crumble Oreo cookies in bottom of large, deep dish.
In one bowl, mix up vanilla pudding and in another bowl, mix cream cheese and powdered sugar with Cool Whip, then add vanilla flavoring. Pour over Oreos.
Crumble more cookies on top.
Freeze overnight or until hard.
Slice like cake.

title: jello punch
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Add sugar and water; stir well.
Add lemonade and pineapple juice; stir and freeze.
As it starts to freeze, stir once or twice.
When ready to serve, pour Sprite, 7-Up or ginger ale over frozen mixture.

title: filled crab rolls
directions: Fix the day ahead.
Scoop out rolls.
Combine ingredients and mix.
Fill rolls.
Wrap each roll in waxed paper.
Store overnight in refrigerator.

title: rod gipson's vegetable soup
directions: In a large pot, cook the potatoes, onion and tomato juice on medium heat until tender.
Add peas and corn (juice and all) and simmer for 10 to 15 minutes.
Add macaroni, hamburger meat, salt and pepper to taste.
Simmer until macaroni is tender. Serves 6 to 8.
Great with Mexican cornbread.

title: lobster balls
directions: Blend all ingredients together, mixing thoroughly.
Chill and form into bite-size balls.
Keep well chilled until party time. Stick a thin 2-inch pretzel into each ball for an edible handle when ready to serve.
Yields 25 to 30 balls.

title: fettucine alfredo
directions: Scald the cream in a saute pan.
Do not allow to boil or it will curdle.
Add egg yolk and whip in thoroughly.
Add fettucine and grated cheese; mix well.
Season to taste with pepper; serve with chopped parsley for color, while piping hot.

title: buttered rice
directions: Melt butter in covered pot and saute onions. Add rice, stir until grains are well coated with butter.
Add the consomme and salt.
Stir and cover.
Simmer over low heat for about 30 minutes, until grains are tender and liquid absorbed.
Toss rice lightly with fork to release steam and put over warm burner without lid until each grain is separated.
Toss rice with butter and chopped parsley before serving.
Excellent with wild game.

title: mexican hamburger casserole
directions: Brown hamburger and onion; drain.
Line 9 x 13-inch baking dish with half of corn chips.
Stir beans and enchilada sauce into beef mixture.
Pour half over corn chips.
Top with half of cheese.
Mix soup and picante sauce in bowl.
Pour over cheese. Layer remaining corn chips, beef mixture and cheese over soup mixture.
Bake at 300° until cheese is melted.

title: tucson lemon cake
directions: Cream sugar and margarine, beat in eggs and add remaining ingredients.
Pour into greased and floured 12 cup Bundt pan. Bake at 325° for 50 to 55 minutes.
Remove from oven when done, punch holes in hot cake.
Drizzle 2/3 of glaze over cake.
Cool in pan for 20 minutes.
Remove cake to plate and spread with remaining glaze.

title: fruit cake
directions: Combine oil, brown sugar and eggs.
Beat 2 minutes.
Sift flour with dry ingredients.
Stir into oil mixture alternately with pineapple juice.
Mix other cup of flour with fruits and nuts.
Pour batter over fruit mixture, mixing thoroughly.
Turn into greased tube pan and bake at 275° for 2 1/2 to 3 hours.

title: sour cream pound cake
directions: Beat butter at medium speed with an electric mixer about 2 minutes, or until soft and creamy.
Gradually add sugar, beating at medium speed 5 to 7 minutes.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating just until yellow disappears.
Combine flour and baking soda; add to creamed mixture alternately with sour cream, beginning and ending with flour mixture.
Mix at lowest speed just until blended after each addition.
Stir in flavorings.

title: alice's health banana oatmeal muffins
directions: Mix together all dry ingredients; set aside.
Mash bananas. Add pineapple, oil and eggs, slightly beaten.
Add all ingredients and mix well.
Spoon into muffin tins 2/3 full.

title: baked cabbage
directions: Place cabbage in a 1 quart casserole that has been sprayed with cooking spray. Mix the remaining ingredients together and pour over the cabbage. Bake at 350 for 40-45 minutes until custard is set.

title: yellow-pineapple cake
directions: Make the cake mix and bake as directed.
While warm, poke holes in cake with toothpick.
Pour the pineapple juice over the cake. When cool, spread the crushed pineapple over the cake.
Whip the pudding, milk,
Dream Whip and vanilla until thick.
Serve on cake.

title: plain old fashioned lemonade
directions: Mix together lemon juice and sugar; stir in water.
Pour over ice.
Don't add any extras.
It's delight as it is.
Makes 1 quart.

title: salsa cheese dip
directions: Mix all of the ingredients in crock-pot and cook for 3 to 4 hours.
Ready to serve when mixed completely.
Serve with nacho chips.

title: sausage souffle
directions: Crumble bread in 9 x 12-inch Pyrex dish.
Put sausage on top. Mix milk, eggs, mustard, salt and pepper.
Pour over sausage and add cheese.
Cover with foil and refrigerate 6 to 8 hours or overnight.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes, covered.
Uncover and bake 10 minutes more to brown.

title: squash combo
directions: In nonstick skillet, saute 1 chopped onion in 1 teaspoon oil until tender, about 3 minutes.
Add squash, halved lengthwise; add zucchini, sliced crosswise; saute until tender, about 4 minutes. Season with dried oregano, salt and pepper.

title: donna's mud pies
directions: Melt peanut butter and chocolate chips on stove over medium-low heat.
When completely melted, add oatmeal and stir until well blended (you may need to add a little more oatmeal). Drop by spoonfuls onto a cookie sheet covered with wax paper. Chill in refrigerator.

title: pink cloud fruit salad
directions: Drain juice from fruit cocktail.
Heat and add gelatine.
Stir in and mix good.
Add cream cheese and beat with mixer.
Add mayonnaise.
Add fruits, juice and miniature marshmallows.
Fold in whipping cream.

title: coconut-pecan carrot cake
directions: Combine flour, cinnamon, soda and salt; set aside.
Combine oil and sugar; beat until smooth.
Combine egg yolks and water; add to oil mixture, beating well.
Stir in carrots and flour mixture, mixing until well blended.
Beat egg whites (at room temperature) until stiff peaks form; fold into creamed mixture. Pour batter into 3 greased and floured 9-inch cake pans.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes or until a wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool cake in pans for 10 minutes. Remove layers from pans; place on wire racks and let cool completely.

title: fettuccine with artichokes
directions: Cook fettuccine "al dente"; drain.
Keep warm and set aside.

title: noodle salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Tastes better once it has been chilled.

title: appetizers
directions: Brown together meats; drain and add oregano.
Stir in cubed Velveeta cheese.
Spread on party rye slices.
Bake at 325° until browned, 12 to 15 minutes.

title: party cheese ball
directions: Place cheeses in small mixer bowl; let stand at room temperature until softened. Add onion and Worcestershire sauce; blend on low speed. Beat on medium speed until fluffy, scraping side and bottom of bowl. Cover; chill at least 8 hours.

title: pasta fagioli(pasta and beans)
directions: Cover bottom of pot with olive oil. Add basil and clove of garlic. Simmer until garlic is browned. Remove garlic. Add small can of sauce, 1 cup of water and cannellini beans. Simmer for approximately 20 minutes. In another pot, boil water and add 1/2 box of ditalini
noodles. Cook al dente. Drain; rinse and add to pot with sauce and beans.
Cook together for approximately 10 minutes. Add pepper to taste. Serves 4.

title: chablis wine pound cake
directions: Cream sugar and oleo until fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time and beat thoroughly.
Add flour and wine; beat until smooth.
Bake in Bundt pan for 1 hour at 350°.

title: carrot salad
directions: Heat the sugar, vinegar, oil, dry mustard and soup.
Put the heated sauce over the carrot mixture. Serve cooled.

title: lazy pierogi
directions: Drain and rinse sauerkraut.
Cook 15 minutes.
Boil noodles until soft to taste.
Fry onions and mushrooms in butter.
Mix sauerkraut, noodles, onions and mushrooms together and place in large casserole dish.
Add mushroom soup and 1 can of water; mix and heat.
Bake in 350° oven for 45 minutes.

title: bass chowder
directions: Cut fillets into inch-square chunks.
Saute onions in melted shortening until soft before adding potatoes, water, salt, pepper and fish.
Cover and simmer for 15 minutes, or until potatoes are tender.
Add milk and corn.
Heat thoroughly and serve.

title: custard dream cake
directions: Use tube pan or angel food pan.
Combine all ingredients in large mixing bowl.
Beat 4 minutes.
Pour into pan greased with oleo.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes and test with toothpick.
Cool for 10 minutes.
Frost with favorite frosting.

title: peas and dumplings
directions: Heat peas in frypan with 2 cups water.
In heavy pan, heat together 1 cup water, salt and shortening.
When boiling, dump in flour and baking powder, mixed.
Beat over fire until stiff enough to come loose from sides of pan and all stick together.
Remove from fire; add eggs one at a time, beating in each egg well.
Drop by teaspoonful into boiling peas.
When all are in, dot with butter.
Cover and cook 12 minutes.
Serve at once.

title: barbecue meatballs
directions: Place meatballs in crock-pot.
Add barbecue sauce to taste. Heat until meatballs are desired temperature, stirring occasionally.
Great for potlucks or any get together.

title: banana pudding
directions: Prepare pudding mix with milk and sour cream.
After pudding has thickened, fold in Cool Whip.
In casserole bowl, make layers of wafers, sliced bananas and pudding mixture.
Garnish with wafer crumbs, if desired.
Cover bowl.
Must keep refrigerated until served.

title: jellied cranberry salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in boiling water.
Mix in cranberry sauce. Add cold water and remaining ingredients.
This makes a 9 x 13-inch size salad.

title: pineapple casserole
directions: Mix togehter.
Pour into baking dish.
Crumble 1 roll of Ritz crackers on top.
Bake 45 minutes at 325°.

title: pizza
directions: Mix together flour, sugar and water.
Stir it up.
Put it in the oven and cook it until the crust gets hard.
Put cheese and pepperoni on top.

title: butterscotch torte
directions: Mix together with a mixer the flour, butter and pecans. Press into 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until brown.

title: cranberry salad
directions: The night before, chop cranberries in blender and soak in sugar overnight.
Mix in pineapple, nuts and whipped cream thoroughly.
When all has been mixed, add marshmallows and continue to mix together.
Keep refrigerated until ready to serve.

title: spanish rice
directions: Add hot water to tomatoes to make 2 1/4 cups.
Heat oil.
Add rice and brown well. Add garlic and onion. Add chopped tomatoes and liquid.
Simmer, covered, 1/2 hour or until liquid is gone.

title: broccoli baked turkey
directions: Trim stems and leaves off broccoli and separate flowerets. Steam flowerets until just tender.
Set aside.
In medium saucepan, melt margarine.
Remove from heat and stir flour into margarine to make a smooth paste.
Return to low heat and blend in chicken broth until sauce is thick and smooth.
Stir salt and mushrooms into sauce.
Preheat oven to 375°.
Grease a shallow pan with margarine.
Place broccoli in pan.
Cover with turkey, then sauce.
Bake, uncovered, 15 to 25 minutes.

title: no cook strawberry preserves
directions: Mix strawberries, crushed with sugar; let stand 20 minutes. Bring water and Sure-Jell to a boil; boil 1 minute. Mix with berries, put in containers and freeze.

title: sauerkraut salad
directions: Boil sugar, water and vinegar to hard rolling boil.
Pour over salad mix.
Let stand at least 24 hours.
Can be kept up to 3 months, if refrigerated.

title: rainbow sherbet punch
directions: Mix each package Kool-Aid with 1 1/2 cups sugar and 2 quarts water.

title: fluffy white icing
directions: Mix margarine and shortening on medium speed until creamy. Add remaining ingredients and whip on high until light and fluffy. Frosts two 9-inch round, one 9 x 13-inch or 2 1/2 dozen cup cakes.

title: pasta italiano bake
directions: Brown meat and drain.
Add onion, green pepper and garlic. Cook until tender.
Stir in tomato paste, water and seasonings. Cover; simmer for 15 minutes.
Combine noodles and parsley; toss lightly.
Combine 1/2 cup cheese and eggs; mix well. Layer noodles and meat sauce in a 10 x 6-inch baking dish.
Top with remaining cheese.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: seafood gumbo
directions: Saute okra in 2 tablespoons butter until lightly browned.
Set aside.
Combine remaining 1/4 cup butter and flour in large skillet; cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until brown colored (20 to 25).
Stir in green onions, celery and garlic; cook until vegetables are tender.
Combine okra, tomatoes and next 6 ingredients into large Dutch oven.
Bring to boil, then reduce heat and simmer, uncovered, 2 hours, stirring once.

title: carrot cake
directions: Combine oil and sugar; mix well.
Mix half dry ingredients into sugar mixture; blend.
Add remaining dry ingredients alternately with eggs, one at a time, mixing well after each addition.
Add carrots; mix well.
Pour into lightly oiled or greased with shortening, then floured pans (three pans 7 x 11-inch).
Bake in 350° oven for about 40 minutes.
Cool.
Frost with Cream Cheese Frosting.

title: graham cracker crust
directions: Mix and put into pie pan.

title: firecracker cheese log
directions: On a sheet of plastic wrap, spread out cream cheese into a 9 x 5-inch rectangle.
In a small bowl, combine 1 teaspoon paprika, parsley, garlic powder and black pepper.
Sprinkle paprika on cheese, covering evenly.
Place in icebox for 20 minutes.
Using plastic wrap as guide, roll up cheese, making a compact log. Cover outside of cheese log with remaining paprika.
Total time: 30 minutes.

title: everlasting bran muffins
directions: Place in a bowl crushed shredded wheat.
Add Raisin Bran.
Pour in hot water.
Stir cereals together and set aside.
Cream shortening and sugar.
Beat in eggs (one at a time).
Add cereal mixture and stir gently by hand.
Sift together flour, baking soda, baking powder and salt.
Add flour mixture alternately with buttermilk to creamed mixture and stir lightly by hand.
Store in refrigerator overnight then bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Batter keeps up to 6 weeks.
Add extra raisins.
Yields 4 dozen.

title: banana rolls
directions: Put bananas, sugar, margarine and eggs in a large bowl; mix well.
Add
about
half
the flour and mix well.
Add dissolved yeast and
mix well.
Add rest of flour and mix.
Knead well.
Let rise until double in bulk.
Roll out and butter the surface. Sprinkle
with
brown sugar and chopped nuts.
Place on greased baking
sheet
and
let
rise until almost double. Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: hoppin' john
directions: Bring 2 cups of water to a boil.
Add rice, peas and bacon. Remove from heat when rice is cooked.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix together.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: hershey bar cake
directions: Melt candy in syrup; set aside to cool.
Cream sugar and butter.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well.
Mix soda and buttermilk.
Add alternately with flour.
Add chocolate mixture, blend well and add vanilla.
Pour into a greased and floured 10-inch tube pan.
Bake in 350° oven for 1 hour and 20 minutes.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Cream butter, sugars and peanut butter. Add eggs and vanilla. Mix. Blend in flour, soda and salt. Chill. Roll into teaspoon-size balls. Press with a fork dipped in flour on greased cookie sheet. Bake at 375° for 9 to 10 minutes.

title: crescent rolls with tuna and sauce
directions: Make tuna salad; roll out crescent rolls and top with tuna salad.
Put another crescent roll on top and pinch edges together. Cook until rolls are done.
While rolls cook, mix sour cream and cream of chicken soup in top of double boiler.
Serve over tuna rolls.

title: crock-pot polish cabbage rolls
directions: Mix ground beef, egg, rice, onion, carrot, salt and pepper. Mix together vinegar, brown sugar and tomato sauce.
Drop cabbage into boiling water for 5 to 10 minutes.
Remove 10 large leaves. Chop remaining cabbage and place in bottom of crock-pot.
Place 2 to 4 tablespoons of meat mixture in center of each leaf.
Roll up and use toothpick to hold.
Place stem side down in crock-pot. Pour on tomato mixture.
Cover and cook on low for 8 to 10 hours. Serves 6 to 8.

title: zucchini chocolate cake
directions: Cream together in a large bowl the first four ingredients. Add eggs, vanilla and buttermilk and stir to mix well.
Measure all dry ingredients into a sifter, then sift into the bowl with wet ingredients.
Grate the zucchini into the bowl.
Stir until well blended.

title: cranberry punch
directions: Combine cranberry juice, grapefruit juice concentrate, club soda, coriander and grated orange peel.
Chill; serve garnished with thin orange slices.
Yield:
About 15 (3 ounce) servings.

title: summer coleslaw
directions: In a medium bowl, combine cabbage, carrots and onion.
In another bowl, combine yogurt, oil, horseradish, salt and pepper. Spoon over cabbage; mix and toss.
Refrigerate until chilled.

title: grilled potatoes
directions: Combine potatoes, pepper and onion in large bowl; set aside. Heat oil, rosemary, garlic and pepper flakes together in small saucepan.
Toss oil mixture with vegetables.
Sprinkle with salt. Place vegetables on a large, square of heavy-duty aluminum foil. Seal well.
Place foil package on grill over medium to hot coals. Cook 45 minutes, turning once.
Yields 4 cups/servings.

title: almond bark candy
directions: Melt almond bark; add remainder of ingredients.
Drop teaspoonfuls onto wax paper.

title: shipwreck
directions: In skillet, cook bacon until crisp.
Remove to paper towel and drain.
Crumble and set aside.
Drain drippings and browned ground beef and drain.
Add onion and cook until tender.
Mix ketchup and brown sugar and stir in beef mixture.
Stir in pork and beans and all but 2 tablespoons of bacon.
Put in 8-inch square baking dish. Top with rest of bacon.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Yield:
6 to 8 servings.

title: debbie's spaghetti sauce
directions: Brown ground beef; drain.
Add remaining ingredients, except linguini.
Simmer for 1/2 to 1 hour.
Cook linguini according to directions on package.
Serve with garlic bread, salad and applesauce.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Put 8 pieces of bread in 9 x 13-inch buttered baking dish. Cover with bacon then cheese slices.
Cover with other bread. Beat eggs, salt, pepper, mustard, onion, green pepper, Worcestershire sauce, milk and Tabasco together.
Pour over bread.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
In the morning, melt butter and pour over top.
Cover with crushed cornflakes.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Let stand 10 minutes.
Serve.

title: chili
directions: Brown garlic and onion in small amount of oil.
Brown beef and add garlic, tomato sauce, onion, salt, pepper and cayenne pepper. Add chili powder and simmer 1 hour.

title: tangy herb dip
directions: Stir cream cheese until fluffy; gradually stir in buttermilk until smooth. Add remaining ingredients, except salt and pepper. Gradually add salt and pepper to taste.
Salt may be omitted. Store covered in refrigerator for 4 to 24 hours to blend flavors. Remove 1 hour before serving.
Serve with a variety of fresh vegetables and crackers or party bread. Yields approximately 2 cups.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix together and bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: banana split
directions: Mix together.
Spread into bottom of 13 x 9-inch pan.

title: tiger cookies
directions: Sift together flour, salt and soda; set aside.
Beat margarine and sugar.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Beat well.
Add flour mix.
Stir in flake crumbs.
Then stir in melted morsels to make marbled appearance.
Bake at 350° for 12 minutes.

title: spicy sesame beef stir-fry
directions: Combine beef strips with 1 1/2 tablespoons sesame seed in a small bowl. Toss to coat well. Cut florets off broccoli stalk. Peel stalk and thinly slice crosswise.
Combine broccoli florets and stalk with yellow pepper in medium bowl.
Stir broth, soy sauce, ginger, garlic, cornstarch and crushed red pepper in small bowl until cornstarch dissolves.
Heat 1 1/2 tablespoons oil in wok or heavy large skillet over high heat. Add beef and stir-fry until brown, about 2 minutes.
Using slotted spoon, transfer beef to plate.
Heat remaining 1 1/2 tablespoons oil in wok.
Add broccoli and peppers and cover wok.
Add beef and accumulated juices from plate. Simmer until sauce thickens, stirring occasionally, about 1 minute.
Transfer beef mixture to platter. Sprinkle with toasted sesame seed, if desired, and serve.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Chill.
Make into balls and push down with glass.

title: sweet and sour meat balls
directions: Place sauces in pan; add meatballs.
Simmer 45 minutes until done.
Serve in chafing dish and keep warm, toothpicks will be needed to serve.
Can be made ahead and frozen.

title: the baby's coming mandel bread
directions: Sift flour, baking powder and salt.
Cream shortening and sugar.
Gradually add eggs to creamed mixture.
Add dry ingredients to shortening mix.
Stir in almonds and lemon juice.
Shape into loaves on a greased baking sheet.
Bake for 30 to 35 minutes at 350°.
Remove from oven and cut into slices approximately 3/4 inch thick.
Return to oven until brown.

title: oriental sesame noodle salad
directions: Cook noodles.
Before draining, add halved and cut into thin slices squash and tomatoes.
Drain and rinse in cold water.
Add sprouts.

title: green beans and red potato vinaigrette
directions: Cook potatoes in slightly salted water.
Drain.
Wash the beans and steam until tender, but crisp, 5 to 10 minutes.
Drain. Run under cold water and refrigerate.

title: stuffed mushrooms
directions: Wash mushrooms well and dry.
Remove stems from mushrooms. Add chopped stems and onions in covered dish and microwave for 4 minutes, stirring after 2 minutes.

title: pico de gallo(really good)
directions: Combine all ingredients and let stand for at least 1 hour. Use as a dip.

title: lemon squares
directions: Mix cake mix, egg and Parkay.
Mixture will be thick.
Press into a 9 x 13-inch greased and floured pan.
Mix the rest of the ingredients together and pour over the mixture in pan.
Bake at 350° until golden and pulls away from pan, about 25 minutes.

title: overnight salad
directions: Combine ingredients and refrigerate.
Excellent when served with barbecue at Christmas.

title: dirt cake
directions: Mix the cream cheese, powdered sugar and margarine together. Mix pudding.
Add Cool Whip to pudding.
Fold into cream cheese. Put Cool Whip cover on bottom of 8-inch flowerpot or sand pail. Put a layer of cream cheese mixture in pot.
Layer with crushed cookies.
Keep layering and end with crushed cookies.
You can put gummy worms or artificial flower in pot for children's party. Delicious.
Keep refrigerated.

title: divine chicken
directions: Cook chicken breasts until soft.
Remove skin and bones and break into pieces.
Mix sour cream and both soups together.
Put chicken in a
9 x 13-inch baking pan. Spread with soup mixture. Top with stuffing mix. Drizzle with butter. Bake at 350° for 25 minutes. Can be put together the day before cooking and refrigerated.
However, then I add 10 minutes to the cooking time.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: Saute onion in olive oil until onion is clear.
Add tomato sauce and tomato paste and water.
Simmer for about 15 minutes; add remaining ingredients and simmer about an hour.
This sauce only has about 3 grams of fat per serving.

title: snappy cheese ball
directions: Blend cheeses.
Add wine, nuts, onion and parsley; mix well. Chill and then shape into 4 balls.
Can be frozen.

title: rice and peas(wartime ca 1940's)
directions: Boil or make rice according to directions.
Chop the onions fine and fry them in oil until tender.
Add the cooked rice and peas and stir until all are blended and hot.
Serve immediately.

title: sausage balls
directions: Put sausage meat into frying pan and heat until grease is cooked out.
Drain off grease.
Mix ingredients together with hands and roll into balls the size of a marble.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Makes 50 balls.

title: pot of "irish gold coins"
directions: Spread peanut butter on 24 vanilla wafers cookies.
Top with remaining cookies to make sandwiches.
Melt butterscotch chips over double boiler.
Dip each cookie sandwich into melted butterscotch and place on waxed paper to cool.
Yield: 2 dozen "coins."

title: steamed, stuffed artichokes
directions: Wash artichokes.
Hold bottom of artichokes and pound 2 or 3 times on a flat surface to loosen the leaves at the top.
In a 5-quart pot, arrange artichokes so they fit tightly.
Mix together the breadcrumbs, garlic, parsley, grated cheese, oregano, salt, pepper and red pepper.
Gradually add about 3 tablespoons olive oil to mixture, until breadcrumbs are all coated.
With a tablespoon, fill each artichoke with about 3 to 4 tablespoons of the breadcrumb mixture.
Without wetting the breadcrumbs, fill the pot 3/4 full with water.
Drizzle about 2 tablespoons of oil over the artichokes.
Steam, covered, for about 25 to 30 minutes, until the leaves pull out easily.

title: easy pineapple cake
directions: Spread pineapple in a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle dry cake mix over the fruit.
Dot with slices of oleo.
Bake at 350° for about 35 minutes.

title: chocolate pixies
directions: Melt oleo and Baker's chocolate together over low heat.
Blend eggs and sugar (1 egg at a time).
Beat 1 minute.
Add dry items and nuts.
Add chocolate.
Mix well.
Chill 15 minutes.

title: strawberry shortcake
directions: Combine flour and sugar.
Cut in cream cheese and butter. Pour beaten egg into measuring cup and add enough milk to measure 3/4 cup.
Gradually stir into flour mixture.
Knead dough about 20 seconds.
Divide dough into 2 parts.
Roll each part 1/2-inch thick.
Cut 6 circles from each half.
Spread 1 circle with melted butter and place another circle on top.
Bake at 425°
for approximately 15 minutes.
When done, separate layers and spread each layer with butter.
Put sweetened berries on one circle and top with other circle.
Top
with additional strawberries and top with whipped cream.
Yields 6 servings.

title: nutty buddies
directions: Crush 42 Oreo cookies fine in blender.
Mix together with melted butter and spread in the bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Soften vanilla ice cream.
Spread on top of Oreo mixture.
Freeze until solid.
When firm, remove from freezer and spread hot fudge or caramel topping.
Add crushed Spanish peanuts or regular peanuts on top of fudge/caramel topping.
Spread softened Cool Whip and sprinkle a little of the crushed Oreos on top of Cool Whip.

title: delicious rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in water.
Add milk, sugar, salt and shortening. Mix well.
Add eggs and flour.
Knead until smooth.
Let rise until doubled in bulk.
Make into rolls.
Let rise.

title: pepper biscuits
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Make a well (hole) and add oil and water.
Mix and knead a little.
Roll and shape.
Bake in a 400° oven for 20 to 25 minutes or longer until brown.

title: wagon bread loaf
directions: Wash and pat dry herbs.
Remove leaves from stems and measure 1 1/2 to 2 cups of leaves.
Evenly spread leaves on a double thickness of a paper towel. Microwave on High for 4 to 6 minutes. Stir several times during drying.
When properly dried, herbs will be brittle and will rattle when stirred.
Store in an airtight container in a cool, dry place.

title: spanakopita(cheese spinach pie)
directions: Cook onion in margarine until tender.
Cool.
Lay pieces over pie dough, follow with spinach, then onions.
Beat eggs, add enough milk for 1 cup.
Pour over spinach.
Bake at 400° for 35 minutes.

title: crock-pot steak and noodles
directions: Cut steak into 1-inch cubes.
Brown in skillet and drain on towel.
Heat crock-pot and add all three cans of soup and one can of water.
Add steak.
Cook on high for 4 to 4 1/2 hours.
Cook noodles and drain.
Serve steak and soup over noodles.

title: apple cake
directions: Mix all ingredients, apples and pecans last.
Pour into a greased and floured tube pan. Sprinkle finely chopped pecans on top.
Cook in a 300° oven for 1 hour.

title: silly putty(don't eat this!)
directions: Mix the glue and starch in a cup.
Stir well.
The mixture will begin to look like dough or "a brain".
(You may need to add more starch.)
As the mixture forms a ball, pour off any excess starch.
Knead this glob in your hands until your hands become "dry".
You can store your finished putty in a plastic container.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Prepare macaroni according to package directions.
While macaroni is cooking, chop tomatoes and green onions into small pieces; place in a 1 1/2-quart bowl.
Drain cooked macaroni; add cheese sauce and butter.
Cool.
Add to bowl containing tomatoes and green onions.
Add salad dressing and mustard; mix.
(More salad dressing can be used if you like salad creamier.)
Add salt, pepper and basil to taste.
Can be served warm or cool.

title: spinach souffle
directions: Brown onions in butter.
Stir in flour; add milk slowly.
Add spinach, cheese and seasonings.
Heat; remove from fire.
Mix in unbeaten yolks.
Cool; fold in whites.
Pour into greased baking dish; set dish in pan of water in a moderate oven.
Bake until mixture rises and sets (about 30 minutes).
Serves 8.

title: grandma's chicken stew
directions: Mix all together and cook about 15 minutes.
You can vary the amount you make but the amount of ingredients you use.

title: apple muffins
directions: Mix combined milk, egg and melted shortening to dry ingredients; stir slightly.
Add apples and mix only until ingredients are moist.
Divide into 18 muffin cups and bake at 400° for 25 minutes.

title: picnic mashed potatoes
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a large, heavy saucepan, place potatoes in just enough water to cover them.
Bring water to a boil over medium-high heat.
Cover saucepan loosely.
Reduce heat to medium.
Cook until potatoes are soft.
Drain potatoes.
Add butter or margarine, cream cheese and sour cream.
Beat on high speed mixer until smooth.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Beat 2 minutes more.
Transfer potatoes into a medium baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Remove from oven.
Sprinkle lightly with paprika.
Serve hot or cold.

title: hot cheese dip
directions: Place cheese in saucepan and melt over low heat.
Add other ingredients and mix well.
Serve with crackers or fresh vegetables.

title: chocolate mousse
directions: Pour milk into bowl.
Add pudding mix.
Beat with wire whisk for 2 minutes.
Stir in 1 cup of whipped topping.
Spoon into serving cups.
Refrigerate until ready to serve.
Garnish with remaining whipped topping.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Beat eggs with Wesson oil and sugar until creamy.
Mix together dry ingredients; add fresh apples, nuts and vanilla.
Mix with egg mixture.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 55 minutes.

title: dutch st. nicholas cookies
directions: Cream the butter and sugar.
Sift the flour with spices, salt and soda and add alternately with sour cream to creamed mixture. Add nuts.
Knead together well.
Place in refrigerator trays, wrapped in waxed paper and chill overnight.
Slice and bake in a 400° oven until brown.
Makes 72 (2 x 4-inch) cookies.

title: hawaiian punch shake
directions: Prepare Kool-Aid as directed on package.
Pour 6 to 8 ounces punch flavored Kool-Aid into blender.
Add Hi-Energy Vanilla Supplement and Sweet 'N Low.
Blend well.
Add ice gradually and blend until smooth.

title: sour cream coffee cake
directions: Cream together margarine, sugar, eggs, vanilla and sour cream; beat well.
Gradually add flour, baking powder and salt to creamed mixture.
Beat until light and smooth.

title: 3 cheese pizzas(low-fat)
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Place bagel halves, cut side up, on ungreased cookie sheet. Top each bagel half with 1 tablespoon spaghetti sauce.
Sprinkle each with 1 tablespoon Cheddar cheese, 1 tablespoon Monterey Jack cheese and 1/2 teaspoon Parmesan cheese. Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes or until cheese is melted.
Makes 4 pizzas.
Serving:
1 pizza.
Calories:
Fat grams:

title: pretzel salad
directions: Mix together broken pretzels, melted butter and 1 tablespoon sugar.
Press into 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Bake at 400° for 8 minutes and cool.
Mix Jell-O, boiling water and frozen strawberries.
Refrigerate until slightly thickened, but not set. Cream together softened cream cheese and 1 cup sugar.
Add Cool Whip and blend.
Spread over cooled crust of pretzels.
Pour thickened Jell-O on top of cream cheese layer and chill until congealed.
Cut in squares.

title: sweet-sour deviled eggs
directions: Slice eggs lengthwise.
Remove yolks and place into mixing bowl.
Mix in La Choy sauce.
Add ground mustard and pickle relish. Mix well.
Spoon mixture back into eggs.
Sprinkle with paprika.

title: marinated cucumbers
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients; let stand for 2 hours.
Mix sugar and vinegar and let stand for 2 hours.
Pour vinegar solution over vegetables and store in refrigerator, covered.
Will keep 2 months.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Boil chicken.
Pull off bone.
Put in a 9 x 13-inch pan. Drain vegetables and spread over chicken.
Mix chicken soup with chicken broth.
