Cook until smooth.
Pour over vegetables.
Mix flour, milk and melted margarine.
Pour over top of pie.
Bake at 400° until crust is brown.

title: southern sweet potato pie
directions: Mix the first 5 ingredients.
Add sweet potatoes and butter; mix well.
Cool.
Beat in eggs.
Stir in lemon rind and milk. Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake 40 to 50 minutes or until done at 400°.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Boil chicken pieces in water until tender, reserving 2 cups broth.
Remove bones from chicken.
Preheat oven to 375°.
Place chicken in 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Sprinkle with chopped eggs. Mix cornstarch and broth.
Add salt, pepper and butter.
Bring to a boil and cook until thickened, stirring constantly.
Pour thickened broth over chicken and eggs.
Unroll dough and place on top of chicken.
Bake 12 minutes.
Serves 2.

title: baked eggplant and tomato casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Lightly grease 12 x 8 baking dish.

title: garden macaroni salad
directions: Cook macaroni and drain.
Add rest of ingredients.

title: sopaipillas
directions: Sift flour, baking powder and salt into medium bowl.
Make well in center of ingredients.
Add 1 tablespoon peanut oil and water; mix well with a fork to form a soft, smooth dough.
Divide into 4 portions.
Knead each part 4 or 5 times, until smooth. Form each part into a ball.
Flatten with palm of hand.

title: ham ball
directions: Mix together and chill in airtight container 24 hours.
Make a ball and roll in pecans.
Serve with crackers.

title: lazy pierogis
directions: Prepare pasta according to package directions.
Saute onion and mushrooms until the onions are translucent.
Mix all the ingredients together.
Bake at 350° in a large, covered casserole for 1 hour or until golden brown.
Serve with Polish sausage. This makes approximately 4 quarts.
Great for a barbecue.

title: cheese cake
directions: Dissolve jello in hot water.
Add lemon juice.
Cool until partly set (about like egg white).
Cream the cream cheese with 1 cup sugar; mix until fluffy.
Mix graham crackers with melted butter and 1/4 cup sugar.
Mix well.
Set aside 3/4 cup crumbs for topping.
Press rest of mixture in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan. Whip milk until very stiff.
Slowly add jello mixture.
Beat well. Add cheese mixture and beat 2 minutes at 1/2 speed.
Pour into cracker shell and top with reserved crumbs; chill several hours.

title: 3 cheese chicken bake
directions: Cook noodles in chicken broth. Rinse in cold water. Layer a 9 x 13 pan as follows: half the noodles, half the sauce, cottage cheese and chicken and other ingredients. Repeat for second layer.

title: cranberry muffins
directions: Generously grease muffin pan
(12 muffin size).
Mix dry ingredients in medium bowl.
Beat
egg,
milk
and margarine in another bowl.
Add to dry mixture
and stir quickly and lightly until flour is almost dampened.
Do
not beat.
Add cranberries and lightly stir.
Do not beat.
Fill muffin cups slightly more than half full.
Sprinkle with
sugar
and	cinnamon mix.
Bake for 20 to 25 minutes at 375°.
Remove from pan at once, loosening around edges with knife first.
Serve hot.

title: brandy balls
directions: Evaporated milk may be whipped and substituted for whipped cream in some recipes.
It triples in volume when whipped. Measure amount desired and pour into ice-cube tray.
Place in freezer to chill until fine ice crystals from around edge.
Chill bowl and beaters at same time.
Pour milk into cold bowl and whip rapidly with cold beaters until stiff and will hold a peak.
Use immediately.

title: busy day vegetable soup
directions: Brown meat and onion in large Dutch oven.
Drain excess fat. Add all remaining ingredients.
Simmer 45 minutes to 1 hour. Serves 8.
Calories per serving, 191 (protein 49%, carbohydrate 39%, fat 12%).

title: spaghetti pie
directions: Cook spaghetti until tender.
Mix in pot with butter, salt, pepper and egg white.
Mix thoroughly.
Add Parmesan cheese. Spread mixture in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cook meat mixture and stir into spaghetti sauce.
Spread cottage cheese over spaghetti layer. Top with meat mixture.
Bake in oven at 350° for 30 minutes. Sprinkle Mozzarella cheese on top and bake additional 10 minutes or until cheese is melted and beginning to brown.
Let stand 15 minutes before cutting.

title: chili-roni
directions: Cook beef in butter (browned); add tomatoes, tomato paste, salt and chili powder.
Cook 25 minutes.
Add beans and cooked Roni.

title: baked spareribs
directions: Mix thoroughly.
Soak ribs completely in the marinade.
Cover and let stand overnight.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix well.
Roll into large pecan-size balls.
Bake on cookie sheet covered in foil about 15 minutes at 350°.
Makes approximately 4 dozen.
Can be frozen.

title: italian potato salad (for a big family)
directions: Boil potatoes in skins until done, but still firm.
Peel and cut into 1-inch cubes.
Put in large mixing bowl and add onion and celery.
Add garlic and parsley.
Season with salt and pepper. Add oil.
Serve at room temperature.
Makes 10 to 12 servings. Enjoy!

title: vegetable chow chow
directions: Wash everything.
Use coarse blade to grind onions, cabbage, tomatoes and peppers.
Sprinkle with pickling salt and let stand overnight.
Rinse and drain.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix thoroughly.
Shape and put into greased loaf pan.
Pour the can of sauce over loaf.
Lay bacon over top.
Cover and bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: rhubarb crunch
directions: Melt margarine and add oats, brown sugar, flour and cinnamon. Mix together and place 1/2 of the mixture in a greased 9-inch square pan.
Add the rhubarb pieces.
Then cook sugar, cornstarch, water and vanilla until it thickens.
Pour this over the rhubarb and put rest of topping over it.
Bake 1 hour at 350°, until bubbly and brown.

title: molded fruit salad
directions: Drain pineapple.
Press out one cup of juice.
Drain raspberry liquid into a measuring cup and add enough water to make 1 cup. Dissolve gelatin in 1 cup boiling water.
Stir in pineapple juice (1 cup) and raspberry liquid (1 cup).
Pour 1 1/2 cups of that mixture into a 6-cup mold or 11 x 7-inch Pyrex pan.
Stir in pineapple.
Chill until partially set.
Chill remaining gelatin until syrupy.
Stir in raspberries, sour cream and walnuts.
Pour over partially set gelatin.
Chill overnight in refrigerator.
May unmold on salad plate lined with salad greens.

title: freezer pickles
directions: In large bowl, combine cucumbers and salt.
Let stand 2 1/2 hours; drain well.
Combine sugar and vinegar; pour over well drained cucumbers.
Mix well.
Let stand 15 minutes.
Place in freezer containers and freeze.

title: can't go wrong fudge
directions: Bring the first 3 ingredients to a boil for 10 minutes, stirring constantly. Remove from heat and add the peanut butter and marshmallow. Beat well, then add the secret of this recipe, the flour.
Mix well again and pour into well buttered 9 x 13-inch pan. This fudge keeps very well and the recipe makes 4 1/4 pounds.

title: mushrooms in sour cream
directions: Combine undrained mushrooms and onion in saucepan; simmer for 10 minutes.
Melt margarine in skillet; blend in flour.
Cook, stirring, until lightly browned.
Add to mushrooms.
Cook, stirring constantly until thickened.
Stir in sour cream; heat through.
Yields 4 servings.

title: oriental salad
directions: Blend well the seasoning packet, virgin olive oil, balsamic vinegar, sugar and soy sauce.

title: quiche
directions: Bake a deep-dish pie shell according to directions.
Brush pie shell with margarine before baking.
Combine all ingredients in mixing bowl and pour into baked pie shell.
Bake quiche at 350° for 30 minutes or until knife inserted into center comes out clean.

title: ron's baked bean - crock pot method
directions: Pick over Beans, rinse and soak overnight in cold water.
Place sliced Onion on bottom of crock pot.
Trim skin off Salt Pork and excess fat (I leave about 1/2 the fat on with meat).
Rinse beans, pick through one last time and place in crock pot.
Add Molasses, Brown Sugar, Salt Pork, Mustard, Salt and Pepper.
Add water to completely cover ingredients, cover and place crock pot on high for first 5 - 6 hours, place on low for final 2 - 3 hours.
Serve with Hamburg patties, Hot Dogs and Brown Bread.

title: monkey bread
directions: In large mixing bowl mix sugar, cinnamon and biscuits.
Seal and shake.
In small saucepan melt together oleo and sugar.
Layer biscuit mixture with syrup mixture in Bundt pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.
Loosen with spatula and put on a plate.

title: five hour stew
directions: Combine first four ingredients in a saucepan.
In roaster, put meat in bottom.
Spread vegetables over meat.
Pour combined soups over top.
Cover and bake at 275° for five hours.
Never have to look at it.
Do not stir.
Mix after stew comes out of oven.
May use other vegetables, too.

title: fudge
directions: Mix all ingredients together and bring to a boil.
When it is a full rolling boil, time and cook 5 minutes.
Add one 6 ounce package semi-sweet chocolate chips and 1 teaspoon vanilla.
Beat a little and pour into a buttered dish.

title: coffee cake with nuts and coconut
directions: In a large mixing bowl, combine oil, sugar, brown sugar, eggs and vanilla; mix well. Combine flour, soda, salt and cinnamon; add to egg mixture alternately with buttermilk. Stir until well moistened; add coconut and nuts. Pour into a greased 13 x 9 baking pan. Bake in 350° oven for 35 to 40 minutes or until a toothpick inserted in center comes out clean. Let cool and dust with powdered sugar.

title: bicycle bar
directions: Melt chocolate and peanut butter in a large saucepan over low heat.
Add all remaining ingredients, mixing well.
Shape quickly with buttered hands into 8 bars, about 3-inches long.
Wrap end bar in plastic wrap and refrigerate
until firm.
Makes 8 bars.

title: taffy apple salad
directions: Drain pineapple; save juice. Toss apples in juice and drain well. Combine apples, pineapple and peanuts and set aside. Combine sugar, flour, vinegar and whipped topping. Toss with apple mixture. Sprinkle with remaining peanuts and chill.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Cook chicken and reserve 2 cups broth.
Debone chicken and cut into small pieces.
Place in large casserole dish.
Mix broth, soup and vegetables in saucepan.
Bring to boil and pour over chicken.
Mix flour, margarine and milk to make pancake-like batter.
Pour evenly over chicken in dish.
Bake at 425° until crust browns (25 to 30 minutes).

title: baked apple pudding
directions: Combine margarine, sugar and egg in mixing bowl; beat until light.
Gradually blend in combined flour, soda, nutmeg and cinnamon.
Stir in vanilla, apples and walnuts.
Pour mixture into an ungreased 13 x 9-inch.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes or until done when tested.
Serve warm or cold topped with ice cream.

title: cheesy rice grape leaf casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Wash grape leaves in water.
Squeeze dry, tear into small pieces.
Set aside bread crumbs and 3/4 cup of Mozzarella.
Mix grape leaves with all remaining ingredients. Pack into 9 x 9-inch pan.
Sprinkle reserved bread crumbs on top. Bake 30 minutes.
Turn off oven.
Sprinkle remaining Mozzarella on top of casserole and leave pan in oven until cheese melts.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: frosted melon mold salad
directions: Pare melon; cut a slice from each end and scoop out seeds. In small bowl, combine cream cheese and milk; mix until smooth. Frost entire outside of melon with cheese mixture.
Chill.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Blend all ingredients until smooth.
Pour into pie shells. Sprinkle with chocolate chips or shaved chocolate to garnish. Freeze at least two hours before serving.
Serve slightly frozen.

title: pork chops
directions: Place pork chops in bottom of 9 x 13 baking pan. Salt and pepper pork chops.

title: best cake
directions: Mix eggs and sugar well; add vanilla.
Mix flour and baking soda together and add to sugar.
Stir in pineapple, nuts and raisins.
Bake at 350° for about 35 minutes.

title: lemon herb chicken
directions: Mix soup, water and oil.
Coat chicken.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes.

title: no bake cake
directions: Use a spring-form pan.
Buy 3 packages of almond toast to be on the safe side.
You may need more than 2, depending on the size of the spring-form pan.
Sprinkle some of the water on the bottom of the pan.
Put cookies, flat side down.
Sprinkle more water on top.
Pour some of the cooked pudding on the first layer.
Repeat until you have 3 layers.
Cover with Saran Wrap and refrigerate overnight or at least 6 hours before serving.
Run knife around the edges of the pan; release and spread Cool Whip on top and sides of the cake.

title: hobo stew
directions: In large Dutch oven place all ingredients together.
Bring to a boil for 10 minutes.
Turn to low or simmer heat until veggies are tender.

title: butterfinger pie
directions: Mix Cool Whip with crunched up candy bars, put in pie crust and leave in freezer for at least 2 hours before serving.

title: salmon croquettes
directions: Drain salmon, remove skin and bones.
Add beaten eggs, then seasonings, butter, bread crumbs and baking powder.
Mix and roll into patties.
Fry in hot oil until brown on both sides.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: parmesan chicken bites or strips
directions: Preheat oven to 450°. Crush croutons in resealable plastic bag.
Grate parmesan cheese.
Combine crouton, cheese, crumbs, parsley and garlic salt.
Whisk egg whites and water.
Dip chicken pieces into egg mixture, then into crumb mixture to coat evenly. Arrange on baking stone or cookie sheet.
Bake 14 to 16 minutes until chicken is no longer pink in center. Serve with dressing.

title: orange julius
directions: Combine all ingredients in a blender, blend until smooth. Makes 2 large or 4 small drinks.

title: dirt cake
directions: Combine the first 3 ingredients in a large bowl.
Combine next 2 ingredients in second bowl.
Fold in whipped topping.
Add to first bowl.
Mix thoroughly.
Put half of the crushed Oreos on bottom of an 8-inch plastic flowerpot.
Pour 1/3 of the mixture in.
Repeat twice, then put Oreos on top to look like dirt. Garnish with artificial flowers and gummy worms, if desired. Chill at least 2 hours.

title: carrot-pear soup
directions: Heat butter in large pot.
Add onion, garlic and celery; saute until softened, about 10 minutes.
Add carrot, potato, pear, bay leaf and chicken broth.
Cover and bring to boil.
Lower heat; simmer 40 minutes.
Remove bay leaf.
Working in batches, whirl soup mixture in blender or food processor until smooth puree. Season with pepper.

title: au gratin potatoes
directions: Mix together.
Pam casserole (10 x 14-inch pan).
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: cherokee casserole
directions: Cook beef in oil until light colored.
Drain.
Add onion and cook until transparent.
Add remaining ingredients, except cheese and olives.
Mix well and spoon into a 3-quart baking dish.
Top with cheese, cover and bake 45 minutes at 350°.
Remove from oven and garnish with olives.
Yield:
4 to 6 servings.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Melt 4 tablespoons margarine in microwave.
Stir in Pepperidge Farm stuffing, adding a small amount of hot tap water to ensure thorough moistening.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Trim all fat, then cut in 1/2-inch strips (easiest to do if meat is partially frozen).
Dredge meat strips in flour and brown in butter on all sides, a few at a time.
Remove meat from pan; keep warm.

title: custard pie
directions: Blend eggs, sugar, salt and vanilla. Gradually, stir in scalded milk. Pour into 9 inch unbaked pit crust. Sprinkle lightly with nutmeg or cinnamon. Bake in preheated oven, 400°F for 25 to 30 minutes, or until knife inserted half-way between outside and center comes out clean. Cool 15 to 30 minutes then refrigerate.

title: tropical cream punch
directions: In punch bowl, combine sweetened condensed milk and juice concentrates; mix well.
Gradually add club soda; stir.
Garnish with orange slices.
Serve over ice.
Makes about 3 quarts.

title: pecan praline(club member: lee higginbotham)
directions: Add all ingredients, except butter. Cook in heavy saucepan until soft ball. Add butter and stir. Beat until candy has glossy appearance. Drop by teaspoonful on wax paper.

title: beef stew
directions: Brown beef in iron skillet with oil and salt.
Put in pressure cooker; set aside.
Reheat skillet.
Turn off heat.
Add water and pour over beef.
Add carrots, potatoes (cut in 6 pieces) and garlic powder.
Pressure cook for 20 minutes.
Now add the other potatoes, celery and beef seasoning.
Cook 30 minutes without lid. Salt to taste and thicken with a flour and water mixture that has been strained.

title: cheese soup
directions: Mix celery and onions; saute.
Add flour, cream, carrots, chicken stock and cheese.
Simmer.

title: quick yellow cake
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Prepare a square pan (8 x 8 x 2-inch) by greasing it lightly with oil or special margarine and dusting with flour.
Add vanilla to eggs and beat until thick.
Gradually beat in sugar.
Sift together the sifted flour, baking powder and salt and stir into egg mixture.
Stir in milk and margarine or shortening that have been heated together until fat is melted. Beat 1 minute or until batter is smooth.
Pour into pan and bake about 25 minutes.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Brown hamburger, onion and bell pepper.
Add tomatoes and noodles.
Put in a casserole and pour a can of Cheddar soup over the top.
Let brown in oven at 375°.

title: spinach quiche
directions: Saute chopped onions in butter.
Cook spinach according to package directions; drain thoroughly.
Combine onions, spinach, Swiss cheese and beaten eggs.
Add milk and seasonings.
Pour into pastry shell and bake at 350° for 40 minutes or until knife comes out clean.

title: festive fruit salad
directions: Clean and peel all of the fruit.
If using canned fruit, drain the juice.
Cut into bite-size chunks.
Toss all of the ingredients in a large bowl.
Sprinkle with sugar, if desired.

title: stromboli
directions: Put bread into bread pan and let rise until double its size. Roll out and spread into cookie sheets. Let rise a little more. Place ham down middle of dough and put pepperoni on top of ham and then place cheese on top of pepperoni.
Take both sides of dough and fold to meet in middle.
Pinch ends together.
Put in 400° oven for 10 minutes.

title: fudgy bonbons
directions: In saucepan, melt butter and chocolate morsels.
When melted, add milk.
Mix until smooth.
Add vanilla.
Take off heat and add flour and pecans (optional).
Mix thoroughly.
Unwrap Hershey's Hugs.
Wrap dough around Hugs, then form into small balls.
Put on ungreased cookie sheet about 1-inch apart.
Bake in preheated oven for 6 minutes at 325°.
You can drizzle white chocolate over top when cooled.

title: bean dinner
directions: Add everything together and stir well.
Cook as long as you want.
You can substitute different types of beans or add to what's here.
If using a crock-pot for all day cooking use low.

title: skillet spaghetti
directions: In large skillet, add Wesson oil.
Break up ground beef.
Add onion and green pepper.
Cook until done; drain.
Add other ingredients and cook until done.
Cook spaghetti in another pot; drain.
Add sauce.
Serve with Parmesan cheese.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: zucchini souffle
directions: Mix in order.
Put in greased 9 x 9-inch pan.
Bake in 350° oven for 40 minutes.

title: crazy fudge
directions: Melt Velveeta cheese and butter together.
Add powdered sugar, vanilla, cocoa and nuts; stir like crazy and pour onto greased pan.
Mixture is thick.
Pat out with buttered hands.
Makes 5 pounds and keeps well.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Boil broccoli 5 minutes and drain.
Combine beaten eggs, mayonnaise, minced onions, grated cheese and cream of celery soup. Salt and pepper to taste.
Top with buttered cracker crumbs (any kind).
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: microwave stuffed green peppers
directions: Wash peppers. Cut in half lengthwise.
Remove seeds and white membrane.
In a mixing bowl, combine meat, rice, seasonings, egg and 1/2 cup tomato sauce.
Mound mixture in pepper halves.
Place in a microproof casserole dish. Stir bouillon crystals into remaining tomato sauce. Spoon over peppers. Cover and cook on High (maximum power) for 15 minutes.
Let stand 5 minutes. Makes 6 servings.

title: oriental beef
directions: Cut meat into strips, 1/4-inch wide and 2 to 3 inches long. Brown in small amount of oil; drain.
Add 1 cup water, soy sauce and chopped onion.
Cover and simmer 45 minutes.
Then add carrot, celery, green pepper, mushrooms, water chestnuts and salt to taste.
Cover and cook 15 to 20 minutes; do not overcook.
Combine cold water and cornstarch and gradually add to hot meat and vegetables, stirring constantly until mixture boils and thickens. Serve over rice.
Yields 4 servings.

title: punch bowl cake
directions: Make cake layers.
Cool completely.
Prepare instant pudding by package.
Refrigerate to set up.
Place one cake layer in bottom of an 11-quart glass bowl.
Add, in layers, 1/2 of the ingredients in the following order:
pineapple, pudding, cherry pie filling, coconut, fruit cocktail, nuts and Cool Whip.
Add 2nd cake layer and repeat layers in the same order. Garnish top with cherries, nuts or more coconut.
Refrigerate.
Serves 35 people. To serve, large spoon down side of bowl to 1st cake for all ingredients.

title: lime punch
directions: Mix Jell-O and hot water.
Add all other ingredients.
Mix well and serve over ice.

title: almond joy cake
directions: Mix cake as directed.
Divide in half and bake in 2 (9 x 13-inch) pans for 20 minutes at 350°.
While cakes are baking, mix 1 cup milk and 1 cup sugar; bring to a boil.
Remove from heat and add marshmallows.
Stir until dissolved and add coconut.
Pour over cakes.
Mix 1 1/2 cups sugar, 1/2 cup canned milk and margarine.
Heat to a boil.
Remove and add chocolate chips.
Stir until dissolved.
Sprinkle almonds on cakes, then drizzle chocolate mixture over each cake.
This cake freezes very well. Very rich but sure is good.
No calories of course.

title: chocolate no-bake cookies
directions: Measure the vanilla, peanut butter and oats; set aside.
Mix the first 4 ingredients in a heavy 4-quart saucepan.
Cook and stir on high.
As soon as the mixture boils, set a timer for 1 minute.
Boil for exactly 1 minute, then remove from heat and stir in the last 3 ingredients.
Mix thoroughly and drop by tablespoonful onto waxed paper.
Let cool.
Yields 20 cookies, 200 calories each.

title: kentucky corn bread
directions: In a large bowl, hand mix with a wooden spoon the melted butter and eggs.
Add the sour cream, creamed corn and drained, whole kernel corn.
Mix together until blended.
Add the Jiffy corn muffin mix and mix together until blended.
Pour batter into greased 9 1/2 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes to 1 hour or until top is a deep golden brown.
Cut to serve.

title: white bean soup
directions: Heat oil in large, heavy saucepan.
Saute onion and garlic until tender; add chicken broth, beans, salt, Italian seasoning, 1/2 teaspoon basil and pepper.
Bring to a boil; simmer 10 minutes.
Puree in blender or food processor.
Return to saucepan. Stir in evaporated milk slowly; heat through.
Garnish with fresh basil.
Makes approximately 4 cups.

title: cut-out cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add eggs and vanilla.
Sift dry ingredients; add to creamed mixture alternately with sour cream. For best results, refrigerate overnight.
Roll and cut out cookies.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: eagle brand milk
directions: Combine all ingredients in container of blender; process until smooth.
Store in refrigerator until ready to use.
Makes about 1 1/4 cups, the same amount as a 14 ounce can of store bought.

title: strawberry pies
directions: Mix all ingredients, except for strawberries, and bring to a boil.
Cool completely.
Place sliced strawberries into 2 baked and cooled pie crusts.
Pour filling over berries.
Chill until firm. Serve with Cool Whip.

title: snickerdoodles
directions: Cream together the margarine, shortening, sugar and vanilla. Add egg and milk.
Add mixture to dry ingredients.
Drop by rounded teaspoonful on ungreased baking sheet.
Dip flat bottomed glass in water, then in granulated sugar and flatten each cookie with glass.
Bake at 400° for 12 minutes.
(It usually takes less than allotted time; try 10 minutes, until cookies are very lightly browned around the edges.)

title: hot tamale pie
directions: Mix cold water with 1 cup of corn meal.
Put 4 cups of water to boil; add salt.
Stir in the cold meal mix and 2 more cups of corn meal.
Cook for at least 1 hour in double boiler, stirring often.
Add chili powder and set aside.

title: mango chutney
directions: Put lemon in an open enamel or stainless steel kettle.
Add sugar, vinegar, garlic, salt and cayenne pepper.
Boil for 30 minutes.
Stir frequently.
Add mangoes, raisins and ginger. Simmer until fruit is tender, but not mushy (about 30 minutes). Ladle boiling chutney into sterilized jars.
Cap with two piece screw band lids.
Makes about 3 pints.

title: deluxe apple crunch
directions: Spread apples in buttered 9-inch baking dish.
Cover with white sugar and sprinkle with nutmeg or cinnamon. Blend remaining ingredients until mixture resembles coarse meal.
Spread over apples.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.
Serve with whipped cream or ice cream.

title: crock-pot dressing
directions: Mix all ingredients and cook in crock-pot for 2 hours on high and 4 hours on low. Add cooked chicken just before dressing is finished.

title: scones
directions: Mix dry ingredients together.
Cut in shortening with fingers until crumbly.
Add milk and currants.
Mix well.

title: crescent chicken
directions: Boil chicken with sage and 1/2 stick butter.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Cool and remove from bone.
Cut up.
Blend with cream cheese and mix with mushrooms.
Spread out each crescent roll and place 1 tablespoon chicken mixture on each roll.
Roll and pinch together.
Roll each roll in melted butter and then in stuffing mix.
Place on cookie sheet and bake until rolls are done at 375°, about 15 to 20 minutes.
Make gravy with broth (and mushrooms if desired) or chicken soup.
Serve over rolls.

title: boiled chocolate cookies
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients together and let boil 3 minutes. Remove from heat.
Add peanut butter and oatmeal.
Mix well.
Drop by teaspoon on waxed paper.
Let cool.

title: maple walnut cake
directions: Mix sugar, eggs and shortening together.
Add Mapleine.
Add flour; mix baking powder with the milk.
Add to other ingredients. Add walnuts.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes in a 9 x 13-inch pan. Frost with Mapleine flavored frosting.

title: mock sour cream
directions: Put all ingredients into a blender on medium-high until smooth and creamy.

title: salmon(grilled or in the oven)
directions: Place steaks on foil.
Make a mixture of the mayonnaise, cheese, Worcestershire sauce and mix well.
Brush over salmon. Fold foil over salmon and grill or bake in a 350-375 degree oven for 20 minutes.

title: easy deluxe brownies
directions: Mix together brownie mix, eggs, water, oil and flour. Stir in chocolate chips and chopped nuts. Bake at 350° for 30-35 minutes.

title: chili chicken stew
directions: Cut chicken into 1-inch pieces.
Cook chicken and next 3 ingredients in hot oil in a Dutch oven until lightly browned.
Add tomatoes and next 5 ingredients; cover, reduce heat and simmer 20 minutes.
Top individual serving with remaining ingredients.

title: ice cream dessert
directions: Mix first four ingredients and cook 15 minutes on cookie sheet at 400°.
Break up when cooled.
Place 1/2 of first four ingredients in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Place sliced ice cream on top. Add other 1/2 of first four ingredients on top, then ice cream. Add caramel sauce and sprinkle chopped nuts on top.
Place in freezer.
When ready to serve, remove from freezer a short time before serving.

title: terrific tacos(i should know, i've made a million!)
directions: Heat oil for tortillas.
In saucepan, add ketchup to meat to give flavor and moisture.
Fry tortillas and drain on plate with paper towels.
Immediately add meat mixture, onion, grated cheese, lettuce and tomatoes.
These are time consuming to make, but always a favorite.
Use your favorite hot sauce or salsa at table.

title: cheese cake
directions: Have eggs at room temperature.
Beat egg whites.
Set aside. At slow speed, mix sour cream, sugar, cream cheese, egg yolks and flavorings.
Fold in egg whites.
Pour mixture onto crust in spring-form pan.
Bake 1 hour and 15 minutes at 325°.
Turn off oven and allow cake to remain in oven for 30 more minutes.
Allow to cool slightly before removing from pan.

title: fudge pie
directions: Mix sugar, flour and cocoa.
Stir in egg yolks and milk.
Add butter while cooking. Cook until thick and a little longer.
Use a double boiler.

title: santa fe casserole bake
directions: Brown meat; drain fat.
Add taco spices and seasonings; blend well.
In small bowl blend broth and flour; add to meat mixture. Stir in sour cream and chiles; blend well.
Pour into a greased baking dish; place 1/2 chips.
Top with 1/2 beef mixture and 1/2 of sauce, 1/2 of cheese and 1/2 of green onions.
Layer, ending with green onions.
Bake uncovered dish in 375° oven for 20 minutes. Let stand 5 minutes before cutting.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook squash in small amount of water until tender.
Drain well and mash.
Add salt and pepper.
Combine soup, carrots, onion, sour cream and butter, blending well.
Add squash, stirring gently.
Alternate layers of squash, mixture and bread crumbs in greased 2-quart casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: pecan pie
directions: Beat eggs, sugar, salt, butter and corn syrup together with rotary beater.
Mix in pecans.
Pour into pastry crust (9-inch pie pan).
Bake 40 to 50 minutes or until set and pastry is brown.

title: potato or pumpkin pie
directions: Mix ingredients and place into pie shells.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes and lower to 350° till done.

title: pineapple-cheese muffins
directions: Heat
oven
to
Line
12 medium muffin cups with paper baking
cups.
Mix pineapple (with juice) and remaining ingredients.
Beat vigorously 30 seconds.
Fill cups 2/3 full. Bake
until
light golden brown and wooden pick inserted comes out clean, about 15 minutes.
Makes 12 muffins.

title: cherry mash candy
directions: Mix vanilla frosting mix, cherry frosting mix, maraschino cherries, condensed milk and powdered sugar.
Roll into very small balls and freeze.
Melt semi-sweet chips and paraffin together then add peanuts to chocolate mixture.
Dip frozen balls into the chocolate mixture and place on wax paper to dry.

title: onion shortbread
directions: For topping:
Melt butter in skillet.
Add onions and saute until tender.
Let cool just a little and add sour cream, dill and half the cheese.

title: date loaf candy
directions: Mix ingredients together with enough milk to wet mixture. Cook until forms a firm ball in cold water.
Pour candy on a wet cloth, roll up and slice when it is cold.

title: pudding cookies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix all ingredients, except sugar, until dough forms a ball.
Shape dough into balls, using 1 teaspoon for each.
Place on ungreased baking sheet.
Dip bottom of a drinking glass into sugar; press dough balls to flatten.
Bake about 8 minutes.
Makes 2 to 2 1/2 dozen cookies.

title: chocolate sheet cake
directions: Bring oleo, shortening, cocoa and water to a boil.
Mix together
the
sugar, flour, buttermilk, eggs, soda, cinnamon, vanilla and salt, then
add
the
chocolate mixture.
Mix well and pour into greased and
floured
16 x 11-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: strawberry salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in hot water.
Add frozen strawberries, unthawed, and stir until berries separate.
Add undrained pineapple.
Pour half of mixture into 9 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Chill in refrigerator until set.
Leave the other half at room temperature.

title: gran-mama's ice cream
directions: Beat eggs good.
Add sugar, Pet milk, vanilla and sweet milk. Pour in freezer, then add rest of sweet milk.

title: cold linguini
directions: Mix well.
Marinate overnight. Stir before serving.

title: dirt dessert
directions: Mix pudding and milk until creamy.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Pour into a plastic pot.
Sprinkle cookie crumbs on top.
Put flowers in for decoration.
Serve with a trowel.

title: awesome frozen punch
directions: Mix together the jello and 9 cups boiling water; let cool. Bring the sugar and 4 cups water to a boil.
Let cool, then add to jello mixture.
Add lemon juice and pineapple juice.
Freeze in two 1-gallon plastic containers.
When ready to serve, take containers out of freezer about 1 hour before serving time.
(You will probably have to cut the bottom out of the containers to get mixture out.)
Put in large punch bowl.
Add the ginger ale or 7-Up; stir until slushy.
You can just use one of the gallon containers with 1 bottle of ginger ale and keep the other frozen to use at a later time.

title: raspberry cordial
directions: Combine ingredients in a 3-quart jar and cover.
Put in a cool, dark place.
Stir well once each week for eight weeks. Strain through a cheesecloth-lined sieve.

title: cocoa mix
directions: Place 1/4 to 1/2 cocoa mix in cup, then add hot water.
Stir briskly.

title: homemade picante sauce
directions: Place stewed tomatoes in saucepan with diced onion; bring to simmer.
Add all other ingredients, except cilantro.
While sauce is simmering, dice small amount of cilantro, then put in sauce. Keep it simmering until onion turns transparent.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Makes 1 1/2 quarts.
Keep in fridge.
It will stay good for up to 2 weeks.

title: jan hagel
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease a jelly roll pan.
Mix butter, sugar and egg yolk.
Blend flour and cinnamon into butter mixture.
Pat into pan.
Beat water and egg white until frothy; brush over dough. Sprinkle with nuts.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes.
Cut immediately into finger-like strips.

title: meat loaf
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine all ingredients; mix well. Press firmly into ungreased loaf pan.
Bake for 1 hour.
Let stand for 5 minutes before serving.

title: hot dog bean soup
directions: Soak beans and drain.
Place beans and next 5 ingredients in Dutch oven; stir well.
Bring to boil.
Reduce heat and simmer, uncovered, 2 hours or until beans are tender.
Remove 1/2 cup bean mixture and blend smooth.
Set aside.

title: grandma schneider's sweet pickles
directions: Wash pickles and slice to 1/2-inch thick.
Put in salt water for 7 days.
Cover with a plate and a weight on top of crock.
The 8th day, pour off salt water and cover with boiling water.
Let stand 24 hours and then pour off.
Day 9, dissolve 1/4 cup alum in boiling water, enough to cover pickles.
Let stand 24 hours.
Day 10, drain and then take 12 cups sugar and 10 cups vinegar and a small handful (1/8 cup) pickling spices.
Heat and pour over pickles.
Let stand 24 hours.
Day 11, 12 and 13, pour brine into pan and heat and pour back on pickles.
On the 14th day, heat pickles and brine together and can.
(Pour hot pickles into jars and seal.)

title: apple sauce cake
directions: Cream sugar and butter. Add eggs, beat well. Sift together flour, soda, cloves and cinnamon. Add dry ingredients to creamed mixture. Alternatively with applesauce, fold in raisins and nuts dredged with half cup flour. Serve in greased floured loaf pan. Bake one hour at 350 degrees.

title: beef dip
directions: Mix all together and chill overnight. Serve with crackers or chips.

title: butterscotch delight
directions: Mix the first 3 ingredients together and press into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 18 minutes or until light brown.
Cool.
Mix powdered sugar, Cool Whip and cream cheese (softened) and pour over the cooled crust.
Mix butterscotch pudding with milk as directed on the box.
Pour over and top with Cool Whip.
Enjoy!

title: tangy lemon chicken
directions: Combine flour, salt and paprika in paper or plastic bag. Brush chicken with lemon juice.
Place a few pieces at a time in bag.
Shake to coat.
Heat Crisco oil to 365° in electric skillet or on medium/high heat in large heavy skillet.
Add chicken. Brown.
Combine water and bouillon granules.
Stir until dissolved.
Add brown sugar and remaining lemon juice.
Pour into skillet.
Cover.
Reduce heat to 250° or low.
Simmer 5 minutes. Turn chicken.
Sprinkle with onion and lemon peel.
Re-cover. Simmer 10 minutes.
Serve garnished with lemon slices and additional parsley, if desired.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Simmer raisins and water over low heat until tender (about 20 minutes).
Drain liquid into a measuring cup.
Add enough water to make 1/2 cup.
Heat oven to 400°.

title: chocolate pound cake
directions: Sift dry ingredients together.
Cream butter and sugar until very light.
Add 4 of the eggs, one at a time, beating thoroughly after each addition.
Add dry ingredients and milk alternately to the creamed mixture.
Add the vanilla, then thoroughly beat the last egg into the batter.
Pour into 10-inch tube pan that has been greased and lightly floured.
Bake in 325° oven for 1 1/2 hours.
Let cool in pan for 10 minutes, then turn out on cake rack and finish cooling.

title: lemon pie and meringue
directions: Melt margarine or butter in baking dish; mix crackers and spread evenly over dish for pie crust.
Beat egg yolks and add milk, lemon juice and rind; mix well by beating.
Add filling to baking dish.

title: apple loaf
directions: Mix apples and 2 cups sugar in a large bowl; leave at room temperature 2 hours stirring occasionally.
Heat oven to 325°. Grease two 8 1/2 x 4 1/2-inch loaf pans.
Melt butter, let cool. Mix flour, baking soda and cinnamon; stir into apples.
Stir in butter, eggs and vanilla.
Pour half into each pan, sprinkle each with 1 teaspoon sugar.
Bake 1 1/4 to 1 1/2 hours until a wooden pick inserted in centers of loaves comes out clear.
Cool in pans 10 minutes before removing.
Refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Mix.
Pour this mixture over fruit mixture.
Bake in center of a 350° oven until golden brown, about 30 minutes.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Peel and quarter number of potatoes desired.
Mix together equal parts of flour and Parmesan cheese.
Coat potatoes well. Season with salt, pepper, garlic salt and seasoning salt.
Melt oleo.
Mix with potatoes.
Bake at 375° until done, stirring often to prevent sticking.

title: citrus waldorf salad
directions: Gently combine all ingredients.

title: brownies
directions: In 8 x 8-inch square pan on stove, melt butter and chocolate squares.
Add sugar and vanilla.
Add beaten eggs and flour.
Mix until smooth.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Before baking, top by sprinkling nuts on top.

title: ting - a - ling
directions: Melt chocolate over hot - not boiling - water. Add other ingredients. Mix well. Drop by teaspoonfuls on wax paper. Allow to cool and harden.

title: cream cheese tuna dip
directions: Stir milk, 1 tablespoon at a time, into cream cheese.
Mix in mayonnaise, onions, horseradish, pepper sauce and Worcestershire sauce.
Stir in tuna; sprinkle with paprika.
Cover and refrigerate at least 1 hour.
Serve with snacks.
Makes about 2 1/2 cups.

title: date bars
directions: Pit dates and cut into quarters.
Mix together flour, baking powder, salt and sugar.
Add dates and nuts to flour mixture. Beat eggs.
Add melted butter and combine mixtures.
Bake in 8 x 12-inch pan for 30 minutes at 350°.
When slightly cool, cut into bars.
Roll each bar in powdered sugar.

title: homemade bread
directions: Mix yeast and warm water together until dissolved.
Add sugar, oil, egg and salt.
Mix thoroughly.
Add half of flour and mix thoroughly.
Add the remaining flour and gradually knead as it is added.
Place into a well-greased large bowl.
Turn once to make sure dough mixture is well-greased.
Cover or put foil over bowl and chill at least 2 hours.

title: healthy turkey burgers
directions: In medium size bowl, mix turkey and all of the ingredients in order.
Form into two large patties on aluminum foil and refrigerate for 15 minutes.

title: potato refrigerator rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in water and add a pinch of sugar.
Set aside. Mix thoroughly mashed potatoes, shortening, sugar, salt and scalded milk.
Let mixture cool to lukewarm then add eggs and yeast mixture.
Stir in enough flour to make a good kneadable dough.
Knead for 5 minutes.
Put in a large greased bowl.	Turn dough over to coat top.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Pinch dough off to form balls.
Place in greased muffin tins using 2 balls each.
Let raise until double.
Bake at 425 degrees for 12-15 minutes until golden brown.

title: buttermilk chicken dinner(microwave)
directions: In a 3-quart casserole, combine water, bouillon granules, thyme, rosemary and bay leaves.
Rinse chicken and pat dry.
Place chicken, breast side down, in casserole.
Cook, covered, on 100% power (10 minutes).
Turn chicken over.

title: easy yeast rolls
directions: Pour cold water over yeast and let stand.
Using an electric mixer, combine shortening, sugar and eggs.
Continue to beat mixture and add boiling water.
Let stand until cool.
Add yeast mixture, flour and salt.
Mix well.
Cover and refrigerate.
When ready to use, punch down dough and knead lightly.
Shape into balls and place in greased muffin pans.
Brush lightly with melted butter.
Let rise 1 to 2 hours or until double in size.
Bake in preheated 375° oven for 18 to 22 minutes.
Yields 3 dozen.

title: greek pasta and shrimp salad
directions: Cook pasta until al dente; drain and toss with 1 tablespoon olive oil.
In skillet, melt butter; add olive oil and garlic. Stir until garlic colors slightly.
Add shrimp, oregano, salt and pepper and cook until shrimp turns pink; remove from heat.
In large serving bowl, combine pasta and cheese.
Fold in shrimp mixture.
Let stand at room temperature to blend flavors.

title: broccoli and rice casserole
directions: Cook rice.
Cook broccoli; drain and mash.
Mix onions, celery and margarine with Cheez Whiz.
Pour rice and broccoli over other mixture.
Add mushroom soup; mix well.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: orange ice cream
directions: Mix all ingredients and freeze in one gallon ice cream freezer according to manufacturer's directions for ice and salt for freezing.

title: macaroni and tuna
directions: Mix macaroni and cheese dinner according to package directions.
Add tuna fish.
For extra taste, seasoned salt may be added.

title: sunday dinner squash casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together and top with cheese and Ritz crackers.
Cook at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: barbara's green beans
directions: Layer 1 can beans, 1/2 onion, 1 can beans and remainder of onion. Heat until sugar is dissolved the sugar, vinegar and bacon drippings. Pour heated mixture over beans and onion which you have layered in Pyrex casserole. Crumble bacon over top and cover with aluminum foil. Bake in 350° oven for 45 minutes. Remove foil and continue to bake 15 minutes longer.

title: apple crisp
directions: Line baking dish with peeled, sliced apples.
Sift together sugar, flour and baking powder.
Break an egg into dry ingredients and toss with a fork until crumbly.
Sprinkle over apples. Drizzle 1/3 cup melted butter over top.
Bake at 375° for 25 to 35 minutes or until brown.

title: chocolate cream cheese pound cake
directions: Cream margarine and cream cheese at room temperature.
Add sugar and cream well.
Mix cocoa and flour.
Add 3 eggs (2 if using large eggs), 1 cup flour and cocoa mixture and vanilla, beating well.
Add 2 eggs and 1 cup flour and cocoa mixture, beating well again, then add last 2 eggs and rest of flour and cocoa mixture. Beat until creamy.
Pour into large 10-inch tube pan that has been well-greased and floured.
Put into cold oven.
Turn oven to 275° and bake for 1 1/2 to 2 hours.

title: apple cake
directions: Pour sugar over apples and let stand.
In a separate bowl, beat the egg whites until stiff.
Add egg yolks and stir.
Add cooking oil to the egg mixture; beat well and let stand.
In another bowl, mix together pecans, flour, soda, salt and cinnamon. Pour egg mixture over apples, then add dry ingredients.
Stir with a spoon.
Pour in a greased tube pan or Bundt pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until done.

title: quickie strawberry "shortcut" cake
directions: Grease 13 x 9-inch cake pan.
Spread marshmallows over the bottom.
Mix cake according to box directions.
Spread carefully over marshmallows.
Stir dry gelatin into strawberries until dissolved.
Spoon over cake batter.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes until cake tests done.
Serve warm or cool, topped with whipped cream, if desired.

title: pineapple upside-down cake
directions: Take 10-inch iron skillet, melt margarine and brown sugar and mix.
Place pineapple rings around pan.
Put cherries in each of the pineapple holes.
Pour cake batter over this and bake.

title: oriental beef and broccoli
directions: Heat oil in skillet.
Stir-fry meat.
Add vegetables and stir-fry.
Mix soy sauce, oyster sauce and water together, then add to meat and vegetables.
Cook for 1 minute.

title: macaroni and cheese deluxe
directions: Cook macaroni according to package directions.
Drain, rinse and set aside.
Combine next 6 ingredients.
Add macaroni and stir well.
Spoon into lightly greased 2-quart casserole.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Yield:
6 to 8 servings.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Lightly grease a 9 x 13-inch casserole dish.
Put mashed potatoes in dish.
Beat eggs lightly; add margarine, brown sugar, granulated sugar, cinnamon, nutmeg or cloves and cereal.
Pour over potatoes.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Stir and cut egg mixture into potatoes.
Bake 30 minutes more.
Top with chopped pecans and marshmallows.
Broil until lightly browned.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: one-bowl chocolate cake
directions: Sift dry ingredients together.
Add remaining ingredients, then slowly add 2 cups water and mix well until all ingredients are well blended.
Pour into a well-greased loaf pan (9 x 13-inch), which has been lined with *wax paper.
Bake at 350° for about 45 minutes.
Remove wax paper immediately after cake is baked.
Frost with your favorite powder sugar icing after the cake has cooled or just dust the top with powdered sugar.

title: best tomatoes
directions: Peel tomatoes; quarter.
Marinate tomatoes in all other ingredients for 3 to 4 hours.

title: cocktail sausage surprise with sauce
directions: Heat together chili sauce and jelly, constantly stirring, until jelly melts and mixture is a smooth consistency.
Add cocktail sausages and heat in sauce mixture for approximately 15 minutes, making sure that sausages are completely coated.
Place all in a chafing dish and keep hot.
Have toothpicks available for handling.

title: cathead biscuits
directions: Mix flour, mayonnaise and buttermilk.
Beat in sweet milk until biscuits are of dropping consistency, too sticky to roll, but stiff enough to sit up.
Drop by big spoonfuls on greased griddle or baking sheets and bake in preheated 350° oven until brown.

title: spinach casserole
directions: Beat eggs and flour; mix well with other ingredients. Bake at 350° for 1 hour (approximately).

title: henrietta hunt morgan's black cake(lexington recipe)
directions: Mix one tablespoon of flour, one teaspoon salt, one teaspoon mustard, one tablespoon sugar and a speck of cayenne pepper.
Add 2 tablespoons of melted butter, two egg yolks and three fourths cup of milk.
Cook in a double boiler until it thickens, stirring constantly.
Then add three tablespoons of vinegar and boil one minute.

title: tortilla chip pie
directions: Layer chips in bottom of a casserole dish.
Brown hamburger in skillet.
Drain and add can of chili, olives and water.
Simmer 15 minutes. Then pour over chips.
Sprinkle a few chopped onions and cheese over this.
Then layer the remaining chips on this and add more onions and cheese.
Heat in oven at 350° for 20 minutes or until cheese is melted.

title: honey glazed carrots
directions: Cook carrots and drain if necessary.
Add remaining ingredients.
Heat 5 to 10 minutes.

title: hi mein
directions: In wok or large saucepan, saute onions and garlic in oil.
Add 2 tablespoons soy sauce.
Add meat and cook until almost done. Add carrots, bamboo shoots, cabbage stems and 2 cups water.
Cook mixture for 3 minutes.
(You may adjust according to your taste.) Add 2 to 3 tablespoons soy sauce and 2 tablespoons sesame oil. Mix well.
Add the cornstarch mix, stirring vigorously, and add cabbage leaves.
Remove from heat and add to linguini.
Add 2 tablespoons sesame oil.
Mix well and serve.

title: m&m party cookies
directions: Blend shortening and sugars. Beat in vanilla and eggs. Sift remaining dry ingredients together. Add to the egg and sugar mixture; mix well. Stir in 1/2 cup M&M's. Save the rest of the M&M's for decorating. Drop from teaspoon onto ungreased cookie sheet. Decorate top of cookies with remaining M&M's. Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Cover and chill.
Bake at 375° for 8 minutes on greased cookie sheet.
Put a Hershey's Kiss on top of each cookie when they come out of oven.
Makes 3 dozen.

title: moisty-rich devil's food cake
directions: In bowl cream first 4 ingredients together.
Pour in boiling water and mix.
Add milk and eggs.
Mix in flour, salt and soda. Beat with mixer until all ingredients are well blended.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch greased cake pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: breakfast drink
directions: Blend at low speed until smooth and frothy.
Can add sugar if you want a sweeter taste.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in hot water and cool. Add rest of ingredients. Pour into 9 x 13 baking dish until set.

title: ground beef vegetable soup
directions: Brown beef and onions.
Add remaining ingredients.
Follow directions on brown gravy mix.
Cook 1 1/2 hours.
Add 1/2 cup elbow macaroni and cook until tender.

title: mom's pistachio pie
directions: Spread creamy mixture on top of thoroughly cooled crust and refrigerate. Spread 1-1/2 can lemon pudding/pie filling (or chocolate) on top of cheese layer. Spread Cool Whip on top and refrigerate.

title: butterfinger cake
directions: Use 1/2 of angel food cake and break into pieces.
Put in bottom of 13 x 9-inch cake pan.
Blend butter, egg yolks and powdered sugar.
Fold Cool Whip into mixture.
Spread 1/2 of batter over crumbled cake.
Sprinkle 3 crushed Butterfingers over mixture.
Repeat second layer the same (crumbled cake, batter and Butterfingers).
